msgid "deathly touch"
msgstr "toque mortal"

#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:44
msgid "Learn Crimson Arts"
msgstr "Aprender Artes Carmesíes"

#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:153
msgid "Invokes aura of light"
msgstr "Invoca aura de luz"

#. [illuminates], id=illumination
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:164
msgid "illuminates"
msgstr "ilumina"

#. [illuminates], id=illumination
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:165
msgid "female^illuminates"
msgstr "ilumina"

#. [illuminates], id=illumination
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:166
msgid ""
"This unit illuminates the surrounding area, making lawful units fight "
"better, and chaotic units fight worse.\n"
"\n"
"Any units adjacent to this unit will fight as if it were dusk when it is "
"night, and as if it were day when it is dusk."
msgstr ""
"Esta unidad ilumina el área que le rodea, haciendo que las unidades legales "
"luchen mejor, y las caóticas peor.\n"
"\n"
"Cualquier unidad adyacente a ésta luchará como si estuviera atardeciendo "
"cuando es de noche, y como si fuera de día cuando está atardeciendo."

#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:184
msgid "able to heal 10 hp per turn"
msgstr "capaz de sanar 10 PV por turno"

#. [heals], id=ultraheal
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:195
msgid "heals +10"
msgstr "sana +10"

#. [heals], id=ultraheal
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:196
msgid "female^heals +10"
msgstr "sana +10"

#. [heals], id=ultraheal
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:197
msgid ""
"This unit combines herbal remedies with magic to heal units more quickly "
"than is normally possible on the battlefield.\n"
"\n"
"A unit cared for by this healer may heal up to 10 HP per turn, and be cured "
"from poisoning."
msgstr ""
"Esta unidad combina remedios herbales con magia para sanar unidades más "
"rápido de lo que normalmente es posible en el campo de batalla.\n"
"\n"
"Una unidad atendida por este sanador puede sanarse hasta 10 PV por turno y "
"ser curada del envenenamiento."

#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:214
msgid "Draw energy from the moonlight and the starlight"
msgstr "Extraer energía de la luz de la luna y las estrellas"

#. [leadership], id=uranometria
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:224
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/Celestial_Master.cfg:29
msgid "uranometria"
msgstr "uranometría"

#. [leadership], id=uranometria
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:225
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/Celestial_Master.cfg:30
msgid "female^uranometria"
msgstr "uranometría"

#. [leadership], id=uranometria
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:226
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/Celestial_Master.cfg:31
msgid ""
"This unit channels the light of the moon and of the stars to ward of the "
"nocturnal darkness, thus strengthening itself in 25%."
msgstr ""
"Esta unidad canaliza la luz de la luna y de las estrellas para repeler la "
"oscuridad nocturna, fortaleciéndose así en un 25 %."

#. [variation], id=merwe1
#. [variation], id=merwe2
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:258 War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:288
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:319
msgid "Adept of Light"
msgstr "Adepto de la Luz"

#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:268
msgid ""
"Certain female mage apprentices are chosen from admission into the academies "
"to study the magic of light. After graduation, they become Adepts. These "
"magi can summon the Light in the form of energy balls and are able cure "
"wounded allies."
msgstr ""
"Ciertas aprendices magas son elegidas desde su ingreso a las academias para "
"estudiar la magia de la luz. Después de graduarse, se convierten en Adeptas. "
"Estas magas pueden invocar la Luz en forma de bolas de energía y son capaces "
"de curar a aliados heridos."

#. [variation], id=merwe3
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:330
msgid "Cleric"
msgstr "Clérigo"

#. [variation], id=merwe4
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Merwe.cfg:342
msgid "Prophetess of Light"
msgstr "Profetisa de la Luz"

#. [unit_type], id=Ethereal Orb, race=elemental
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Orb.cfg:5
msgid "Ethereal Orb"
msgstr "Orbe etéreo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ethereal Orb, race=elemental
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Orb.cfg:34
msgid ""
"Some magic servants, after gathering enough power, can become an orb of "
"arcane energy. These orbs are light, but very dense, and are difficult to "
"shatter or destroy. They can heal nearby allies and bind parts of themselves "
"as bolts of unstable energy."
msgstr ""
"Algunos sirvientes mágicos, tras reunir suficiente poder, pueden convertirse "
"en un orbe de energía arcana. Estos orbes son ligeros, pero muy densos, y "
"resultan difíciles de romper o destruir. Pueden sanar a aliados cercanos y "
"proyectar partes de sí mismos como descargas de energía inestable."

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Orb.cfg:59
msgid "ethereal wave"
msgstr "onda etérea"

#. [unit_type], id=SaTarva, race=washraha, gender=female
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/SaTarva.cfg:4
msgid "Amazon Princess"
msgstr "Princesa Amazona"

#. [unit_type], id=SaTarva, race=washraha, gender=female
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/SaTarva.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Sa-Tarva is the only child of Emperor Tarva Ghar of Shray Tahl. Having been "
"born in the Washrahan society, she was already destined to live a life of "
"fighting, but fate reserved even more battles for her: because the Empress "
"died birthing Sa-Tarva, the Emperor had no more children - he didn't want to "
"marry any other woman - and he was never happy that his only descendant was "
"a woman. In order to prove herself worthy at the eyes of her father and of "
"her countrymen, Sa-Tarva trained harder than any other child of her "
"generation in the art of war, starting from before sunrise and only stopping "
"when the moon was high on the sky. Furthermore, she avidly learned from her "
"father's best generals. The results of such harsh training are visible: at "
"age twenty-five, Sa-Tarva is a fearsome warrior and a skilled tactician, "
"capable of shooting volleys of arrows while most archers would shoot only "
"three at best, and also of leading her brothers and sisters-at-arms to the "
"most unexpected victories."
msgstr ""
"Sa-Tarva es la única hija del Emperador Tarva Ghar de Shray Tahl. Al haber "
"nacido en la sociedad washraha, ya estaba destinada a vivir una vida de "
"combate, pero el destino le reservó aún más batallas: porque la Emperatriz "
"murió al dar a luz a Sa-Tarva, el Emperador no tuvo más hijos —no quería "
"casarse con ninguna otra mujer— y nunca estuvo feliz de que su única "
"descendiente fuera una mujer. Para demostrarse digna a los ojos de su padre "
"y de sus compatriotas, Sa-Tarva se entrenó más duro que cualquier otro niño "
"de su generación en el arte de la guerra, comenzando antes del amanecer y "
"deteniéndose solo cuando la luna estaba alta en el cielo. Además, aprendió "
"ávidamente de los mejores generales de su padre. Los resultados de un "
"entrenamiento tan duro son visibles: a los veinticinco años, Sa-Tarva es una "
"guerrera temible y una hábil estratega, capaz de disparar salvas de flechas "
"mientras la mayoría de los arqueros solo dispararían tres como máximo, y "
"también de liderar a sus hermanos y hermanas de armas hacia las victorias "
"más inesperadas."

