#. [unit_type], id=Atseger, race=maatkarian, gender=female
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Silver_Master_Atseger.cfg:4
msgid "Silver Master"
msgstr "Maestra de Plata"

#. [unit_type], id=Atseger, race=maatkarian, gender=female
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Silver_Master_Atseger.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Atseger of Khem, formerly known as Atseger of Iolca, is the highly respected "
"Headmistress of the Academy of Maat'Kare, and one of the brightest "
"Maat'Karian mages in History; a Master of the Lucent, Crimson and Umbra "
"arts, she's most famous for having deciphered the Windsong Teleporting Spell "
"- a feat that not even Menon himself had succeeded - and learning it "
"herself, thus becoming the first known non-Windsong human to teleport.\n"
"Nevertheless, all this renown and admiration only came later in her life; "
"during both her childhood and her youth, she was only famous for being the "
"daughter of an exiled noblewoman of Skiron and of a Maat'Karia general who "
"disgraced himself by leading his men to a crushing defeat in a battle "
"against Lich-Lord Aegaion. As if that wasn't enough, her father died when "
"she was young, and so she had to take care of her mother, who was affected "
"by an incurable dark disease that slowly consumed her health. In her "
"miserable life at the town of Khem, the young Atseger thought that she would "
"never be able to pursue her dream of becoming a Master - but it all changed "
"the day she met Menon Hekare. Sensing that she had a huge magic potential "
"inside her, the Master of Four Lights invited her to join the Academy; when "
"she retorted that she had to take care of her mother, Menon offered to pay "
"her a room at Maat'Kare's Central Healing Sanctum.\n"
"Thus, Atseger and her mother moved to the City of the Sun, and the former "
"joined the grand Academy, where she met Sadjet Merewi, then her senior, and "
"who would become her life-long friend. After marking her name in Maat'Kare's "
"History for her accomplishments in the magical arts, Menon appointed her as "
"the Academy's Headmistress. Resolved not to disappoint the man to whom she "
"owed everything, Atseger fully dedicates herself to guiding the Academy and "
"its students, so that it will keep producing the finest magic-users in all "
"of Netjer-Ta."
msgstr ""
"Atseger de Khem, anteriormente conocida como Atseger de Iolca, es la "
"altamente respetada Directora de la Academia de Maat'Kare, y una de las "
"magas maat'karianas más brillantes de la Historia; Maestra de las artes "
"Lucientes, Carmesíes y Umbra, es más famosa por haber descifrado el Hechizo "
"de Teletransportación de las Hijas del Viento —una hazaña que ni siquiera "
"Menon mismo había logrado— y aprenderlo ella misma, convirtiéndose así en la "
"primera humana no Hija del Viento conocida en teletransportarse.\n"
"Sin embargo, toda esta fama y admiración solo llegó más tarde en su vida; "
"durante tanto su infancia como su juventud, solo era famosa por ser la hija "
"de una noble exiliada de Skiron y de un general maat'kariano que se deshonró "
"al llevar a sus hombres a una aplastante derrota en una batalla contra el "
"Señor Liche Aegaion. Como si eso no fuera suficiente, su padre murió cuando "
"ella era joven, y por eso tuvo que cuidar de su madre, que estaba afectada "
"por una enfermedad oscura incurable que lentamente consumía su salud. En su "
"miserable vida en la ciudad de Khem, la joven Atseger pensó que nunca podría "
"perseguir su sueño de convertirse en Maestra, pero todo cambió el día que "
"conoció a Menon Hekare. Sintiendo que tenía un enorme potencial mágico "
"dentro de ella, el Maestro de las Cuatro Luces la invitó a unirse a la "
"Academia; cuando ella respondió que tenía que cuidar de su madre, Menon se "
"ofreció a pagarle una habitación en el Santuario Central de Sanación de "
"Maat'Kare.\n"
"Así, Atseger y su madre se mudaron a la Ciudad del Sol, y la primera se unió "
"a la gran Academia, donde conoció a Sadjet Merewi, entonces su superiora, y "
"quien se convertiría en su amiga de toda la vida. Después de marcar su "
"nombre en la Historia de Maat'Kare por sus logros en las artes mágicas, "
"Menon la nombró Directora de la Academia. Resuelta a no decepcionar al "
"hombre al que le debía todo, Atseger se dedica completamente a guiar la "
"Academia y a sus estudiantes, para que siga produciendo los mejores usuarios "
"de magia en todo Netjer-Ta."

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Silver_Master_Atseger.cfg:72
msgid "Gaze of Medusa"
msgstr "Mirada de Medusa"

#. [unit_type], id=Spearman, race=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Skiron_Army.cfg:17
msgid "Hoplite"
msgstr "Hoplita"

#. [unit_type], id=Spearman, race=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Skiron_Army.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Hoplites are the most basic human military unit of Skiron; albeit they may "
"lack in training, the long spears they use can be a threat to many "
"opponents, as they'll often hit the enemy before it can even get close to "
"the Hoplites."
msgstr ""
"Los hoplitas son la unidad militar humana más básica de Skiron; aunque "
"pueden carecer de entrenamiento, las largas lanzas que usan pueden ser una "
"amenaza para muchos oponentes, ya que a menudo golpearán al enemigo antes de "
"que pueda siquiera acercarse a los hoplitas."

#. [unit_type], id=Pikeman, race=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Skiron_Army.cfg:33
msgid "Sarissa"
msgstr "Sarissa"

#. [unit_type], id=Pikeman, race=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Skiron_Army.cfg:36
msgid ""
"Hoplites with greater reflexes, strength and resiliency will receive better "
"equipment and longer spears called sarissa, to which this unit owes its name."
msgstr ""
"Los hoplitas con mejores reflejos, fuerza y resistencia recibirán mejor "
"equipo y lanzas más largas llamadas sarissa, a las que esta unidad debe su "
"nombre."

#. [unit_type], id=Halberdier, race=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Skiron_Army.cfg:49
msgid "Phalanx"
msgstr "Falange"

#. [unit_type], id=Halberdier, race=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Skiron_Army.cfg:51
msgid ""
"The elite of Skiron's living infantry, Phalanxes disdain the use of spears "
"in favour of much more powerful and deadlier halberds. Once the pride of the "
"Imperial armies, Phalanxes have lost much importance to undead warriors, but "
"they have not lost their honour, and so they will fight to death in order to "
"reclaim their old prestige."
msgstr ""
"La élite de la infantería viva de Skiron, las Falanges desdeñan el uso de "
"lanzas a favor de alabardas mucho más poderosas y mortales. Una vez el "
"orgullo de los ejércitos imperiales, las Falanges han perdido mucha "
"importancia frente a los guerreros no muertos, pero no han perdido su honor, "
"y por eso lucharán hasta la muerte para recuperar su antiguo prestigio."

#. [unit_type], id=Bowman, race=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Skiron_Army.cfg:68
msgid ""
"In contradition to the history of their ancestors, Skironians have never "
"valued archery so much. This might be due to the fact that most wars they "
"have fought were against centaurs, whose archery skills surpassed that of "
"even the best human archer - which means that using bows and arrows against "
"them was highly impractical. Still, no Skironian commander has ever "
"underestimated the importance of having ranged units in their army; and no "
"bowman has ever allowed them to forget that."
msgstr ""
"En contradicción con la historia de sus ancestros, los skironianos nunca han "
"valorado tanto la arquería. Esto podría deberse al hecho de que la mayoría "
"de las guerras que han librado fueron contra centauros, cuyas habilidades "
"con el arco superaban incluso a las del mejor arquero humano, lo que "
"significa que usar arcos y flechas contra ellos era muy poco práctico. Aun "
"así, ningún comandante skironiano ha subestimado nunca la importancia de "
"tener unidades a distancia en su ejército; y ningún arquero les ha permitido "
"olvidarlo."

#. [unit_type], id=Longbowman, race=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Skiron_Army.cfg:83
msgid ""
"Those who have mastered the use of the short bow may be challenged with a "
"larger, more powerful version of that weapon. Longbows are harder to use, "
"but they can hit targets much farther away, and with greater precision."
msgstr ""
"Aquellos que han dominado el uso del arco corto pueden ser desafiados con "
"una versión más grande y poderosa de esa arma. Los arcos largos son más "
"difíciles de usar, pero pueden alcanzar objetivos mucho más lejos y con "
"mayor precisión."

#. [unit_type], id=Master Bowman, race=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Skiron_Army.cfg:96
msgid "Sagitarius"
msgstr "Sagitario"

#. [unit_type], id=Master Bowman, race=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Skiron_Army.cfg:98
msgid ""
"There is a very popular Skironian legend about an archer who managed to beat "
"the champion of the centaurs in a duel by shooting his opponent's arrow with "
"his own. Whether this hero actually existed or not is open for debate; his "
"name, however, has since been used as a title by the finest Skironian bowmen "
"- and the fact that no one dares to challenge their right to use it tells a "
"great deal about their own skill."
msgstr ""
"Existe una leyenda skironia muy popular sobre un arquero que logró vencer al "
"campeón de los centauros en un duelo disparando la flecha de su oponente con "
"la suya propia. Si este héroe realmente existió o no está abierto al debate; "
"sin embargo, su nombre ha sido usado desde entonces como un título por los "
"mejores arqueros skironianos, y el hecho de que nadie se atreva a desafiar "
"su derecho a usarlo dice mucho sobre su propia habilidad."

#. [unit_type], id=Dark Sorcerer, race=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Skiron_Army.cfg:143
msgid "Dark Priest"
msgstr "Sacerdote Oscuro"

#. [female]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Skiron_Army.cfg:145
msgid "female^Dark Priestess"
msgstr "Sacerdotisa Oscura"

#. [unit_type], id=Duelist, race=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Skiron_Army.cfg:160
msgid ""
"When the Aerian Dinasty was brought to an end by Aegaion, a great shift in "
"power took place in Skiron. Noblemen who formerly held great power and ruled "
"entire provinces were replaced by Lich-Lords - who, by their turn, "
"'following the people's request', punished the fallen nobility for their old "
"abuses of power by turning them into undead aberrations. Some Lich-Lords did "
"forgive the noblemen from their own provinces, but forced them to train as "
"fighters in order to atone for the exploitation they once imposed on "
"commoners. These noblemen know that they are being used and toyed with - "
"after all, they wear no armour, and so their chances of dying in battle are "
"high - but they do not complain, for this is a far better fate than many of "
"their class have received at the hands of the twisted new lords of Skiron."
msgstr ""
"Cuando la Dinastía Aeriana fue terminada por Aegaion, se produjo un gran "
"cambio de poder en Skiron. Los nobles que antes tenían gran poder y "
"gobernaban provincias enteras fueron reemplazados por Señores Liche, "
"quienes, a su vez, «siguiendo la petición del pueblo», castigaron a la "
"nobleza caída por sus viejos abusos de poder convirtiéndolos en aberraciones "
"no muertas. Algunos Señores Liche sí perdonaron a los nobles de sus propias "
"provincias, pero los obligaron a entrenarse como luchadores para expiar la "
"explotación que una vez impusieron sobre los plebeyos. Estos nobles saben "
"que están siendo usados y manipulados —después de todo, no usan armadura, "
"por lo que sus probabilidades de morir en batalla son altas—, pero no se "
"quejan, porque este es un destino mucho mejor que el que muchos de su clase "
"han recibido a manos de los nuevos señores retorcidos de Skiron."

#. [unit_type], id=Duelist, race=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Skiron_Army.cfg:161
msgid "Nobleman"
msgstr "Noble"

#. [unit_type], id=Lich Lady, race=undead
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Stygia.cfg:4
msgid "Lich-Lady"
msgstr "Señora Liche"

#. [unit_type], id=Lich Lady, race=undead
#. [unit_type], id=Lich Lord WotJ, race=undead
#. [unit_type], id=Lich Lord Jevyan, race=undead
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Stygia.cfg:22
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/undead/Lich_Lord.cfg:23
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/undead/Lich_Lord_Jevyan.cfg:23
msgid ""
"The Order of the Lich-Lords is the nobility of the Empire of Skiron, men and "
"women who have traded their humanity for immortality, adding a great level "
"of magical power to their already vast political power. Their arts are "
"uncannily similar to the Umbra Arts, even though they've never even had a "
"glimpse of the Book of the Dead; the source of their mysterious and immense "
"powers is something that frightens even the Maat'Karians."
msgstr ""
"La Orden de los Señores Liche es la nobleza del Imperio de Skiron, hombres y "
"mujeres que han cambiado su humanidad por la inmortalidad, añadiendo un gran "
"nivel de poder mágico a su ya vasto poder político. Sus artes son "
"sorprendentemente similares a las Artes Umbra, aunque nunca han tenido "
"siquiera un vistazo al Libro de los Muertos; la fuente de sus misteriosos e "
"inmensos poderes es algo que asusta incluso a los maat'karianos."

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=melee
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Stygia.cfg:35
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/undead/Aegaion.cfg:38
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/undead/Lich_Lord.cfg:47
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/undead/Lich_Lord_Jevyan.cfg:47
msgid "baneblade"
msgstr "espada de la perdición"

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Stygia.cfg:47
msgid "Acheron's Wave"
msgstr "Ola de Aqueronte"

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Stygia.cfg:59
msgid "Cocytus' Despair"
msgstr "Desesperación de Cocito"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Stygia.cfg:72
msgid "Phlegeton's Unleashing"
msgstr "Liberación de Flegetonte"

#. [attack], type=cold, range=ranged
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Stygia.cfg:85
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/undead/Aegaion.cfg:78
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/undead/Lich_Lord.cfg:84
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/undead/Lich_Lord_Jevyan.cfg:97
msgid "March of the Cacodaemones"
msgstr "Marcha de los Cacodaemones"

#. [unit_type], id=Sword Dancer Nyx, race=vampire, gender=female
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Sword_Dancer_Nyx.cfg:5
msgid "Sword Dancer"
msgstr "Espadalchin Danzante"

#. [unit_type], id=Sword Dancer Nyx, race=vampire, gender=female
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Sword_Dancer_Nyx.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Vampires live a long time, and have time to develop many social graces, "
"including dance. Duelists who have spent extended amounts of time fighting, "
"and dancing see similarities between the two, and combine them into a "
"devastating and accurate form of fighting that cuts through defenses."
msgstr ""
"Los vampiros viven mucho tiempo y tienen tiempo para desarrollar muchas "
"gracias sociales, incluyendo el baile. Los duelistas que han pasado largos "
"períodos luchando y bailando ven similitudes entre ambos y los combinan en "
"una forma de lucha devastadora y precisa que atraviesa las defensas."

#. [unit_type], id=Thug
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:22
msgid "Villager"
msgstr "Aldeano"

#. [unit_type], id=Thug
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Peasants live in the small hamlets and villages scattered across the Green "
"Isle."
msgstr ""
"Los campesinos viven en las pequeñas aldeas y pueblos dispersos por la Isla "
"Verde."

#. [unit_type], id=Bandit
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:38
msgid "Village Elder"
msgstr "Anciano del Pueblo"

#. [unit_type], id=Bandit
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:41
msgid ""
"Each of the villages scattered across the Green Isle is normally guided by a "
"group of elders, who are the village’s wisest and most experienced residents."
msgstr ""
"Cada uno de los pueblos dispersos por la Isla Verde normalmente es guiado "
"por un grupo de ancianos, que son los residentes más sabios y experimentados "
"del pueblo."

#. [unit_type], id=Highwayman, gender=female
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:54
msgid "Senior Village Elder"
msgstr "Anciana Principal del Pueblo"

#. [unit_type], id=Highwayman, gender=female
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:58
msgid ""
"The entire village looks to the senior elder for guidance. Strong and wise, "
"the senior elders take responsibility for the community’s well-being on "
"their shoulders. Provincial officials tend to choose senior village elders "
"as magistrates so that legal and customary authority will coincide."
msgstr ""
"Todo el pueblo mira al anciano principal en busca de guía. Fuertes y sabios, "
"los ancianos principales asumen la responsabilidad del bienestar de la "
"comunidad sobre sus hombros. Los funcionarios provinciales tienden a elegir "
"a los ancianos principales del pueblo como magistrados para que la autoridad "
"legal y consuetudinaria coincidan."

#. [female]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:60
msgid "female^Senior Village Elder"
msgstr "Anciana Principal del Pueblo"

#. [unit_type], id=Footpad
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:121
msgid "Peasant Youth"
msgstr "Joven Campesino"

#. [unit_type], id=Footpad
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:125
msgid ""
"The scruffy-haired peasant youth are much like the young people living "
"elsewhere in the Green Isle: reckless, cocky, and eager to explore."
msgstr ""
"Los jóvenes campesinos de cabello desaliñado son muy parecidos a los jóvenes "
"que viven en otros lugares de la Isla Verde: imprudentes, arrogantes y "
"ansiosos por explorar."

#. [female]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:131
msgid "female^Peasant Youth"
msgstr "Joven Campesina"

#. [unit_type], id=Outlaw
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:145
msgid "Watchman"
msgstr "Vigilante"

#. [unit_type], id=Outlaw
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:150
msgid ""
"The watchmen are men and women who protect the villages from marauders, both "
"human and otherwise, that prowl the Green Isle at night."
msgstr ""
"Los vigilantes son hombres y mujeres que protegen los pueblos de "
"merodeadores, tanto humanos como de otro tipo, que acechan la Isla Verde por "
"la noche."

#. [female]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:152
msgid "female^Watchwoman"
msgstr "Vigilante"

#. [unit_type], id=Fugitive
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:166
msgid "Borderer"
msgstr "Fronterizo"

#. [unit_type], id=Fugitive
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:171
msgid ""
"Border villages maintain militias dedicated to fending off hostiles. While "
"these borderers are not trained and armed to up to military standards, their "
"native toughness and knowledge of local conditions make them formidable on "
"their home ground."
msgstr ""
"Los pueblos fronterizos mantienen milicias dedicadas a repeler a los "
"hostiles. Aunque estos fronterizos no están entrenados ni armados hasta "
"estándares militares, su dureza nativa y conocimiento de las condiciones "
"locales los hacen formidables en su terreno natal."

#. [female]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:173
msgid "female^Borderer"
msgstr "Fronteriza"

#. [unit_type], id=Poacher
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:192
msgid "Peasant Hunter"
msgstr "Cazador Campesino"

#. [unit_type], id=Poacher
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:195
msgid ""
"Villages, especially in wilder areas near frontiers, rely on hunters to "
"bring in much of their food supply. Their stealth and intimate knowledge of "
"local terrain can be valuable assets in combat."
msgstr ""
"Los pueblos, especialmente en áreas más salvajes cerca de las fronteras, "
"dependen de los cazadores para traer gran parte de su suministro de comida. "
"Su sigilo y conocimiento íntimo del terreno local pueden ser activos "
"valiosos en combate."

#. [unit_type], id=Trapper
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:208
msgid "Peasant Trapper"
msgstr "Trampero Campesino"

#. [unit_type], id=Trapper
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:212
msgid ""
"Trappers are skilled hunters who supply food and furs for several villages. "
"Their hunting experience makes them most valuable at night and in forests "
"and swamps."
msgstr ""
"Los tramperos son cazadores hábiles que suministran comida y pieles para "
"varios pueblos. Su experiencia en la caza los hace más valiosos por la noche "
"y en bosques y pantanos."

#. [unit_type], id=Huntsman
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:225
msgid "Peasant Huntsman"
msgstr "Cazador Campesino Experto"

#. [unit_type], id=Huntsman
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:230
msgid ""
"Huntsmen have spent their lives in the backwoods and swamps of their "
"wilderness homes. They can bullseye ferocious swamp rats and track anything "
"that moves in their territory."
msgstr ""
"Los cazadores han pasado sus vidas en los bosques y pantanos de sus hogares "
"salvajes. Pueden acertar en el centro a ratas de pantano feroces y rastrear "
"cualquier cosa que se mueva en su territorio."

#. [unit_type], id=Thief
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:247
msgid "Peasant Minuteman"
msgstr "Milicia Campesina"

#. [unit_type], id=Thief
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:252
msgid ""
"In moments of greatest need, every single able-bodied person of a village "
"will join the fight, using whatever weapon is available; even the knives "
"used for cooking and eating will come in hand."
msgstr ""
"En momentos de mayor necesidad, cada persona capaz de un pueblo se unirá a "
"la lucha, usando cualquier arma disponible; incluso los cuchillos usados "
"para cocinar y comer servirán."

#. [female]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:254
msgid "female^Peasant Minutewoman"
msgstr "Milicia Campesina"

#. [unit_type], id=Rogue
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:268
msgid "Peasant Militia"
msgstr "Milicia Campesina"

#. [unit_type], id=Rogue
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:273
msgid ""
"Knife-throwing is a popular play amongst the youths of the Green Isle; a "
"good knife thrower will often be regarded as a 'cool' and 'strong' person, "
"though elderly people will most likely consider them as delinquents."
msgstr ""
"Lanzar cuchillos es un juego popular entre los jóvenes de la Isla Verde; un "
"buen lanzador de cuchillos a menudo será considerado como una persona "
"«genial» y «fuerte», aunque las personas mayores probablemente los "
"consideren delincuentes."

#. [female]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:275
msgid "female^Peasant Militia"
msgstr "Milicia Campesina"

#. [unit_type], id=Assassin
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:289
msgid "Dagger Expert"
msgstr "Experto en Dagas"

#. [unit_type], id=Assassin
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:296
msgid ""
"The most profficient knife-wielders are often feared as being equal to a "
"criminal, and many of them are shunned by their fellow villagers. Forced to "
"wander about the Green Isle on their own, they hide their faces in order not "
"to be recognized and arrested, but in truth most of them are actually law-"
"abiding and helpful towards other travellers."
msgstr ""
"Los más hábiles con los cuchillos a menudo son temidos como si fueran "
"criminales, y muchos de ellos son rechazados por sus conciudadanos. "
"Obligados a vagar solos por la Isla Verde, ocultan sus rostros para no ser "
"reconocidos y arrestados, pero en verdad la mayoría son realmente "
"respetuosos de la ley y útiles hacia otros viajeros."

#. [female]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/Villagers.cfg:298
msgid "female^Dagger Expert"
msgstr "Experta en Dagas"

#. [unit_type], id=Ancient Feral Dragon, race=monster
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/ancient_feral_dragon.cfg:7
msgid "Ancient Feral Dragon"
msgstr "Dragón Salvaje Antiguo"

#. [unit_type], id=Ancient Feral Dragon, race=monster
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/ancient_feral_dragon.cfg:22
msgid ""
"A dragon is a legendary creature, normally seen only in fantastic tales. "
"They are very rare, and were it not for the historical events, the "
"singlehanded destruction of cities and towns that these creatures have "
"wrought, they might be dismissed as mere myth. Legends are very specific "
"about the ravages of dragons; noting their great strength, speed, their "
"preternatural cunning, and above all else, the great fire that burns inside "
"of them.\n"
"\n"
"The ancient library of Anaktoron records some details regarding the solitary "
"nature of dragons, impossible to verify in more recent times. They did not "
"appear to suffer the presence of other dragons. On the few occasions they "
"have been observed in pairs, the occasion was a fight to the death, most "
"often between an adult and a juvenile presumably attempting to establish "
"territory. In no case was a juvenile observed to survive these encounters. \n"
"\n"
"Though dragons have not been observed to mate, it is known that they lay "
"eggs. These eggs however, are peculiar in that they do not hatch in the "
"presence of the parent. They have been observed to lie in the dragon's lair "
"for hundreds of years, with hatchlings emerging only after the death of the "
"parent or, in some rare but significant cases, removal of the eggs from the "
"lair.\n"
"\n"
"It is presumed that these peculiar habits exist by reason of the vast "
"territory required to provide meat, which dragons consume in large "
"quantites.\n"
"\n"
"Battling a dragon is said to be the pinnacle of danger itself, fit only for "
"fools or the bravest of knights."
msgstr ""
"Un dragón es una criatura legendaria, normalmente vista solo en cuentos "
"fantásticos. Son muy raros, y si no fuera por los eventos históricos, la "
"destrucción individual de ciudades y pueblos que estas criaturas han "
"causado, podrían ser descartados como mera mitología. Las leyendas son muy "
"específicas sobre las devastaciones de los dragones; notando su gran fuerza, "
"velocidad, su astucia sobrenatural, y por encima de todo, el gran fuego que "
"arde dentro de ellos.\n"
"\n"
"La antigua biblioteca de Anaktoron registra algunos detalles sobre la "
"naturaleza solitaria de los dragones, imposibles de verificar en tiempos más "
"recientes. No parecían soportar la presencia de otros dragones. En las pocas "
"ocasiones en que se les ha observado en parejas, la ocasión fue una pelea a "
"muerte, la mayoría de las veces entre un adulto y un juvenil que "
"presumiblemente intentaba establecer territorio. En ningún caso se observó "
"que un juvenil sobreviviera a estos encuentros.\n"
"\n"
"Aunque no se ha observado que los dragones se apareen, se sabe que ponen "
"huevos. Estos huevos, sin embargo, son peculiares en que no eclosionan en "
"presencia del padre. Se ha observado que yacen en la guarida del dragón "
"durante cientos de años, con crías emergiendo solo después de la muerte del "
"padre o, en algunos casos raros pero significativos, la remoción de los "
"huevos de la guarida.\n"
"\n"
"Se presume que estos hábitos peculiares existen debido al vasto territorio "
"requerido para proporcionar carne, que los dragones consumen en grandes "
"cantidades.\n"
"\n"
"Luchar contra un dragón se dice que es el pináculo del peligro mismo, "
"adecuado solo para tontos o los más valientes de los caballeros."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/ancient_feral_dragon.cfg:37
msgid "bite"
msgstr "mordisco"

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/ancient_feral_dragon.cfg:46
msgid "tail"
msgstr "coletazo"

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/ancient_feral_dragon.cfg:55
msgid "fire breath"
msgstr "aliento ardiente"

#. [race], id=celestial
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/celestials.cfg:9
msgid "race^Celestial"
msgstr "Celestial"

#. [race], id=celestial
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/celestials.cfg:10
msgid "race+female^Celestial"
msgstr "Celestial"

#. [race], id=celestial
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/celestials.cfg:11
msgid "race^Celestials"
msgstr "Celestiales"

#. [race], id=celestial
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/celestials.cfg:15
msgid ""
"The Celestials have vestigial wings that for most of them do not mature. "
"Celestials believe that light and darkness each have power, and they choose "
"as a culture to fight for the light, and to spread it through-out the world. "
"They are a militaristic society with great law and order that gives them "
"strength and unity which caries over into their style of fighting. The order "
"and unified purpose of celestial society tends to make them form larger "
"nations than the other factions giving the Celestials great military "
"strength."
msgstr ""
"Los celestiales tienen alas vestigiales que en la mayoría no llegan a "
"desarrollarse. Los celestiales creen que la luz y la oscuridad tienen poder "
"propio, y eligen como cultura luchar por la luz y difundirla por todo el "
"mundo. Son una sociedad militarista con gran ley y orden que les otorga "
"fuerza y unidad, lo que se refleja en su estilo de combate. El orden y "
"propósito unificado de la sociedad celestial tiende a hacer que formen "
"naciones más grandes que otras facciones, otorgando a los celestiales una "
"gran fuerza militar."

#. [race], id=chomi
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/chomi.cfg:7
msgid "race^Chom"
msgstr "Chom"

#. [race], id=chomi
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/chomi.cfg:8
msgid "race+female^Chom"
msgstr "Chom"

#. [race], id=chomi
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/chomi.cfg:9
msgid "race^Chomi"
msgstr "Chomi"

#. [race], id=chomi
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/chomi.cfg:13
msgid ""
"The Chomi are a people, or a confederation of culturally similar tribes, who "
"lived on the northern shores of the continent of Arajunna. They were "
"numerous, had relatively large cities and were good at sailing and trading, "
"but weren't very strong in terms of military, and their settlements weren't "
"fortified; thus, they were constantly being harassed by the neighbouring "
"Washraha and, in rarer occasions, by the giants known as Deshra.\n"
"\n"
"They stand out amongst the dwellers of Arajunna for their knowledge of "
"seafaring skills. Indeed, the sea plays a large role in the Chomi culture, "
"being the main source of the food they eat, the main defence against both "
"Washraha and Deshra (who are both afraid of the sea) and the stage of many "
"of their legends. Their vessels, albeit frail, can endure long journeys in "
"the stormy seas to the north of Arajunna.\n"
"\n"
"Each of the Chomi tribes is ruled by its own king; other than through "
"commerce, those tribes didn't have any strong relationship with each other. "
"Even though they do not excel at war, even the Washraha fear the day the "
"Chomi cities-state will unite, for such a day might mark the beginning of a "
"new era in the whole continent, such is the strength of the Chomi culture."
msgstr ""
"Los Chomi son un pueblo, o una confederación de tribus culturalmente "
"similares, que vivía en las costas norteñas del continente de Arajunna. Eran "
"numerosos, tenían ciudades relativamente grandes y eran buenos navegando y "
"comerciando, pero no eran muy fuertes en términos militares, y sus "
"asentamientos no estaban fortificados; por eso eran constantemente acosados "
"por los vecinos Washraha y, en ocasiones más raras, por los gigantes "
"conocidos como Deshra.\n"
"\n"
"Se destacan entre los habitantes de Arajunna por su conocimiento de las "
"habilidades marítimas. En efecto, el mar juega un papel importante en la "
"cultura chomi, siendo la principal fuente de alimento que comen, la "
"principal defensa contra tanto los Washraha como los Deshra (quienes temen "
"al mar) y el escenario de muchas de sus leyendas. Sus embarcaciones, aunque "
"frágiles, pueden soportar largos viajes en los mares tormentosos al norte de "
"Arajunna.\n"
"\n"
"Cada una de las tribus chomi es gobernada por su propio rey; aparte del "
"comercio, esas tribus no tenían ninguna relación fuerte entre sí. Aunque no "
"destacan en la guerra, incluso los Washraha temen el día en que las ciudades-"
"estado chomi se unan, pues tal día podría marcar el comienzo de una nueva "
"era en todo el continente, tal es la fuerza de la cultura chomi."

#. [unit_type], id=Seraph, race=celestial
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/d4_Seraphin.cfg:5
msgid "Seraph"
msgstr "Serafín"

#. [unit_type], id=Seraph, race=celestial
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/d4_Seraphin.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Exalted is the title given to the mightiest of winged celestials. They are "
"honored to the point where they are no longer considered officers in the "
"army, but rather the manifestation of glory. Few  exist that fight with "
"greater strength, or with greater ability to inspire and lead."
msgstr ""
"Exaltado es el título que reciben los celestiales alados más poderosos. Son "
"honrados hasta el punto de que ya no se les considera oficiales del "
"ejército, sino la manifestación misma de la gloria. Pocos luchan con mayor "
"fuerza o con mayor capacidad para inspirar y liderar."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/d4_Seraphin.cfg:36
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/wargs/c2_Warrior_Warg.cfg:24
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/wargs/c3_Pack_Leader.cfg:28
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/wargs/c4_Garou.cfg:29
msgid "Sword"
msgstr "Espada"

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/d4_Seraphin.cfg:48
msgid "heavenly light"
msgstr "luz celestial"

#. [female]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/d4_Seraphin.cfg:118
msgid "female^Seraph"
msgstr "Serafina"

#. [race], id=deshra
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/deshra.cfg:7
msgid "race^Deshra"
msgstr "Deshra"

#. [race], id=deshra
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/deshra.cfg:8
msgid "race+female^Deshra"
msgstr "Deshra"

#. [race], id=deshra
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/deshra.cfg:9
msgid "race^Deshrai"
msgstr "Deshrai"

#. [race], id=deshra
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/deshra.cfg:15
msgid "The Deshra (literally "
msgstr "Los Deshra (literalmente "

#. [race], id=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians.cfg:5
msgid "race^Maat'Karian"
msgstr "Maat'kariano"

#. [race], id=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians.cfg:6
msgid "race+female^Maat'Karian"
msgstr "Maat'kariana"

#. [race], id=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians.cfg:7
msgid "race^Maat'Karians"
msgstr "Maat'karianos"

#. [race], id=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians.cfg:11
msgid ""
"The Maat'Karians descend of Aragwaithi and Hannuks who journeyed from the "
"Great Continent to Netjer-Ta led by Myra of Hiera'Shirsha. They get their "
"name from the first city they built on their new land, Maat'Kare.\n"
"\t\n"
"Maat'Kare's History is full of challenges and conflicts. The first of them "
"concerned the Maat'Karians' consolidation as an unified culture: their "
"ancestors, the Hannuks and the Aragwaithi, were historical enemies, and none "
"of them was willing to abandon their own respective cultures to embrace the "
"other's. This schism's most critical moment happened when a large group of "
"Aragwaithi decided to abandon Maat'Kare and settle in Argea, a continent to "
"the south of Netjer-Ta. It was Kun'lun, a Sage of the city's third "
"generation, who found the way to unite both cultures: with the aid of her "
"scholars, she revived the ancient language of the Windsong and made its "
"learning obligatory in the the schools, later turning it into the city's "
"official language. This common tongue broke many of the cultural barriers "
"between both peoples; and it was so popular that, in the following "
"generations, more and more aspects of the ancient Windsong culture were "
"adopted by the Maat'Karians - including names and their main symbol, the "
"Winged Protectress.\n"
"\n"
"Maat'Karian society sets itself apart from most of the world's civilizations "
"for two things. The first is that the power to rule the nation is not "
"concentrated on the hands of a single person; rather, it's shared by two "
"governing bodies, the Chamber of Sages, formed the nation's oldest and "
"wisest individuals; and the Chamber of Lords, formed by the generals and the "
"rulers of the towns and even villages. Since these Lords can be stripped of "
"their title if the citizens are unsatisfied with them, one can say that "
"Maat'Kare is a near-democratic nation. The second thing is the Maat'Karians' "
"high level of education: even at the tiniest village, every child is sent to "
"schools maintained by the Academy, and thought subjects such as History, "
"Geography, Grammar and Math. Thus, they become very well-educated citizens, "
"and are more participative in the country's politics. Furthermore, if the "
"child shows signs of magical talents, he/she is granted a place at the "
"Academy of Maat'Kare, which is arguably the best magic academy in the world "
"for forming masters in nearly all areas of magic, including the Elemental "
"and the Dark Arts.\n"
"\n"
"The population of Maat'Kare has never been high. In order not to be forced "
"to expand and take lands from their allies, the Maat'Karians are only "
"allowed to have two children for couple - though this birth control was only "
"established much time after Maat'Kare's founding. There's little internal "
"migration amongst Maat'Karians, who generally live their entire lives in the "
"cities they're born at.\n"
"\n"
"The Maat'Karian nation's formed by many near-independent cities and towns "
"all over the Land's End peninsula, in Netjer-Ta's utmost east, and in "
"Tarkyn's Meadows, which separates the peninsula from the rest of the "
"continent. There are also many Migdols - or armed outposts - in farther "
"locations which are under Maat'Karian control, such as the Gnoll Swamps and "
"the Windswept Cliffs.\n"
"\n"
"Maat'Karians do not differ from other human peoples, even though they live "
"in a different environment - that is, except for their resistance against "
"high temperatures, a natural adaptation to the Land's End peninsula's heat "
"and sunniness. On the other hand, they're more vulnerable to cold than most "
"humans."
msgstr ""
"Los maat'karianos descienden de aragwaithi y hannuks que viajaron desde el "
"Gran Continente hasta Netjer-Ta liderados por Myra de Hiera'Shirsha. Reciben "
"su nombre de la primera ciudad que construyeron en su nueva tierra, "
"Maat'Kare.\n"
"\t\n"
"La historia de Maat'Kare está llena de desafíos y conflictos. El primero de "
"ellos concernió la consolidación de los maat'karianos como una cultura "
"unificada: sus ancestros, los hannuks y los aragwaithi, eran enemigos "
"históricos, y ninguno estaba dispuesto a abandonar su propia cultura para "
"abrazar la del otro. El momento más crítico de esta división ocurrió cuando "
"un gran grupo de aragwaithi decidió abandonar Maat'Kare y establecerse en "
"Argea, un continente al sur de Netjer-Ta. Fue Kun'lun, una Sabia de la "
"tercera generación de la ciudad, quien encontró la forma de unir ambas "
"culturas: con la ayuda de sus eruditos, revivió la antigua lengua de las "
"Hijas del Viento y hizo su aprendizaje obligatorio en las escuelas, "
"convirtiéndola luego en la lengua oficial de la ciudad. Esta lengua común "
"rompió muchas de las barreras culturales entre ambos pueblos; y fue tan "
"popular que, en las generaciones siguientes, cada vez más aspectos de la "
"antigua cultura de las Hijas del Viento fueron adoptados por los "
"maat'karianos —incluyendo nombres y su principal símbolo, la Protectora "
"Alada.\n"
"\n"
"La sociedad maat'kariana se distingue de la mayoría de las civilizaciones "
"del mundo por dos cosas. La primera es que el poder para gobernar la nación "
"no se concentra en las manos de una sola persona; más bien, se comparte "
"entre dos órganos de gobierno: la Cámara de Sabios, formada por los "
"individuos más viejos y sabios de la nación; y la Cámara de Señores, formada "
"por los generales y los gobernantes de las ciudades e incluso aldeas. Dado "
"que estos Señores pueden ser despojados de su título si los ciudadanos no "
"están satisfechos con ellos, se puede decir que Maat'Kare es una nación casi "
"democrática. La segunda cosa es el alto nivel de educación de los "
"maat'karianos: incluso en la aldea más pequeña, todos los niños son enviados "
"a escuelas mantenidas por la Academia, y se les enseña materias como "
"Historia, Geografía, Gramática y Matemáticas. Así, se convierten en "
"ciudadanos muy bien educados y más participativos en la política del país. "
"Además, si el niño muestra signos de talento mágico, se le concede un lugar "
"en la Academia de Maat'Kare, que es posiblemente la mejor academia de magia "
"del mundo para formar maestros en casi todas las áreas de la magia, "
"incluidas las Artes Elementales y las Artes Oscuras.\n"
"\n"
"La población de Maat'Kare nunca ha sido alta. Para no verse obligados a "
"expandirse y tomar tierras de sus aliados, a los maat'karianos solo se les "
"permite tener dos hijos por pareja —aunque este control de natalidad se "
"estableció mucho tiempo después de la fundación de Maat'Kare. Hay poca "
"migración interna entre los maat'karianos, quienes generalmente viven toda "
"su vida en las ciudades donde nacen.\n"
"\n"
"La nación maat'kariana está formada por muchas ciudades y pueblos casi "
"independientes en toda la península de Fin de la Tierra, en el extremo este "
"de Netjer-Ta, y en los Prados de Tarkyn, que separa la península del resto "
"del continente. También hay muchos Migdols —o puestos armados— en lugares "
"más lejanos que están bajo control maat'kariano, como los Pantanos de Gnolls "
"y los Acantilados Barridos por el Viento.\n"
"\n"
"Los maat'karianos no difieren de otros pueblos humanos, aunque viven en un "
"entorno diferente —es decir, excepto por su resistencia a las altas "
"temperaturas, una adaptación natural al calor y la soleada península de Fin "
"de la Tierra. Por otro lado, son más vulnerables al frío que la mayoría de "
"los humanos."

#. [race], id=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/skironians.cfg:5
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/skironians.cfg:6
msgid "Skironian"
msgstr "Skironiano"

#. [race], id=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/skironians.cfg:7
msgid "Skironians"
msgstr "Skironianos"

#. [race], id=skironian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/skironians.cfg:10
msgid ""
"The Skironians are a human civilization that have settled in the distant "
"continent of Argea centuries before the Founding of Wesnoth. Their ancestors "
"were, in their majority, ancient Aragwaithi who left the city of Maat'Kare "
"for not being willing to embrace the developing Maat'Karian culture in "
"detriment of their own ancestors' traditions.\n"
"\t\n"
"Their first years in Argea were hard, and they were nearly destroyed by the "
"land's older inhabitants, the orcs, the fauns and the centaurs. Their "
"salvation came when they found a chain of islands on the eastern coast; "
"taking advantage of their neighbours' lack of ships, they made themselves "
"unreachable in those islands, at the same time honing their own sailing "
"skills. When they were strong and numerous again, they launched many "
"campaigns on coastal tribes, reclaiming many lands and building more "
"cities.\n"
"\t\n"
"When most of Eastern Argea was under human control, the king of the city of "
"Aeria, Alexias, united his and all other cities into a single empire, which "
"he called Skiron after the name of the first of those islands to be settled. "
"Once united, the Argean humans built a thriving nation and a solid culture, "
"which rivalled Maat'Kare itself.\n"
"\n"
"However, the control of so many lands by a single aristocracy formed an "
"increasingly power-hungry elite. After a period of unstoppable growth, the "
"empire entered an age of gradual social degradation, which culminated with "
"the army growing weaker, and with the loss of many lands to orcs and "
"minotaurs.\n"
"\n"
"In this scenario of decay and social neglect, a leader rose amongst the "
"people with the courage and the power to defy the emperor. His name was "
"Aegaion, and he wielded fabulous power over life and death which the "
"Skironians, who did not practice magic, believed to be unrivalled even by "
"that of the Maat'Karians. Aegaion harnessed the population's revolt into a "
"army bent on toppling the Imperial Dinasty, thus starting a brutal civil "
"war.\n"
"\n"
"But the civilians, as angry and numerous as they were, could not match the "
"superior military might of Emperor Amphyon's armies. Seeing his forces being "
"crushed in the hundreds, Aegaion taught his most loyal followers some of his "
"own powers; and together, they raised a vast army of undead, before which "
"the Imperial forces fell in the thousands. After a reign of a thousand "
"years, Skiron's dinasty fell to the hands of Aegaion, who crowned himself "
"the new emperor and gave his closest followers administrative powers, naming "
"them Lich-Lords.\n"
"\n"
"The new Skiron quickly became a juggernaut like Argea had never seen, "
"retaking the lost lands and expanding the empire's borders to unprecedented "
"extent; the centaurs were the worst victims of this expansion, as they were "
"driven to near-extinction. Poverty was greatly diminished as well, and the "
"people hailed Aegaion as their 'Dark Saint'.\n"
"\n"
"But this power came at a cost. Albeit stronger and richer, Skiron became a "
"land of little freedom; twisted by the dark powers learned from Aegaion, "
"most Lich-Lords became tyrants; some were even known to use their own "
"subjects for dark experiments, and a few turned their own fiefs' entire "
"population into undead. Such was the price Skiron paid to become powerful "
"again."
msgstr ""
"Los skironianos son una civilización humana que se estableció en el lejano "
"continente de Argea siglos antes de la Fundación de Wesnoth. Sus ancestros "
"fueron, en su mayoría, antiguos aragwaiti que dejaron la ciudad de Maat'Kare "
"por no estar dispuestos a abrazar la cultura maat'kariana en desarrollo en "
"detrimento de las tradiciones de sus propios ancestros.\n"
"\t\n"
"Sus primeros años en Argea fueron duros, y casi fueron destruidos por los "
"habitantes más antiguos de la tierra, los orcos, los faunos y los centauros. "
"Su salvación llegó cuando encontraron una cadena de islas en la costa "
"oriental; aprovechando la falta de barcos de sus vecinos, se volvieron "
"inalcanzables en esas islas, al mismo tiempo que perfeccionaban sus propias "
"habilidades de navegación. Cuando volvieron a ser fuertes y numerosos, "
"lanzaron muchas campañas contra tribus costeras, recuperando muchas tierras "
"y construyendo más ciudades.\n"
"\t\n"
"Cuando la mayor parte del este de Argea estaba bajo control humano, el rey "
"de la ciudad de Aeria, Alexias, unió su ciudad y todas las demás en un solo "
"imperio, al que llamó Skiron en honor al nombre de la primera de esas islas "
"que se estableció. Una vez unidos, los humanos de Argea construyeron una "
"nación próspera y una cultura sólida, que rivalizaba con la propia "
"Maat'Kare.\n"
"\n"
"Sin embargo, el control de tantas tierras por una sola aristocracia formó "
"una élite cada vez más hambrienta de poder. Después de un período de "
"crecimiento  imparable, el imperio entró en una era de degradación social "
"gradual, que culminó con el ejército debilitándose y con la pérdida de "
"muchas tierras a manos de orcos y minotauros.\n"
"\n"
"En este escenario de decadencia y abandono social, surgió un líder entre el "
"pueblo con el coraje y el poder para desafiar al emperador. Su nombre era "
"Aegaion, y empuñaba un poder fabuloso sobre la vida y la muerte que los "
"skironianos, que no practicaban la magia, creían que no tenía rival ni "
"siquiera con el de los maat'karianos. Aegaion aprovechó la revuelta de la "
"población para formar un ejército decidido a derrocar a la Dinastía "
"Imperial, iniciando así una brutal guerra civil.\n"
"\n"
"Pero los civiles, por muy enojados y numerosos que fueran, no podían igualar "
"el poder militar superior de los ejércitos del Emperador Amphyon. Al ver sus "
"fuerzas siendo aplastadas por cientos, Aegaion enseñó a sus seguidores más "
"leales algunos de sus propios poderes; y juntos, levantaron un vasto "
"ejército de no muertos, ante el cual las fuerzas imperiales cayeron por "
"miles. Después de un reinado de mil años, la dinastía de Skiron cayó en "
"manos de Aegaion, quien se coronó a sí mismo como el nuevo emperador y dio a "
"sus seguidores más cercanos poderes administrativos, nombrándolos Señores "
"Liche.\n"
"\n"
"El nuevo Skiron rápidamente se convirtió en un gigante como Argea nunca "
"había visto, retomando las tierras perdidas y expandiendo las fronteras del "
"imperio a un alcance sin precedentes; los centauros fueron las peores "
"víctimas de esta expansión, ya que fueron llevados casi a la extinción. La "
"pobreza también se redujo enormemente, y el pueblo aclamó a Aegaion como su "
"«Santo Oscuro».\n"
"\n"
"Pero este poder tuvo un costo. Aunque más fuerte y rico, Skiron se convirtió "
"en una tierra de poca libertad; retorcido por los poderes oscuros aprendidos "
"de Aegaion, la mayoría de los Señores Liche se volvieron tiranos; algunos "
"incluso eran conocidos por usar a sus propios súbditos para experimentos "
"oscuros, y unos pocos convirtieron a toda la población de sus feudos en no "
"muertos. Ese fue el precio que Skiron pagó para volverse poderoso de nuevo."

#. [race], id=dryad
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/warg.cfg:5
msgid "race^Dryad"
msgstr "Dríada"

#. [race], id=dryad
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/warg.cfg:6
msgid "race^Dryads"
msgstr "Dríadas"

#. [race], id=warg
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/warg.cfg:20
msgid "race^Warg"
msgstr "Huargo"

#. [race], id=warg
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/warg.cfg:21
msgid "race+female^Warg"
msgstr "Huargo"

#. [race], id=warg
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/warg.cfg:22
msgid "race^Wargs"
msgstr "Huargos"

#. [race], id=warg
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/warg.cfg:26
msgid ""
"Warg are also known as wolfmen. They live in the wilds and woods in almost "
"any climate, some favor the lush jungle, others the arctic woods, others "
"alpine mountains. The warg tend to live in packs or clans, and establish "
"their hunting grounds where they tend not to like intruders. Although "
"hunters, they are for the most part peaceful, however they have a primal "
"blood-lust, that can be inspired by various things, especially if vampires "
"are involved."
msgstr ""
"Los huargos también son conocidos como hombres-lobo. Viven en zonas salvajes "
"y bosques en casi cualquier clima: algunos prefieren la selva exuberante, "
"otros los bosques árticos, otros las montañas alpinas. Los huargos suelen "
"vivir en manadas o clanes y establecen sus terrenos de caza donde no suelen "
"tolerar intrusos. Aunque son cazadores, en su mayoría son pacíficos; sin "
"embargo, tienen una sed de sangre primal que puede desencadenarse por varias "
"causas, especialmente si hay vampiros de por medio."

#. [race], id=washraha
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/washraha.cfg:7
msgid "race^Washraha"
msgstr "Washraha"

#. [race], id=washraha
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/washraha.cfg:8
msgid "race+female^Washrahani"
msgstr "Washrahani"

#. [race], id=washraha
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/washraha.cfg:9
msgid "race^Washrahan"
msgstr "Washrahan"

#. [race], id=washraha
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/washraha.cfg:14
msgid ""
"The nation of Washraha on Arajunna was formed when the Tarva dynasty came to "
"power and united several squabbling tribes and city-states to drive out the "
"giants known as Deshra. The ruler of the city-state of Shray Tahl, a warlord "
"known as Tarva Pah, was responsible for uniting these cities-state. His army "
"became known as the Washrajan, or knee-cutters, and they lent their name to "
"the resulting empire.\n"
"\n"
"When he became their first emperor, Tarva Pah became a fearful and paranoid "
"man. He instituted a paradigm of isolationism and xenophobia, building a "
"wall along their land borders as mighty Washrahan scouting groups watched "
"over the savannah and the mountains surrounding his lands, swiftly putting a "
"violent end to anyone who came exploring or seeking trade or refuge. These "
"policies were carried out by his successors for generations; the Washrahan "
"themselves often visited neighbouring lands and people, but with ill-"
"intention: for in the belligerent Washrahan culture, the warriors must be "
"constantly proving their mettle in combat, and so they are often raiding "
"smaller foreign tribes, though seldom destroying any of them completely.\n"
"\n"
"In the reign of Empress Sa-Tarva, however, the Washraha decided to expand, "
"razing countless towns and villages and conquering vast extensions of land, "
"becoming the absolute power in Arajunna. Their power became unrivalled "
"indeed, and it could have expanded to realms far beyond their continent, "
"were it not for the Washraha's almost superstitious fear of the sea."
msgstr ""
"La nación de Washraha en Arajunna se formó cuando la dinastía Tarva llegó al "
"poder y unió varias tribus y ciudades-estado en disputa para expulsar a los "
"gigantes conocidos como Deshra. El gobernante de la ciudad-estado de Shray "
"Tahl, un señor de la guerra conocido como Tarva Pah, fue el responsable de "
"unir estas ciudades-estado. Su ejército se conoció como los washrajan, o "
"cortadores de rodillas, y prestaron su nombre al imperio resultante.\n"
"\n"
"Cuando se convirtió en su primer emperador, Tarva Pah se volvió un hombre "
"temeroso y paranoico. Instituyó un paradigma de aislacionismo y xenofobia, "
"construyendo un muro a lo largo de sus fronteras terrestres mientras "
"poderosos grupos de exploración washrahan vigilaban la sabana y las montañas "
"que rodeaban sus tierras, poniendo fin violento rápidamente a cualquiera que "
"viniera explorando o buscando comercio o refugio. Estas políticas fueron "
"llevadas a cabo por sus sucesores durante generaciones; los propios "
"washrahan a menudo visitaban tierras y pueblos vecinos, pero con malas "
"intenciones: pues en la cultura beligerante washrahan, los guerreros deben "
"probar constantemente su valía en combate, y por eso a menudo saquean tribus "
"extranjeras más pequeñas, aunque rara vez destruyen alguna por completo.\n"
"\n"
"Sin embargo, en el reinado de la Emperatriz Sa-Tarva, los Washraha "
"decidieron expandirse, arrasando incontables pueblos y aldeas y conquistando "
"vastas extensiones de tierra, convirtiéndose en el poder absoluto en "
"Arajunna. Su poder se volvió realmente sin rival, y podría haber expandido a "
"reinos mucho más allá de su continente, de no ser por el miedo casi "
"supersticioso de los Washraha al mar."

#. [race], id=woodlander
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/woodlanders.cfg:5
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/woodlanders.cfg:6
msgid "Woodlander"
msgstr "Habitante del Bosque"

#. [race], id=woodlander
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/woodlanders.cfg:7
msgid "Woodlanders"
msgstr "Habitantes del Bosque"

#. [race], id=woodlander
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/woodlanders.cfg:10
msgid ""
"The Woodlanders are a quite variegated population. Indeed, this faction "
"isn't composed by only one race but by some different ones with some common "
"traits. In addition to their shy and lone nature (that makes them very "
"skilled in hiding and ambushes), these warriors have in common the choice of "
"the forest as their habitat; some forced to it, others for their own will. "
"The members of this group are mainly legendary creatures, whose existence is "
"still ignored by some. Indeed those who had met this army rarely had such a "
"long life to be able to tell it! Many legends are told about some of them, "
"wherein sometimes they are evil wizards who draw their prey where they can "
"be lethal (into the wood), other times they are told as good creatures "
"living a nature-friendly and cheerful life. However, wise travelers usually "
"avoid those places where the shadow of the trees eats the light and "
"thousands glittering eyes are seen in the dark."
msgstr ""
"Los Habitantes del Bosque son una población bastante variada. En efecto, "
"esta facción no está compuesta por una sola raza sino por varias diferentes "
"con algunos rasgos comunes. Además de su naturaleza tímida y solitaria (que "
"los hace muy hábiles en esconderse y tender emboscadas), estos guerreros "
"tienen en común la elección del bosque como su hábitat; algunos obligados a "
"ello, otros por voluntad propia. Los miembros de este grupo son "
"principalmente criaturas legendarias, cuya existencia aún es ignorada por "
"algunos. ¡En efecto, quienes han encontrado a este ejército rara vez han "
"vivido lo suficiente para contarlo! Muchas leyendas se cuentan sobre algunos "
"de ellos, en las que a veces son magos malvados que atraen a sus presas "
"donde pueden ser letales (dentro del bosque), otras veces se les describe "
"como criaturas buenas que viven una vida amistosa con la naturaleza y "
"alegre. Sin embargo, los viajeros sabios suelen evitar esos lugares donde la "
"sombra de los árboles devora la luz y miles de ojos brillantes se ven en la "
"oscuridad."

