#. [unit_type], id=Chariot Archer, race=maatkarian, gender=female
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Chariot_Archer.cfg:5
msgid "Chariot Archer"
msgstr "Arquera de Carro"

#. [unit_type], id=Chariot Archer, race=maatkarian, gender=female
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Chariot_Archer.cfg:20
msgid ""
"The Hannuks, one of the two peoples from whom the Maat'Karians descend, were "
"famed for being excellent archers and outstanding horsemen. Indeed, both "
"archery and horsemanship were such important skills in their culture that "
"those who managed to excel at both were considered heroes. It is thus ironic "
"that their heirs have so little regard for both archery and horsemanship, "
"prefering to use the horses for transportation and the bows for hunting - "
"archers were taken out of the army for being too vulnerable to enemy attacks "
"with their light armour. Nevertheless, still early in Maat'Kare's History a "
"new military unit was created by women who, not wanting to simply sit "
"comfortably at home but unable to don the standard Maat'Karian armour, "
"ressurrected the old Hannuk War Chariot, but adapting it to their needs: in "
"the end, they had developed a lighter and less resistant, but also swifter "
"and more agile vehicle, and one which didn't lose speed on sandy terrain. "
"Those women also learned archery, becoming quite proficient at it; thus they "
"would, like the War Charioteers of yore, shoot deadly arrows from inside the "
"chariot, which was to be driven by trained charioteers. This unit quickly "
"became quite popular for their accurate ranged attacks, high defense against "
"most physical damage, great speed and capacity of moving through enemy lines "
"thanks to its sheer weight; their only downsides, in fact, are their "
"uselessness on nearly any terrain other than plains and sands, and the high "
"costs of building and maintaining them."
msgstr ""
"Los Hannuks, uno de los dos pueblos de los que descienden los maat'karianos, "
"eran famosos por ser excelentes arqueros y destacados jinetes. En efecto, "
"tanto la arquería como la equitación eran habilidades tan importantes en su "
"cultura que quienes lograban destacar en ambas eran considerados héroes. Por "
"eso es irónico que sus herederos tengan tan poco aprecio por ambas, "
"prefiriendo usar los caballos para transporte y los arcos para cazar —los "
"arqueros fueron retirados del ejército por ser demasiado vulnerables a "
"ataques enemigos con su armadura ligera. Sin embargo, aún temprano en la "
"historia de Maat'Kare, un nuevo grupo militar fue creado por mujeres que, no "
"queriendo simplemente quedarse cómodas en casa pero incapaces de usar la "
"armadura maat'kariana estándar, resucitaron el antiguo Carro de Guerra "
"Hannuk, pero adaptándolo a sus necesidades: al final, desarrollaron un "
"vehículo más ligero y menos resistente, pero también más rápido y ágil, y "
"que no perdía velocidad en terreno arenoso. Esas mujeres también aprendieron "
"arquería, volviéndose bastante competentes en ella; así, al igual que los "
"antiguos Carros de Guerra, disparaban flechas letales desde dentro del "
"carro, que era conducido por cocheros entrenados. Esta unidad se volvió "
"rápidamente muy popular por sus precisos ataques a distancia, alta defensa "
"contra la mayoría del daño físico, gran velocidad y capacidad de atravesar "
"líneas enemigas gracias a su puro peso; sus únicos inconvenientes, de hecho, "
"son su inutilidad en casi cualquier terreno que no sean llanuras y arenas, y "
"los altos costos de construirlos y mantenerlos."

