#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Elder Sage, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Elder_Sage.cfg:7
msgid "Elder Sage"
msgstr "Sabio Anciano"

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Elder Sage, race=maatkarian
#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Sage, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Elder_Sage.cfg:21
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sage.cfg:21
msgid ""
"The Sages of Maat'Kare are the eldest and wisest amongst the Maat'Karian "
"citizens. As the representatives of the commoners, they don't have magic or "
"military skills, but their vast life experience and great skill in politics "
"make them competent administrators of the Maat'Karian civilization, and for "
"this they are highly respected."
msgstr ""
"Los Sabios de Maat'Kare son los más ancianos y sabios entre los ciudadanos "
"maat'karianos. Como representantes de la gente común, no tienen habilidades "
"mágicas ni militares, pero su vasta experiencia de vida y gran habilidad en "
"política los convierten en competentes administradores de la civilización "
"maat'kariana, y por eso son altamente respetados."

#. [unit_type], id=Electrum Slinger, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Electrum_Slinger.cfg:5
msgid "Maat'Karian Electrum Slinger"
msgstr "Hondero de Electrum Maat'kariano"

#. [unit_type], id=Electrum Slinger, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Electrum_Slinger.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Though Slingers are not an official military unit, some commanders do "
"recruit them, to compensate the Sefet's lack of ranged attacks, and because "
"they're far less expensive than Chariot Archers. These Slingers thus have a "
"chance to further hone their skills and improve their physical prowess with "
"military training; and the best ones are given better equipment and electrum "
"balls, which are much harder than stone, as ammunition. Albeit still "
"vulnerable due to their lack of armour, their speed and the deadliness and "
"accuracy of their slingshots are undoubtedly valuable assets for the "
"Maat'Karian Army."
msgstr ""
"Aunque los honderos no son una unidad militar oficial, algunos comandantes "
"los reclutan para compensar la falta de ataques a distancia de los Sefet y "
"porque son mucho menos costosos que las Arqueras de Carro. Estos honderos "
"tienen así la oportunidad de perfeccionar aún más sus habilidades y mejorar "
"su destreza física con entrenamiento militar; y a los mejores se les da "
"mejor equipo y bolas de electrum, mucho más duras que la piedra, como "
"munición. Aunque siguen siendo vulnerables por la falta de armadura, su "
"velocidad y la letalidad y precisión de sus hondas son sin duda activos "
"valiosos para el Ejército Maat'kariano."

#. [unit_type], id=Imeyer, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Imeyer.cfg:4
msgid "Imey'er"
msgstr "Imey'er"

#. [unit_type], id=Imeyer, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Imeyer.cfg:24
msgid ""
"After leading his soldiers for many battles, a Shakafa will have learned the "
"skills that the military academy couldn't teach: to take quick decisions as "
"his life and that of his men are on the verge of death, to gain the trust of "
"his soldiers, to decide the best moves according to terrain, weather and "
"time conditions... Because not all Shakafa live long enough to learn these "
"lessons, those who do are highly valued, and are know as Imey'er, or "
"captains - for only now has he truly earned the right to be known as such."
msgstr ""
"Tras liderar a sus soldados en muchas batallas, un Shakafa habrá aprendido "
"las habilidades que la academia militar no podía enseñar: tomar decisiones "
"rápidas cuando su vida y la de sus hombres están al borde de la muerte, "
"ganarse la confianza de sus soldados, decidir los mejores movimientos según "
"el terreno, el clima y las condiciones del momento… Como no todos los "
"Shakafa viven lo suficiente para aprender estas lecciones, aquellos que lo "
"hacen son altamente valorados y se les conoce como Imey'er, o capitanes —"
"pues solo ahora ha ganado verdaderamente el derecho a ser llamado así."

#. [unit_type], id=Khopesh, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Khopesh.cfg:4
msgid "Khopesh"
msgstr "Khopesh"

#. [unit_type], id=Khopesh, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Khopesh.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The Sefet who stand out of his colleagues will be given an even stronger "
"armour, and a slightly longer sword - a khopesh - which increases their "
"attacking power. Although the weight of their new armour decreases their "
"speed, it also enables them to withstand considerably more rounds of "
"fighting than most infantry soldiers from other armies. They're still "
"vulnerable to ranged attacks, but they've also learned to make better use of "
"their equipment."
msgstr ""
"Al Sefet que destaca entre sus compañeros se le da una armadura aún más "
"fuerte y una espada ligeramente más larga —un khopesh— que aumenta su poder "
"de ataque. Aunque el peso de su nueva armadura disminuye su velocidad, "
"también les permite resistir considerablemente más rondas de combate que la "
"mayoría de los soldados de infantería de otros ejércitos. Siguen siendo "
"vulnerables a ataques a distancia, pero también han aprendido a hacer mejor "
"uso de su equipo."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Khopesh.cfg:35
msgid "khopesh"
msgstr "khopesh"

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Khopesh.cfg:47
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sefet.cfg:43
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Wersefet.cfg:51
msgid "stab"
msgstr "apuñalada"

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Khopesh.cfg:59
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Medjay.cfg:47
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Migdol_Guard.cfg:46
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sentinel.cfg:45
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Wersefet.cfg:63
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/washraha/Washraha_Warrior.cfg:75
msgid "shield bash"
msgstr "golpe de escudo"

#. [unit_type], id=Maryannu, race=maatkarian, gender=female
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Maryannu.cfg:5
msgid "Maryannu"
msgstr "Maryannu"

#. [unit_type], id=Maryannu, race=maatkarian, gender=female
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Maryannu.cfg:21
msgid ""
"It has often been pointed out by commanders and even common citizens that "
"the Ten'Thors, with all their might, seldom survive more than seven battles. "
"This is probably due to their defencelessness on all kinds of terrain, which "
"makes them an easy target; and specially to the overconfidence that has "
"become a signature trait of both archer and charioteer. Nevertheless, those "
"Tenthors who do manage to survive many battles and hone their skills even "
"further are amongst Maat'Kare's enemies' most dreaded banes. They thunder "
"across the plains and the desert like a juggernaut, striking down any foe "
"that manages to avoid being cruelly trampled by the vehicle and the horses, "
"and leading infantrymen and Chariot Archers alike as if they were the actual "
"commanders of their respective armies. Imposing and powerful, these superb "
"charioteers and archers have earned the well-deserved name of Maryannu, or "
"'valiant warriors'."
msgstr ""
"A menudo se ha señalado por comandantes e incluso ciudadanos comunes que los "
"Ten'Thors, con todo su poder, rara vez sobreviven más de siete batallas. "
"Esto probablemente se debe a su indefensión en todo tipo de terreno, lo que "
"los convierte en un blanco fácil; y especialmente a la excesiva confianza "
"que se ha convertido en un rasgo característico tanto del arquero como del "
"auriga. Sin embargo, aquellos Ten'Thors que logran sobrevivir a muchas "
"batallas y perfeccionan sus habilidades aún más están entre los azotes más "
"temidos de los enemigos de Maat'Kare. Atruenan a través de las llanuras y el "
"desierto como un gigante, derribando a cualquier enemigo que logre evitar "
"ser cruelmente pisoteado por el vehículo y los caballos, y liderando a los "
"infantes y a los Arqueras de Carro por igual como si fueran los verdaderos "
"comandantes de sus respectivos ejércitos. Imponentes y poderosos, estos "
"superbios aurigas y arqueros han ganado el bien merecido nombre de Maryannu, "
"o «guerreros valientes»."

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Maryannu.cfg:59
msgid "fearless charge"
msgstr "carga sin miedo"

#. [unit_type], id=Medjay, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Medjay.cfg:5
msgid "Medjay"
msgstr "Medjay"

#. [unit_type], id=Medjay, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Medjay.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Many Sentinels die every year in frontier clashes against vampires, "
"minotaurs and orcs; nevertheless, it's exactly this environment of danger "
"and of constant fighting that shapes those who are renowned all over Netjer-"
"Ta as the most fearsome defenders any army can hope to meet. Clad in shining "
"electrum armour and wielding towering shields adorned with the Winged "
"Protectress of Maat'Kare, these warriors are called the Medjay - which means "
"'dead end' in the Maat'Karian language. Indeed, if an enemy comes across a "
"Medjay, his best option is to go another way."
msgstr ""
"Muchos Centinelas mueren cada año en choques fronterizos contra vampiros, "
"minotauros y orcos; sin embargo, es precisamente este entorno de peligro y "
"combate constante el que moldea a aquellos que son renombrados en todo "
"Netjer-Ta como los defensores más temibles que cualquier ejército puede "
"esperar encontrar. Vestidos con brillante armadura de electrum y empuñando "
"escudos imponentes adornados con la Protectora Alada de Maat'Kare, estos "
"guerreros son llamados Medjay —que significa «callejón sin salida» en la "
"lengua maat'kariana. En efecto, si un enemigo se topa con un Medjay, su "
"mejor opción es tomar otro camino."

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Medjay.cfg:38
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/wargs/b1_Stalker.cfg:28
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/wargs/b2_Shadow_Pelt.cfg:28
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/wargs/b3_Night_Eye.cfg:30
msgid "Spear"
msgstr "Lanza"

#. [unit_type], id=Migdol Guard, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Migdol_Guard.cfg:5
msgid "Migdol Guard"
msgstr "Guardia Migdol"

#. [unit_type], id=Migdol Guard, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Migdol_Guard.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Those amongst the Sentinels who show greater prowess with the spear are "
"given better armour and sent to the Migdols, small fortresses that protect "
"the most vulnerable points of the Maat'Karian frontier."
msgstr ""
"A aquellos Centinelas que destacan más con la lanza se les da mejor armadura "
"y se les envía a los Migdols, pequeñas fortalezas que protegen los puntos "
"más vulnerables de la frontera maat'kariana."

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Sage, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sage.cfg:7
msgid "Sage"
msgstr "Sabio"

#. [unit_type], id=Sefet, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sefet.cfg:5
msgid "Sefet"
msgstr "Sefet"

#. [unit_type], id=Sefet, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sefet.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Since its very founding, Maat'Kare has always been forced to deal with a "
"dilemma: at the same it had to control its population's size, it was "
"constantly involved in wars against vampires, orcs, minotaurs and gnolls. "
"Ravyan Aracyne, one of the city's Founders, was the first to worry about the "
"number of losses that the Maat'Karians could have in each battle; to "
"diminish their chances of dying or being severely maimed, the Maat'Karian "
"soldiers are given a very resistant armour made of electrum (an alloy of "
"gold and silver), which crafting the humans learned from the Aigathol "
"dwarves. This armour protects them well from all kinds of phsical damage, "
"but are very heavy, and so the soldiers are trained to be extremely "
"muscular. The Maat'Karian soldiers' great physical strength, allied with the "
"weight and sharpness of their sefet - or swords -, also renders their blows "
"extremely devastating, especially for such a basic military unit; and their "
"stamina enables them to move well on most terrain types. The downside, "
"however, is that the cost of forging such equipment and training such a "
"soldier is high. Another downside of the Sefet is that they're vulnerable to "
"ranged attacks."
msgstr ""
"Desde su misma fundación, Maat'Kare siempre se ha visto obligada a lidiar "
"con un dilema: al mismo tiempo que debía controlar el tamaño de su "
"población, estaba constantemente involucrada en guerras contra vampiros, "
"orcos, minotauros y gnolls. Ravyan Aracyne, uno de los Fundadores de la "
"ciudad, fue el primero en preocuparse por la cantidad de pérdidas que los "
"maat'karianos podían sufrir en cada batalla; para disminuir sus "
"posibilidades de morir o quedar gravemente mutilados, a los soldados "
"maat'karianos se les da una armadura muy resistente hecha de electrum (una "
"aleación de oro y plata), cuya forja los humanos aprendieron de los enanos "
"Aigathol. Esta armadura los protege bien de todo tipo de daño físico, pero "
"es muy pesada, y por eso los soldados son entrenados para ser extremadamente "
"musculosos. La gran fuerza física de los soldados maat'karianos, aliada al "
"peso y filo de su sefet —o espadas—, también hace que sus golpes sean "
"extremadamente devastadores, especialmente para una unidad militar tan "
"básica; y su resistencia les permite moverse bien en la mayoría de los tipos "
"de terreno. El inconveniente, sin embargo, es que el costo de forjar tal "
"equipo y entrenar a tal soldado es alto. Otro inconveniente de los Sefet es "
"que son vulnerables a ataques a distancia."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sefet.cfg:31
msgid "sefet"
msgstr "sefet"

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Sentinel, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sentinel.cfg:5
msgid "Sentinel"
msgstr "Centinela"

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Sentinel, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Sentinel.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Maat'Karian soldiers are famed for their defensive power: wearing heavy "
"armour that covers nearly the entirety of their bodies, they are highly "
"resistant to most kinds of attack. Nevertheless, this poses two problems for "
"their military: firstly, they can't afford producing electrum armour for "
"many soldiers; and second, even if they could, not all would have the "
"necessary height, strength and stamina to efficiently fight while donning "
"them. It was Erakyn, a famous general of Maat'Kare's third generation, who "
"solved both problems by creating a new unit which donnned a new type of "
"armour, one that didn't protect the soldier as the one donned by the Sefet "
"did; but which was lighter and less expensive, and made of electrum as well. "
"This new unit was given long spears, which was a cheaper and more accessible "
"weapon to people. These units were seldom sent to fight on pitched battles, "
"but they became an important part of Maat'Kare's defence, for they are "
"always employed as guards and patrollers in towns, villages and frontier "
"outposts."
msgstr ""
"Los soldados maat'karianos son famosos por su poder defensivo: vistiendo "
"pesada armadura que cubre casi todo su cuerpo, son altamente resistentes a "
"la mayoría de los tipos de ataque. Sin embargo, esto plantea dos problemas "
"para su ejército: primero, no pueden permitirse producir armadura de "
"electrum para muchos soldados; y segundo, incluso si pudieran, no todos "
"tendrían la altura, fuerza y resistencia necesarias para luchar "
"eficientemente mientras la llevan. Fue Erakyn, un famoso general de la "
"tercera generación de Maat'Kare, quien resolvió ambos problemas creando una "
"nueva unidad que vestía un nuevo tipo de armadura, una que no protegía al "
"soldado como la de los Sefet; pero que era más ligera y menos costosa, y "
"también hecha de electrum. A esta nueva unidad se le dieron lanzas largas, "
"un arma más barata y accesible para la gente. Estas unidades rara vez eran "
"enviadas a luchar en batallas campales, pero se convirtieron en una parte "
"importante de la defensa de Maat'Kare, pues siempre se emplean como guardias "
"y patrulleros en ciudades, aldeas y puestos fronterizos."

#. [unit_type], id=Shakafa, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Shakafa.cfg:4
msgid "Shakafa"
msgstr "Shakafa"

#. [unit_type], id=Shakafa, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Shakafa.cfg:24
msgid ""
"The Maat'Karians aren't an expansionistic people by tradition, but it "
"doesn't mean that they simply sit behind their walls waiting for their foes "
"to attack. After the securing of the Land's End peninsula, they set out to "
"conquer nearby lands that were controlled by minotaurs and vampires, and "
"times later, they started attacking faraway vampire and orcish fortresses. "
"These conquest campaigns required soldiers with good leadership skills, and "
"so a new battle school was formed with the goal of training commanders. Not "
"everyone can join it, though, due to the high cost of their equipment: an "
"iron mace and a massive electrum armour, far more resistant than that of a "
"Sefet - after all, a commander must be well protected. This also means that "
"the commander-in-training must develop even stronger muscles than a normal "
"soldier; besides, he's expected to be the first to do whatever he asks of "
"his men, and so he must be courageous.\n"
"\n"
"Finally, if the commander-in-training leaves the military academy "
"successfully, he receives the title of Shakafa, which means 'he who leads "
"the conquests'. However, the most important knowledge he must have to be a "
"true commander can only be found in battle."
msgstr ""
"Los maat'karianos no son un pueblo expansionista por tradición, pero eso no "
"significa que simplemente se queden detrás de sus murallas esperando a que "
"sus enemigos ataquen. Tras asegurar la península de Fin de la Tierra, "
"partieron a conquistar tierras cercanas controladas por minotauros y "
"vampiros, y tiempo después comenzaron a atacar fortalezas lejanas de "
"vampiros y orcos. Estas campañas de conquista requerían soldados con buenas "
"habilidades de liderazgo, y así se formó una nueva escuela de batalla con el "
"objetivo de entrenar comandantes. No todos pueden unirse a ella, sin "
"embargo, debido al alto costo de su equipo: una maza de hierro y una "
"armadura masiva de electrum, mucho más resistente que la de un Sefet —"
"después de todo, un comandante debe estar bien protegido. Esto también "
"significa que el comandante en entrenamiento debe desarrollar músculos aún "
"más fuertes que un soldado normal; además, se espera que sea el primero en "
"hacer lo que pide a sus hombres, y por lo tanto debe ser valiente.\n"
"\n"
"Finalmente, si el comandante en entrenamiento abandona con éxito la academia "
"militar, recibe el título de Shakafa, que significa «el que lidera las "
"conquistas». Sin embargo, el conocimiento más importante que debe tener para "
"ser un verdadero comandante solo se encuentra en la batalla."

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Slinger, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Slinger.cfg:4
msgid "Maat'Karian Slinger"
msgstr "Hondero Maat'kariano"

#. [unit_type], id=MaatKarian Slinger, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Slinger.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Joining the military is the dream of many Maat'Karian youths; unfortunately, "
"however, not all of them have the build to become a Sefet or a Sentinel, or "
"the skill to train as an archer. Those amongst these youths who live in the "
"rural areas were thus forced to remain as farmers; and, while hunting or "
"scaring off wild animals, they developed a great skill with the sling. The "
"usefulness of such ability was first noticed when, during a frontier "
"skirmish against a rogue Warg pack, a group of slingers came to the aid of "
"the soldiers, unbalancing the fight in their favour due to the Wargs' "
"vulnerability to ranged attacks. Since that fight, slingers have risen in "
"prominence, and now there are even some commanders who use them as regular "
"soldiers. Nevertheless, because they are quite vulnerable to physical "
"attacks - after all, they don't wear any armour - they haven't been made an "
"official military unit yet."
msgstr ""
"Unirse al ejército es el sueño de muchos jóvenes maat'karianos; "
"desafortunadamente, sin embargo, no todos tienen la constitución para "
"convertirse en Sefet o Centinela, ni la habilidad para entrenar como "
"arquero. Aquellos entre estos jóvenes que viven en áreas rurales se vieron "
"obligados a permanecer como agricultores; y, mientras cazaban o ahuyentaban "
"animales salvajes, desarrollaron una gran habilidad con la honda. La "
"utilidad de tal habilidad se notó por primera vez cuando, durante una "
"escaramuza fronteriza contra una manada de huargos renegados, un grupo de "
"honderos acudió en ayuda de los soldados, desequilibrando la pelea a su "
"favor debido a la vulnerabilidad de los huargos a ataques a distancia. Desde "
"esa pelea, los honderos han ganado prominencia, y ahora incluso hay algunos "
"comandantes que los usan como soldados regulares. Sin embargo, porque son "
"bastante vulnerables a ataques físicos —después de todo, no llevan armadura— "
"aún no han sido convertidos en una unidad militar oficial."

#. [unit_type], id=Tenthor, race=maatkarian, gender=female
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Tenthor.cfg:5
msgid "Ten'Thor"
msgstr "Ten'Thor"

#. [unit_type], id=Tenthor, race=maatkarian, gender=female
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Tenthor.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Not every commander likes employing Chariot Archers in their batallions, due "
"to their expensiveness and low terrain versatility. Those who do, however, "
"use their own gold to buy electrum and iron plates with which to reinforce "
"the vehicles of the best Chariot Archers, and also horseshoes to make the "
"horses' kicks deadlier. Curiously, though few are the commanders who recruit "
"that unit, those who do often relies heavily on them, forming entire "
"batallions composed exclusively of seasoned Chariot Archers. Because of "
"that, they've been called Ten'Thor, which literally means 'chariot force', "
"and they're widely known for turning the tide of countless battles all by "
"themselves."
msgstr ""
"No todos los comandantes gustan de emplear Arqueras de Carro en sus "
"batallones, debido a su alto costo y baja versatilidad en terrenos. Aquellos "
"que sí lo hacen, sin embargo, usan su propio oro para comprar placas de "
"electrum y hierro con las que reforzar los vehículos de las mejores Arqueras "
"de Carro, y también herraduras para hacer más letales las patadas de los "
"caballos. Curiosamente, aunque pocos son los comandantes que reclutan esa "
"unidad, aquellos que lo hacen a menudo dependen mucho de ellas, formando "
"batallones enteros compuestos exclusivamente de Arqueras de Carro "
"experimentadas. Por eso se les ha llamado Ten'Thor, que literalmente "
"significa «fuerza de carro», y son ampliamente conocidos por cambiar el "
"rumbo de innumerables batallas por sí solos."

#. [unit_type], id=Wersefet, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Wersefet.cfg:4
msgid "Wersefet"
msgstr "Wersefet"

#. [unit_type], id=Wersefet, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Wersefet.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Not many soldiers advance past the rank of a Khopesh, and for a simple "
"reason: few are the men who have the strength and the stamina to don the "
"armour and wield the sword reserved for the elite of the Maat'Karian "
"infantry. This sword, known as wersefet - literally 'great blade' is almost "
"as massive as an Orcish chiefain's sword, but far sharper and far more "
"resistant. A single line of Wersefet soldiers, with their golden armour, "
"towering shields and lethal blades gleaming in the sunlight, would be enough "
"to repel even a massive attack by seasoned warriors, but their mere sight is "
"often enough to make most foes flee in terror."
msgstr ""
"No muchos soldados avanzan más allá del rango de Khopesh, y por una razón "
"simple: pocos son los hombres que tienen la fuerza y la resistencia para "
"vestir la armadura y empuñar la espada reservada para la élite de la "
"infantería maat'kariana. Esta espada, conocida como wersefet —literalmente "
"«gran hoja»— es casi tan masiva como la espada de un jefe orco, pero mucho "
"más afilada y mucho más resistente. Una sola línea de soldados Wersefet, con "
"su armadura dorada, escudos imponentes y hojas letales brillando bajo el "
"sol, sería suficiente para repeler incluso un ataque masivo de guerreros "
"experimentados, pero su mera visión a menudo basta para hacer que la mayoría "
"de los enemigos huya aterrorizada."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/MaatKarian_Wersefet.cfg:39
msgid "wersefet"
msgstr "wersefet"

#. [unit_type], id=Novice Mage, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/Novice_Mage.cfg:4
msgid "Novice Mage"
msgstr "Mago Novato"

#. [unit_type], id=Novice Mage, race=maatkarian
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/Novice_Mage.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Novice Mages are youths who have just been admitted into the Academy of "
"Maat'Kare. Though currently little more than children who can channel their "
"power into mildly burning missiles, they have the potential to become great "
"mages in the future."
msgstr ""
"Los Magos Novatos son jóvenes que acaban de ser admitidos en la Academia de "
"Maat'Kare. Aunque actualmente no son más que niños capaces de canalizar su "
"poder en misiles que queman levemente, tienen el potencial de convertirse en "
"grandes magos en el futuro."

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/Novice_Mage.cfg:46
msgid "missile"
msgstr "proyectil"

#. [female]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/maatkarians/Novice_Mage.cfg:94
msgid "female^Novice Mage"
msgstr "Maga Novata"

#. [unit_type], id=Amphyon, race=monster
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/Amphyon.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Once the corrupt ruler of the Empire of Skiron, this creature is proudly "
"held by Aegaion as his masterpiece. The Amphyon is more commonly used as the "
"beast that draws the Eternal Emperor's chariot; but, when used in combat, "
"the Amphyon is a virtually unstoppable force. Whoever stands on his way will "
"suffer an outstandingly brutal death."
msgstr ""
"Una vez el gobernante corrupto del Imperio de Skiron, esta criatura es "
"orgullosamente considerada por Aegaion como su obra maestra. El Amphyon se "
"usa más comúnmente como la bestia que tira del carro del Emperador Eterno; "
"pero, cuando se usa en combate, el Amphyon es una fuerza prácticamente "
"imparable. Quien se interponga en su camino sufrirá una muerte "
"excepcionalmente brutal."

#. [attack], type=blade, range=melee
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/Amphyon.cfg:30
msgid "brutality"
msgstr "brutalidad"

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/Amphyon.cfg:42
msgid "juggernaut"
msgstr "yuggernaut"

#. [attack], type=impact, range=ranged
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/Amphyon.cfg:55
msgid "poison"
