msgstr "andanada de flechas de fuego"

#. [unit_type], id=Light Spirit, race=celestial
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/c1_Light_Spirit.cfg:5
msgid "Light Spirit"
msgstr "Espíritu de Luz"

#. [unit_type], id=Light Spirit, race=celestial
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/c1_Light_Spirit.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Light Spirits are a breed of faeries who possess an aura of arcane energy "
"that infuses their entire body with a radiant light. They share their energy "
"with the miscelanea in return for protection, and to some extent worship."
msgstr ""
"Los Espíritus de Luz son una raza de hadas que poseen un aura de energía "
"arcana que infunde todo su cuerpo con una luz radiante. Comparten su energía "
"con la miscelánea a cambio de protección, y en cierta medida adoración."

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/c1_Light_Spirit.cfg:77
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/c2_Lantern_Archon.cfg:76
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/c3_Master_of_Light.cfg:78
msgid "shock of light"
msgstr "descarga de luz"

#. [unit_type], id=Lantern Archon, race=celestial
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/c2_Lantern_Archon.cfg:5
msgid "Lantern Archon"
msgstr "Arconte Linterna"

#. [unit_type], id=Lantern Archon, race=celestial
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/c2_Lantern_Archon.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Lantern Archons are a breed of faeries who possess an aura of arcane energy "
"that infuses their entire body with a radiant light. Lantern Archons defend "
"themselves with powerful shocks of arcane energy at a distance; up close "
"they are quite defenseless."
msgstr ""
"Los arcontes linterna son una raza de hadas que poseen un aura de energía "
"arcana que impregna todo su cuerpo con una luz radiante. Los arcontes "
"linterna se defienden con poderosas descargas de energía arcana a distancia; "
"de cerca están bastante desprotegidos."

#. [unit_type], id=Master of Light, race=celestial
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/c3_Master_of_Light.cfg:5
msgid "Master of Light"
msgstr "Maestro de la Luz"

#. [unit_type], id=Master of Light, race=celestial
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/miscelanea/c3_Master_of_Light.cfg:25
msgid ""
"A faerie who exercises her output of arcane energy may master using it as a "
"weapon to such a degree that they are named Masters of Light."
msgstr ""
"Un hada que entrena su emisión de energía arcana puede dominar su uso como "
"arma hasta tal punto que recibe el nombre de maestro de la luz."

#. [unit_type], id=Aegaion, race=undead
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/undead/Aegaion.cfg:4
msgid "Dark Saint"
msgstr "Santo Oscuro"

#. [unit_type], id=Aegaion, race=undead
#: War_of_the_Jewel/units/undead/Aegaion.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Whoever met young Aegaion would never have believed what he was to become. "
"Born a peasant in the remote town of Kornepia, he was known for his "
"liveliness and kindness, always protecting small wild animals from being "
"hunted by other children. He was also known for his friendship with a young "
"girl of his age called Perseias; the two of them were inseparable, and they "
"continued to be so when they grew up. Together they walked around, together "
"they made plans for the future, and together they protested against the "
"tyrannical Emperor Amphyon. For those protests they were chased out of their "
"village by Imperial soldiers. For a time they wandered the wildlands of "
"Argea; it was in such wanderings that they came upon the remains of an "
"ancient dragon, amidst which they found a ruby whose power even they could "
"feel. Perseias sensed its malice, but Aegaion convinced her that in that "
"jewel they had found the power to stand against Amphyon.\n"
"\n"
"Aegaion's dream of toppling the despot and building a better Skiron proved "
"to be his downfall. The spirits locked within the ruby - which Perseias had "
"dubbed 'Ruby of Fire' - found the way to Aegaion's heart through his hatred "
"of the Empire. At some point, he ceased to let the Ruby far from his "
"clutches for a single second, and even grew aloof towards his best friend. "
"Worried about him, Perseias sought to get rid of the Ruby, but that was a "
"mistake: corrupted by the jewel's malice, thinking that she only wanted it "
"for herself, Aegaion killed her in a fit of rage. When he got back to his "
"senses, he was shocked to find out that he'd killed his childhood friend, "
"but the Ruby whispered into his soul that her death was Amphyon's fault; "
"that became yet another reason to hate the emperor.\n"
"\n"
"In the following years, Aegaion mastered the secrets and the powers of the "
"Ruby, to such an extent that he achieved the impossible and overcame death "
"itself; he had become a Lich. Then he began gathering followers: they came "
"easily to him, attracted to his charisma, ideals of justice and, especially, "
"to his power, which could even bring the dead back to life. His appearance "
"often frightened people, but even that became part of his mystique: "
"convinced themselves that his undeath was actually another proof of his "
"holiness, the people dubbed him 'the Dark Saint'. When his influence was too "
"strong to go unopposed, he and his followers were attacked by the Imperial "
"forces; however, Amphyon was too hated by his subjects, and Aegaion was too "
"popular and had too many supporters. At the climax of the short, but bloody "
"Skironian Civil War, Aegaion personally killed Amphyon, turned him into an "
"undead monster, and crowned himself the Eternal Emperor of Skiron.\n"
"\n"
"As the new ruler, he did fulfil his promise of improving people's lives, "
"also turning Skiron into a strong and rich nation once again. However, his "
"intolerance of oppositionists is even greater than Amphyon's, as is his "
"violence when dealing with enemies. However, nobody is brave enough to tell "
"Aegaion that he has become a monster far worse than that which now drags his "
"personal chariot."
msgstr ""
"Quien conociera al joven Aegaion nunca habría creído en lo que se "
"convertiría. Nacido como campesino en la remota ciudad de Kornepia, era "
"conocido por su vitalidad y bondad, siempre protegiendo a pequeños animales "
"salvajes de ser cazados por otros niños. También era conocido por su amistad "
"con una joven de su edad llamada Perseias; los dos eran inseparables, y "
"siguieron siéndolo cuando crecieron. Juntos caminaban, juntos hacían planes "
"para el futuro, y juntos protestaban contra el tiránico Emperador Amphyon. "
"Por esas protestas fueron expulsados de su aldea por soldados imperiales. "
"Durante un tiempo vagaron por las tierras salvajes de Argea; fue en tales "
"vagabundeos que se toparon con los restos de un dragón antiguo, en medio de "
"los cuales encontraron un rubí cuyo poder incluso ellos podían sentir. "
"Perseias percibió su malicia, pero Aegaion la convenció de que en esa joya "
"habían encontrado el poder para enfrentarse a Amphyon.\n"
"\n"
"El sueño de Aegaion de derrocar al déspota y construir un Skiron mejor "
"resultó ser su perdición. Los espíritus encerrados dentro del rubí —al que "
"Perseias había llamado «Rubí de Fuego»— encontraron el camino al corazón de "
"Aegaion a través de su odio al Imperio. En algún momento, dejó de dejar el "
"Rubí lejos de sus garras ni por un segundo, e incluso se volvió distante "
"hacia su mejor amiga. Preocupada por él, Perseias buscó deshacerse del Rubí, "
"pero eso fue un error: corrompido por la malicia de la joya, pensando que "
"ella solo la quería para sí misma, Aegaion la mató en un ataque de rabia. "
"Cuando recuperó el sentido, se horrorizó al descubrir que había matado a su "
"amiga de la infancia, pero el Rubí susurró en su alma que su muerte era "
"culpa de Amphyon; eso se convirtió en otra razón más para odiar al "
"emperador.\n"
"\n"
"En los años siguientes, Aegaion dominó los secretos y los poderes del Rubí, "
"hasta el punto de lograr lo imposible y superar la muerte misma; se había "
"convertido en un Liche. Entonces comenzó a reunir seguidores: le llegaron "
"fácilmente, atraídos por su carisma, sus ideales de justicia y, "
"especialmente, por su poder, que incluso podía traer a los muertos de vuelta "
"a la vida. Su apariencia a menudo asustaba a la gente, pero incluso eso se "
"convirtió en parte de su mística: se convencieron a sí mismos de que su no-"
"muerte era en realidad otra prueba de su santidad, y el pueblo lo apodó «el "
"Santo Oscuro». Cuando su influencia fue demasiado fuerte para no ser "
"confrontada, él y sus seguidores fueron atacados por las fuerzas imperiales; "
"sin embargo, Amphyon era demasiado odiado por sus súbditos, y Aegaion era "
"demasiado popular y tenía demasiados seguidores. En el clímax de la corta "
"pero sangrienta Guerra Civil Skironiana, Aegaion mató personalmente a "
"Amphyon, lo convirtió en un monstruo no muerto y se coronó a sí mismo como "
"el Emperador Eterno de Skiron.\n"
"\n"
"Como nuevo gobernante, sí cumplió su promesa de mejorar la vida de la gente, "
"también convirtiendo a Skiron en una nación fuerte y rica una vez más. Sin "
"embargo, su intolerancia hacia los opositores es incluso mayor que la de "
"Amphyon, al igual que su violencia al tratar con enemigos. Sin embargo, "
"nadie es lo suficientemente valiente como para decirle a Aegaion que se ha "
"convertido en un monstruo mucho peor que aquel que ahora tira de su carro "
"personal."

