msgstr "refrescado"

#. [lua]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/dehydration-utils.cfg:216
msgid ""
"dehydrated: This unit is dehydrated. It will lose 4 HP and have its damage "
"reduced by 1 each turn during the day unless prevented by healers or cured "
"by water at an oasis.\n"
"\n"
"Units cannot be killed or deal no damage as a result of dehydration."
msgstr ""
"deshidratada: Esta unidad está deshidratada. Perderá 4 PV y tiene reducido "
"el daño en 1 por cada turno durante el día a no ser que lo impida un sanador "
"adyacente o se cure con agua en un oasis. \n"
"\n"
"Las unidades no pueden morir o dejar de hacer daño como resultado de la "
"deshidratación."

#. [unstore_unit]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/freezing-utils.cfg:147
msgid "freezing"
msgstr "congelado"

#. [unstore_unit]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/freezing-utils.cfg:200
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/freezing-utils.cfg:326
msgid "warmed"
msgstr "calentado"

#. [lua]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/freezing-utils.cfg:234
msgid ""
"frozen: This unit is freezing. It will lose 2 HP and have its damage reduced "
"by 1 each turn unless prevented by healers or shelter at a village, a keep "
"or a castle.\n"
"\n"
"Units cannot be killed or deal no damage as a result of freezing."
msgstr ""
"congelado: Esta unidad está congelándose. Perderá 2 PV y su daño se reducirá "
"en 1 cada turno a menos que sea prevenido por sanadores o se resguarde en "
"una aldea, torreón o castillo.\n"
"\n"
"Las unidades no pueden morir ni dejar de hacer daño como resultado de la "
"congelación."

#. [message], speaker=Hashira
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:15
msgid "No! I can't die before learning the truth...!"
msgstr "¡No! ¡No puedo morir antes de conocer la verdad...!"

#. [message], speaker=Ayraton
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:29
msgid "Ouch! Lady Hashira, please save-"
msgstr "¡Ay! Lady Hashira, por favor salva-"

#. [message], speaker=Hashira
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Damn it! I won't be able to understand that jewel's secrets without his aid!"
msgstr "¡Maldición! ¡No podré entender los secretos de esa joya sin su ayuda!"

#. [message], speaker=Akhen
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:47
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:110
msgid "I'm... not supposed to die now..."
msgstr "No... se supone que muera ahora..."

#. [message], speaker=Merwe
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:61
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:124
msgid "Ouch! Dammit, how could I fail like this... Akhen, I l-"
msgstr "¡Ay! Maldición, ¿cómo pude fallar así... Akhen, te qu-"

#. [message], speaker=Akhen
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:65
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:128
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:223
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:294
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:398
msgid "MERWE, NO!"
msgstr "¡MERWE, NO!"

#. [message], speaker=Mahyus
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:79
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:142
msgid "Aarrgh! Damn these lackeys..."
msgstr "¡Aarrgh! Malditos lacayos..."

#. [message], speaker=Atenak
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:93
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:156
msgid "I... have fallen...?!"
msgstr "Yo… ¿he caído…?"

#. [message], speaker=Nyx
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:170
msgid "I can't fall like this, I still have to avenge-"
msgstr "No puedo caer así, todavía tengo que vengar-"

#. [message], speaker=Sigdral
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:184
msgid ""
"To dream so much about knowing the outside world, only to die as I fulfill "
"it..."
msgstr ""
"Soñar tanto con conocer el mundo exterior, solo para morir mientras lo "
"cumplo..."

#. [message], speaker=Akhen
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:201
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:272
msgid "I now go join my ancestors; please, fight on without me, friends..."
msgstr ""
"Ahora voy a unirme a mis ancestros; por favor, sigan luchando sin mí, "
"amigos..."

#. [message], speaker=Nyx
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:205
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:276
msgid "AKHEN, NO! We can't go on without you!!!"
msgstr "¡AKHEN, NO! ¡No podemos continuar sin ti!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Merwe
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:219
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:290
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:394
msgid "I can't fall now, I must save our homeland...!"
msgstr "No puedo caer ahora, ¡debo salvar nuestra patria...!"

#. [message], speaker=Mahyus
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:237
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:308
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:412
msgid "At last the embrace of the Death Goddess has reached me... Darn it..."
msgstr ""
"Por fin el abrazo de la Diosa de la Muerte me ha alcanzado... Maldición..."

#. [message], speaker=Nyx
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:251
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:322
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:430
msgid "No, I... can't die yet, I must protect Ak-"
msgstr "No, yo... todavía no puedo morir, debo proteger a Ak-"

#. [message], speaker=Akhen
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:255
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:326
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:434
msgid "NYX, NO!!!"
msgstr "¡NYX, NO!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Branwyn
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:340
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:448
msgid "I can't fall now... Mahy-"
msgstr "No puedo caer ahora... Mahy-"

#. [message], speaker=Mahyus
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:344
msgid "BRANWYN, NO!!!"
msgstr "¡BRANWYN, NO!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Eren
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:358
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:523
msgid "(howls in pain)"
msgstr "(aúlla de dolor)"

#. [message], speaker=Merwe
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:362
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:527
msgid "Eren, no! You monsters, you will pay for that!"
msgstr "¡Eren, no! ¡Monstruos, pagarán por eso!"

#. [message], speaker=Akhen
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:376
msgid "How can I die now, so close to saving my land and Master Menon...?"
msgstr ""
"¿Cómo puedo morir ahora, tan cerca de salvar mi tierra y al Maestro Menon...?"

#. [message], speaker=Branwyn
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:416
msgid "Mahyus, please, don't die!!!"
msgstr "¡Mahyus, por favor, no mueras!!!"

#. [message], speaker=Mahyus
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:452
msgid "BRANWYN!!! How could I have let her die...?!"
msgstr "¡BRANWYN!!! ¿¡Cómo pude dejarla morir...!?"

#. [message], speaker=Atenak
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:466
msgid "I have failed my people..."
msgstr "He fallado a mi pueblo..."

#. [message], speaker=Sigdral
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:480
msgid "I mustn't... fall... My people... need me!..."
msgstr "No debo... caer... ¡Mi pueblo... me necesita!... "

#. [message], speaker=Gomatol
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/heroes-last-breath.cfg:494
msgid "Agh! Sorry, boys, I've failed you..."
msgstr "¡Agh! Lo siento, muchachos, les he fallado..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:8
msgid ""
"So, avid traveller, you have returned to hear yet another tale... I have "
"already told you the song of Myra of Hiera'Shirsha, the greatest heroine of "
"the ancient days, and of how her fate and that of so many other individuals "
"were knit together by the gem known as the Sky Soul. So, I will now tell of "
"the heirs and heiresses of those heroes who, having lost their homeland in "
"the Dragon War, crossed the vast ocean and reached the distant Netjer-Ta; I "
"shall tell you the song of Maat'Kare, the glorious city which, like its "
"founder, was nearly forgotten amidst the mists of time."
msgstr ""
"Entonces, ávido viajero, has regresado para escuchar otra historia más... Ya "
"te conté la canción de Myra de Hiera'Shirsha, la mayor heroína de los días "
"antiguos, y de cómo su destino y el de tantos otros individuos se "
"entrelazaron por la gema conocida como el Alma del Cielo. Así que ahora te "
"contaré de los herederos y herederas de esos héroes que, habiendo perdido su "
"patria en la Guerra de los Dragones, cruzaron el vasto océano y llegaron al "
"lejano Netjer-Ta; te contaré la canción de Maat'Kare, la gloriosa ciudad "
"que, como su fundador, casi fue olvidada entre las nieblas del tiempo."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:12
msgid ""
"The saga of Maat'Kare began, as you may remember, with the Continental War, "
"in which the Celestials were expelled from the continent by humans, dwarves "
"and wargs. After the war, Maat'Kare and its people thrived in peace "
"alongside the other human settlement in Netjer-Ta: Hiera'Laksha, home of the "
"wise Order of the Windsong."
msgstr ""
"La saga de Maat'Kare comenzó, como quizás recuerdes, con la Guerra "
"Continental, en la que los Celestiales fueron expulsados del continente por "
"humanos, enanos y huargos. Después de la guerra, Maat'Kare y su pueblo "
"prosperaron en paz junto al otro asentamiento humano en Netjer-Ta: "
"Hiera'Laksha, hogar de la sabia Orden de las Hijas del Viento."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Both Maat'Kare and Hiera'Laksha benefited greatly from their alliance, often "
"helping each other whenever it was necessary. However, neither of them "
"meddled in the other's internal affairs; for even though the Windsong were "
"all native Maat'Karians, they preserved their Order's autonomy."
msgstr ""
"Tanto Maat'Kare como Hiera'Laksha se beneficiaron enormemente de su alianza, "
"a menudo ayudándose mutuamente cuando era necesario. Sin embargo, ninguno de "
"ellos se entrometió en los asuntos internos del otro; porque aunque las "
"Hijas del Viento eran todas nativas maat'karianas, preservaron la autonomía "
"de su Orden."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:20
msgid ""
"The two cities remained good allies for over nine centuries, until the time "
"of Hashira, Head of the Windsong and heiress of the Aelones, an influential "
"family that descended of Ravyan of Garet-Desh, one of Maat'Kare's Founders. "
"Being a Windsong, she was thirsty for knowledge, and at the age of thirty-"
"one she'd already authored many scrolls based on her experiences and "
"discoveries."
msgstr ""
"Las dos ciudades permanecieron como buenos aliados durante más de nueve "
"siglos, hasta la época de Hashira, Jefa de las Hijas del Viento y heredera "
"de los Aelones, una familia influyente que descendía de Ravyan de Garet-"
"Desh, uno de los Fundadores de Maat'Kare. Siendo una Hija del Viento, tenía "
"sed de conocimiento, y a la edad de treinta y un años ya había escrito "
"muchos pergaminos basados en sus experiencias y descubrimientos."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:24
msgid ""
"However, her greatest ambition was to find out the truth about the 'Garnet "
"of the Cursed Souls', a jewel whose existence was considered by everyone as "
"mere folk tale, since no scroll even mentioned it, but which Hashira "
"believed to be the explanation to many strange events surrounding the Dragon "
"War and the Exodus towards Netjer-Ta."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, su mayor ambición era descubrir la verdad sobre el «Granate de "
"las Almas Malditas», una joya cuya existencia era considerada por todos como "
"un mero cuento popular, ya que ningún pergamino siquiera la mencionaba, pero "
"que Hashira creía que era la explicación a muchos eventos extraños alrededor "
"de la Guerra de los Dragones y el Éxodo hacia Netjer-Ta."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:28
msgid ""
"One day, while studying her family's documents, she found a journal written "
"by Ravyan himself, a journal whose existence had been entirely unknown to "
"anyone until then. And there, in those manuscripts, she found the evidence "
"that the fabled Garnet was much more than mere legend."
msgstr ""
"Un día, mientras estudiaba los documentos de su familia, encontró un diario "
"escrito por el propio Ravyan, un diario cuya existencia había sido "
"completamente desconocida para cualquiera hasta entonces. Y allí, en esos "
"manuscritos, encontró la evidencia de que el legendario Granate era mucho "
"más que una mera leyenda."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Hashira kept that discovery for herself, fearful that someone might steal "
"the glory of finding the Garnet. However, she knew that, if her theory about "
"the gem's true nature was right, she'd need the aid of an expert on spirit "
"lore, and so she hired a young mage of the Umbra Arts called Ayraton, who "
"accepted her condition of absolute secrecy about their work. Afterwards, she "
"gathered her personal soldiers and set out for the Silent Desert, where, "
"according to the journal, the Garnet had been lost. Little did she know how "
"her expedition would affect the future of Maat’Kare and of the whole "
"continent..."
msgstr ""
"Hashira guardó ese descubrimiento para sí misma, temerosa de que alguien "
"pudiera robarle la gloria de encontrar el Granate. Sin embargo, sabía que, "
"si su teoría sobre la verdadera naturaleza de la gema era correcta, "
"necesitaría la ayuda de un experto en conocimiento de espíritus, y por eso "
"contrató a un joven mago de las Artes Umbra llamado Ayraton, quien aceptó su "
"condición de secreto absoluto sobre su trabajo. Después, reunió a sus "
"soldados personales y partió hacia el Desierto Silencioso, donde, según el "
"diario, el Granate se había perdido. Poco sabía ella cómo su expedición "
"afectaría el futuro de Maat'Kare y de todo el continente..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:43
msgid ""
"And so the Sky Soul was retrieved from the place where it had lain for "
"centuries; Hashira managed to disguise the gem's energy with her ciphers, "
"which allowed her to take it through the cities unnoticed. Once at the "
"remote village of Hatshep, she provided Ayraton with everything he'd need to "
"work and live at her mansion."
msgstr ""
"Y así el Alma del Cielo fue recuperada del lugar donde había yacido durante "
"siglos; Hashira logró disfrazar la energía de la gema con sus cifrados, lo "
"que le permitió llevarla a través de las ciudades sin ser notada. Una vez en "
"el remoto pueblo de Hatshep, le proporcionó a Ayraton todo lo que "
"necesitaría para trabajar y vivir en su mansión."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:46
msgid ""
"Thus many weeks passed; the young mage gave his best to understand the gem's "
"secrets; and, considering that he had almost no previous lore to base "
"himself on, he was doing quite well."
msgstr ""
"Así pasaron muchas semanas; el joven mago dio lo mejor de sí para entender "
"los secretos de la gema; y, considerando que casi no tenía conocimiento "
"previo en el que basarse, lo estaba haciendo bastante bien."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:49
msgid ""
"The first thing he discovered was that each of the four souls was in a "
"dormant state; then, he found out that the gem had different levels of "
"power, the shallowest ones being connected to the souls of the three Fire "
"Dragons. The deepest, most unreachable level accessed the power of the Sky "
"Dragon's soul itself, but the presence of the others hindered his energy's "
"outflow. In other words, the Sky Soul's true power could not be fathomed due "
"to the three fire dragons' souls; to solve this problem, Hashira ordered "
"Ayraton to find a way to split them into separate gems."
msgstr ""
"Lo primero que descubrió fue que cada una de las cuatro almas estaba en un "
"estado latente; luego, descubrió que la gema tenía diferentes niveles de "
"poder, los más superficiales conectados a las almas de los tres Dragones de "
"Fuego. El nivel más profundo e inalcanzable accedía al poder del alma del "
"propio Dragón del Cielo, pero la presencia de los otros dificultaba el flujo "
"de su energía. En otras palabras, el verdadero poder del Alma del Cielo no "
"podía ser comprendido debido a las almas de los tres dragones de fuego; para "
"resolver este problema, Hashira ordenó a Ayraton que encontrara una forma de "
"dividirlas en gemas separadas."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:52
msgid ""
"Only one thing spoiled Hashira's enthusiasm in those days: the growing "
"suspicion of her fiercest oppositionist, Ithania, who accused her of "
"involving Hiera’Laksha in Maat'Kare's politics through her family's "
"influence in the two Chambers. She had never been much more than a nuisance, "
"but Hashira's frequent and unexplained travels to Hatshep started raising "
"suspicion not only amongst the Windsong, but also, as she later discovered, "
"amongst Maat'Kare's politicians."
msgstr ""
"Solo una cosa arruinaba el entusiasmo de Hashira en aquellos días: la "
"creciente sospecha de su más feroz opositora, Ithania, quien la acusaba de "
"involucrar a Hiera'Laksha en la política de Maat'Kare a través de la "
"influencia de su familia en las dos Cámaras. Nunca había sido mucho más que "
"una molestia, pero los frecuentes y inexplicables viajes de Hashira a "
"Hatshep comenzaron a levantar sospechas no solo entre las Hijas del Viento, "
"sino también, como descubrió más tarde, entre los políticos de Maat'Kare."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:55
msgid ""
"Alarmed with the increasing pressure on her, Hashira daringly decided to "
"take Ayraton to Hiera'Laksha. She cleverly avoided her sisters' criticism by "
"claiming that the Chambers were spying on her, thus earning their support, "
"for the Windsong took that as an insult to their leader. Then, she explained "
"about the Sky Soul, claiming that she was trying to find a way to destroy it "
"for good. Only Ithania did not believe Hashira's words, and left the "
"Windsong Foundation in protest."
msgstr ""
"Alarmada por la presión creciente sobre ella, Hashira decidió audazmente "
"llevar a Ayraton a Hiera'Laksha. Evitó hábilmente las críticas de sus "
"hermanas alegando que las Cámaras la estaban espiando, ganando así su apoyo, "
"porque las Hijas del Viento tomaron eso como un insulto a su líder. Luego, "
"explicó sobre el Alma del Cielo, afirmando que estaba tratando de encontrar "
"una forma de destruirla definitivamente. Solo Ithania no creyó en las "
"palabras de Hashira, y dejó la Fundación de las Hijas del Viento en protesta."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:58
msgid ""
"For a few days, Ayraton calmly continued his work at Hiera'Laksha, now with "
"the aid of many Windsong assistants. However, certain morning he, Hashira "
"and her sisters were awakened by the alarming shouts of the oathkeepers: two "
"people stood before the Bald Mountain, one being Ithania, and the other "
"being the Master of Four Lights himself..."
msgstr ""
"Durante unos días, Ayraton continuó tranquilamente su trabajo en "
"Hiera'Laksha, ahora con la ayuda de muchas asistentes Hijas del Viento. Sin "
"embargo, cierta mañana él, Hashira y sus hermanas fueron despertados por los "
"gritos alarmantes de los guardianes del juramento: dos personas estaban "
"frente a la Montaña Calva, una era Ithania y la otra era el propio Maestro "
"de las Cuatro Luces..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:68
msgid ""
"The year 907 of Maat'Kare's calendar was marked by what was known as the "
"Treason: the humans received the news of the Windsong's departure with "
"shock, and there were some who even suspected some trickery by Menon - who "
"had his share of enemies, after all - but, with time, the Maat'Karians only "
"remembered their former allies as betrayers, and Hiera'Laksha became a "
"Maat'Karian fortress."
msgstr ""
"El año 907 del calendario de Maat'Kare quedó marcado por lo que se conoció "
"como la Traición: los humanos recibieron la noticia de la partida de las "
"Hijas del Viento con conmoción, y hubo quienes incluso sospecharon alguna "
"artimaña de Menon —quien tenía sus enemigos, después de todo—, pero con el "
"tiempo los maat'karianos solo recordaron a sus antiguos aliados como "
"traidores, y Hiera'Laksha se convirtió en una fortaleza maat'kariana."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:72
msgid ""
"The Sky Soul's existence was only revealed to the Sages, who unanimously "
"agreed that Menon was the one best fit to keep it. Although he initially "
"refused, he ultimately accepted the task. In fact, he became so dedicated to "
"it that he even abandoned his military career, joining the Academy as a "
"professor so he might settle down; and, when he reached certain age, he "
"requested the Chamber of Sages permission to become a lich, so that he might "
"keep the Soul until he found someone else worthy enough to protect it in his "
"stead."
msgstr ""
"La existencia del Alma del Cielo solo fue revelada a los Sabios, quienes "
"acordaron por unanimidad que Menon era la persona más adecuada para "
"custodiarla. Aunque inicialmente se negó, finalmente aceptó la tarea. De "
"hecho, se dedicó tanto a ella que incluso abandonó su carrera militar, "
"uniéndose a la Academia como profesor para asentarse; y cuando alcanzó "
"cierta edad, solicitó permiso a la Cámara de los Sabios para convertirse en "
"liche, a fin de poder custodiar el Alma hasta encontrar a alguien más digno "
"de protegerla en su lugar."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:76
msgid ""
"And so Menon guarded the Sky Soul for seven centuries; by the year 1614 of "
"Maat'Kare's calendar, he was revered as the Chief Elder of the Chamber of "
"Sages and as the Elder Headmaster of the Academy. And it is there that our "
"tale continues; with a student called Akhen, the last heir of the House of "
"Wadjet, famous all over Netjer-Ta for being the descendants of Myra of "
"Hiera'Shirsha herself..."
msgstr ""
"Y así Menon custodió el Alma del Cielo durante siete siglos; para el año "
"1614 del calendario de Maat'Kare, era reverenciado como el Gran Anciano de "
"la Cámara de los Sabios y como el Director Anciano de la Academia. Y es allí "
"donde continúa nuestro relato: con un estudiante llamado Akhen, el último "
"heredero de la Casa de Wadjet, famosa en todo Netjer-Ta por ser "
"descendientes de la propia Myra de Hiera'Shirsha..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:81
msgid "Part IV: City of the Sun"
msgstr "Parte IV: Ciudad del Sol"

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:91
msgid ""
"That night, the Maat'Karians slept until sunrise - except for Akhen, who "
"stayed awaken before the bound Nyx, trying to start a conversation, but only "
"getting long silences punctuated by occasional angry snorts as response. "
"After many hours, the vampiress, annoyed at the young man's relentless gaze, "
"revealed that she was an exiled vampire seeking a safe haven for herself. "
"That was far from being enough to satisfy Akhen's curiosity, but he decided "
"not to press her any more."
msgstr ""
"Aquella noche, los maat'karianos durmieron hasta el amanecer, excepto Akhen, "
"quien permaneció despierto frente a Nyx encadenada, intentando iniciar una "
"conversación, pero solo recibiendo largos silencios interrumpidos por "
"ocasionales resoplidos enfadados como respuesta. Después de muchas horas, la "
"vampiresa, molesta por la mirada insistente del joven, reveló que era una "
"vampira exiliada que buscaba un refugio seguro para sí misma. Eso estaba "
"lejos de satisfacer la curiosidad de Akhen, pero decidió no presionarla más."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:95
msgid ""
"Nevertheless, he didn't make any progress in the following days. He sought "
"to make her feel as comfortable as possible, sending elementals to hunt for "
"her, and even yielding his own horse to her, but she rejected his "
"courtesies. Still, because she was being ogled by the soldiers - for even "
"though she was a vampire, her beauty was outstanding - she accepted a place "
"in the provisions' chariot, where she nestled amidst the piles of food to "
"avoid everyone's stares."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, no hizo ningún progreso en los días siguientes. Intentó que se "
"sintiera lo más cómoda posible, enviando elementales a cazar para ella e "
"incluso cediéndole su propio caballo, pero ella rechazó sus cortesías. Aun "
"así, como los soldados la observaban con insistencia —pues aunque era una "
"vampira, su belleza era extraordinaria—, aceptó un lugar en el carro de "
"provisiones, donde se acomodó entre las pilas de comida para evitar las "
"miradas de todos."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:99
msgid ""
"Ten days after their departure from Maat'Kare, the retinue reached the Cyan "
"Mountains and entered the so-called Celestial Path, a series of valleys that "
"connected the Sun Path to the Silent Desert; and which, in ancient times, "
"was often used by Celestial armies. Following this path, Atenak and her "
"retinue reached the Valley of Alenya, where they were faced with more "
"unexpected events..."
msgstr ""
"Diez días después de su partida de Maat'Kare, el séquito llegó a las "
"Montañas Cyan y entró en el llamado Camino Celestial, una serie de valles "
"que conectaban el Camino del Sol con el Desierto Silencioso; y que, en "
"tiempos antiguos, era usado frecuentemente por los ejércitos Celestiales. "
"Siguiendo este camino, Atenak y su séquito llegaron al Valle de Alenya, "
"donde se enfrentaron a más eventos inesperados..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:110
msgid ""
"Sigdral's presence in the expedition helped lift the soldiers' spirits; not "
"only did she amuse everyone with her little quarrels with Nyx, but she also "
"renewed the Maat'Karians' confidence with her relentless energy and "
"impressive power."
msgstr ""
"La presencia de Sigdral en la expedición ayudó a levantar el ánimo de los "
"soldados; no solo divertía a todos con sus pequeñas disputas con Nyx, sino "
"que también renovaba la confianza de los maat'karianos con su energía "
"incansable y su poder impresionante."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:114
msgid ""
"Besides, having the dwarf maiden nearby made the vampiress warm up - albeit "
"only a little - to the humans. She even surprised everyone certain night, "
"when she brought two huge boars from her nightly hunt and gave them to the "
"Maat'Karians. When thanked for the gifts, she claimed that she simply had "
"eaten enough already, and didn't want to let the boars go to waste. Both "
"Akhen and Sigdral, however, knew that she actually wanted to be friendly "
"with them all."
msgstr ""
"Además, tener cerca a la doncella enana hizo que la vampiresa se acercara —"
"aunque solo un poco— a los humanos. Incluso sorprendió a todos cierta noche, "
"cuando trajo dos jabalíes enormes de su cacería nocturna y se los entregó a "
"los maat'karianos. Cuando le agradecieron los regalos, ella afirmó que "
"simplemente ya había comido suficiente y no quería que los jabalíes se "
"desperdiciaran. Sin embargo, tanto Akhen como Sigdral sabían que en realidad "
"quería ser amable con todos ellos."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:118
msgid ""
"They soon reached the Silent Desert, and from that point on even Sigdral "
"became more serious; after all, in addition to the well-known dangers of the "
"region, there was an orcish host on the move - and whatever evil that had "
"destroyed Desret. However, as they crossed the dunes, only scorpions, small "
"Gnoll bands and a scorching heat harassed them; and it was this strange "
"calmness that made them increasingly nervous..."
msgstr ""
"Pronto llegaron al Desierto Silencioso, y a partir de ese punto incluso "
"Sigdral se volvió más seria; después de todo, además de los peligros "
"conocidos de la región, había un ejército orco en movimiento, y lo que fuera "
"que había destruido Desret. Sin embargo, mientras cruzaban las dunas, solo "
"los escorpiones, pequeñas bandas de gnolls y un calor abrasador los "
"hostigaban; y fue esta extraña calma la que los ponía cada vez más "
"nerviosos..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:129
msgid ""
"Both Akhen and Merwe had always wanted to sail the blue eastern ocean, but "
"certainly not in a ship run by a crew of skeletons and walking corpses, nor "
"under a Lich-Lady's onerous gaze that made even Mahyus, who was used to the "
"company of undead, feel extremely uneasy."
msgstr ""
"Tanto Akhen como Merwe siempre habían querido navegar por el océano azul "
"oriental, pero ciertamente no en un barco tripulado por esqueletos y "
"cadáveres andantes, ni bajo la mirada onerosa de una Dama Liche que hacía "
"que incluso Mahyus, acostumbrado a la compañía de no muertos, se sintiera "
"extremadamente incómodo."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:132
msgid ""
"Atenak quickly recovered from Stygia's attack, thanks to Merwe's and "
"Sigdral's skills. She was calm enough; she saw no reason for the Lich-Lady "
"to cause them any further harm if only they gave her no reason to, for she "
"wouldn't be able to walk two steps into Maat'Kare otherwise. When queried "
"about the ruined village discovered near Desret, the commander simply "
"remained in silence."
msgstr ""
"Atenak se recuperó rápidamente del ataque de Stygia, gracias a las "
"habilidades de Merwe y Sigdral. Estaba lo suficientemente tranquila; no veía "
"motivo para que la Dama Liche les causara más daño siempre y cuando no le "
"dieran razones, pues de otro modo no podría dar ni dos pasos en Maat'Kare. "
"Cuando le preguntaron por la aldea en ruinas descubierta cerca de Desret, la "
"comandante simplemente permaneció en silencio."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:135
msgid ""
"The Skironians' naval prowess became evident when the Maat'Karians spotted "
"their city's towers on the horizon a mere two days after their departure "
"from Desret. As expected, there was a huge stir in the city at the sight of "
"Stygia's banners, more so as the Lich-Lady paraded throughout Maat'Kare, "
"followed by city guards and by the defeated expedition. It was evident that "
"her goal was the Hall of the Sages, and so the Sages and the Lords hurriedly "
"gathered there..."
msgstr ""
"El poder naval de los skironianos se hizo evidente cuando los maat'karianos "
"avistaron las torres de su ciudad en el horizonte apenas dos días después de "
"su partida de Desret. Como era de esperar, hubo un gran revuelo en la ciudad "
"al ver los estandartes de Stygia, más aún cuando la Dama Liche desfiló por "
"Maat'Kare, seguida por guardias de la ciudad y por la expedición derrotada. "
"Era evidente que su objetivo era el Salón de los Sabios, por lo que los "
"Sabios y los Señores se reunieron apresuradamente allí..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:145
msgid ""
"Few were the Maat'Karians who had ever witnessed such stir in their country: "
"messengers ran throughout Maat'Karian lands, and soon entire platoons began "
"rallying at the larger settlements; and, in order to protect Maat'Kare from "
"sea attacks, the mages raised the Nitiballi Wall, a long line of powerful "
"water elementals around the entire Land's End peninsula."
msgstr ""
"Pocos fueron los maat'karianos que habían presenciado tal revuelo en su "
"país: los mensajeros corrían por las tierras maat'karianas, y pronto "
"pelotones enteros comenzaron a concentrarse en los asentamientos más "
"grandes; y para proteger Maat'Kare de ataques por mar, los magos alzaron el "
"Muro Nitiballi, una larga línea de poderosos elementales de agua alrededor "
"de toda la península de Land's End."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:148
msgid ""
"In the city halls, lords and generals discussed strategies, and in every "
"household the citizens commented on the latest events, from the orcs' "
"refusal to ally with the humans to Menon's controversial exile - but no word "
"was uttered about the Sky Soul, for the Lords decided to hide it from the "
"civilians, at least for the time being."
msgstr ""
"En los salones de la ciudad, señores y generales discutían estrategias, y en "
"cada hogar los ciudadanos comentaban los últimos acontecimientos, desde la "
"negativa de los orcos a aliarse con los humanos hasta el controvertido "
"exilio de Menon; pero no se pronunció ni una palabra sobre el Alma del "
"Cielo, pues los Señores decidieron ocultarla a los civiles, al menos por el "
"momento."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:151
msgid ""
"Meanwhile, the three friends remained stuck at the Academy alongside the "
"other veterans - because classes were suspended due to the war declaration, "
"younger students were sent back to their respective homes. Atseger had "
"indeed put them in a mage battalion led by Sadjet, the 'Fire Empress', but "
"until she received further orders from the Chamber of Sages, she and her "
"mages had nothing to do. However, the friends wouldn't simply watch idly as "
"everyone else did something to prepare their nation for the looming war..."
msgstr ""
"Mientras tanto, los tres amigos permanecieron varados en la Academia junto a "
"los demás veteranos. Como las clases fueron suspendidas debido a la "
"declaración de guerra, los estudiantes más jóvenes fueron enviados de vuelta "
"a sus hogares. Atseger los había asignado a un batallón de magos liderado "
"por Sadjet, la «Emperatriz del Fuego», pero hasta que recibiera nuevas "
"órdenes de la Cámara de los Sabios, ella y sus magos no tenían nada que "
"hacer. Sin embargo, los amigos no se conformarían con mirar ociosamente "
"mientras los demás hacían algo para preparar su nación para la guerra que se "
"avecinaba..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:161
msgid ""
"The rest of the meeting didn't last long; the same, however, couldn't be "
"said of Sigdral's lecture: she couldn't believe that Nyx had been so close "
"to being handed over to the enemy, and Vindalf, still feeling guilty, "
"received his sister's wrath upon himself in silence. When she knew that the "
"vampiress was going to follow the Maat'Karians, she decided to go with them, "
"and Vindalf, true to his promise to Nyx, was forced to allow that."
msgstr ""
"El resto de la reunión no duró mucho; sin embargo, no se podía decir lo "
"mismo de la reprimenda de Sigdral: no podía creer que Nyx hubiera estado tan "
"cerca de ser entregada al enemigo, y Vindalf, todavía sintiéndose culpable, "
"recibió en silencio la ira de su hermana. Cuando supo que la vampiresa iba a "
"seguir a los maat'karianos, decidió ir con ellos, y Vindalf, fiel a su "
"promesa a Nyx, se vio obligado a permitirlo."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:165
msgid ""
"Back to Maat'Kare, there was great consternation with the news of the "
"alliance between Skiron and Erynia. New plans were made: General Smenkhare "
"and Sadjet were both ordered to join Romlur's wargs and Vindalf's dwarves in "
"the campaign against the vampires."
msgstr ""
"De vuelta en Maat'Kare, hubo gran consternación con la noticia de la alianza "
"entre Skiron y Erynia. Se hicieron nuevos planes: tanto el general Smenkhare "
"como Sadjet recibieron la orden de unirse a los huargos de Romlur y a los "
"enanos de Vindalf en la campaña contra los vampiros."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:169
msgid ""
"The three friends, however, didn't follow the Fire Empress' mages. In fact, "
"they'd have been removed from the war by the very mad Atseger - after all, "
"they had left Sadjet's battalion without permission - were it not for a "
"miraculous letter from Tewarin, who pleaded with the Headmistress to let "
"them accompany his niece in yet another mission. Unwilling to refuse a "
"Lord's request, Atseger let them go; Sigdral and Nyx, who had been having "
"fun at the near-deserted Academy in the meantime, followed them."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, los tres amigos no siguieron a los magos de la Emperatriz del "
"Fuego. De hecho, habrían sido apartados de la guerra por la propia Atseger —"
"después de todo, habían abandonado el batallón de Sadjet sin permiso— de no "
"ser por una milagrosa carta de Tewarin, quien suplicó a la Directora que les "
"permitiera acompañar a su sobrina en otra misión. Poco dispuesta a rechazar "
"la petición de un Señor, Atseger los dejó ir; Sigdral y Nyx, que se habían "
"estado divirtiendo en la casi desierta Academia mientras tanto, los "
"siguieron."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:173
msgid ""
"Thus, the five friends met Atenak again, and she explained their mission: to "
"infiltrate orcish territory and take Grimbek, the most important fortress in "
"western Netjer-Ta, and which was currently controlled by Varag, to secure a "
"Maat'Karian outpost in the region. According to the dwarves' reports, "
"Varag's forces were depleted, and so conquering his fortress shouldn't be "
"troublesome. The hardest part was taking it before other orcish chieftains "
"did, and so they swiftly sailed down the River Ruthen and reached the orcs' "
"land two weeks after Stygia's truce expired..."
msgstr ""
"Así, los cinco amigos se reunieron de nuevo con Atenak, y ella les explicó "
"su misión: infiltrarse en territorio orco y tomar Grimbek, la fortaleza más "
"importante del oeste de Netjer-Ta, que en ese momento estaba controlada por "
"Varag, para asegurar un puesto avanzado maat'kariano en la región. Según los "
"informes de los enanos, las fuerzas de Varag estaban debilitadas, por lo que "
"conquistar su fortaleza no debería ser problemático. La parte más difícil "
"era tomarla antes de que lo hicieran otros jefes orcos, por lo que navegaron "
"rápidamente por el río Ruthen y llegaron a las tierras de los orcos dos "
"semanas después de que expirara la tregua de Stygia..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:184
msgid ""
"The Maat’Karians stayed in their new allies' lands until they finished "
"repairing Grimbek and fixing its weak points - both a token of good will and "
"a way of ensuring they were able to better withstand their enemies. The "
"humans were surprised by the orcs' behaviour: though sullen and suspicious-"
"looking, they treated their guests very cordially. While the orcs worked on "
"the old fortress, Atenak sent messages to Maat'Kare, informing the Chamber "
"of Lords of that new human-orcish alliance."
msgstr ""
"Los maat'karianos permanecieron en las tierras de sus nuevos aliados hasta "
"que terminaron de reparar Grimbek y reforzar sus puntos débiles, tanto como "
"muestra de buena voluntad como para asegurarse de poder resistir mejor a sus "
"enemigos. Los humanos se sorprendieron por el comportamiento de los orcos: "
"aunque parecían hoscos y desconfiados, trataron a sus invitados con mucha "
"cortesía. Mientras los orcos trabajaban en la antigua fortaleza, Atenak "
"envió mensajes a Maat'Kare informando a la Cámara de los Señores sobre esta "
"nueva alianza humano-orca."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:188
msgid ""
"Ten days after the battle against Skotas, just as the Maat'Karians began "
"complaining of boredom, they sighted a small, but hardened dwarvish troop "
"led by Gomatol passing near Varag's lands. After some commotion, Atenak and "
"the others met him on a nearby hill - for the orcs staunchly refused to let "
"dwarves in their lands -, and there he informed the humans about the latest "
"events:"
msgstr ""
"Diez días después de la batalla contra Skotas, justo cuando los "
"maat'karianos empezaban a quejarse del aburrimiento, avistaron una pequeña "
"pero endurecida tropa enana liderada por Gomatol que pasaba cerca de las "
"tierras de Varag. Tras cierto alboroto, Atenak y los demás se reunieron con "
"él en una colina cercana —pues los orcos se negaban rotundamente a dejar "
"entrar enanos en sus tierras—, y allí él informó a los humanos sobre los "
"últimos acontecimientos:"

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:192
msgid ""
"The Silent Desert had become Skironian possession, and the dwarves fought "
"hordes of undead day and night in the outskirts of the mountain ranges; "
"Suryen's army held the Skironians off in the Celestial Path, aided by the "
"Academy's elemental and light mages. Meanwhile, on the northern front, the "
"wargs and the Maat'Karians led by Smenkhare and Sadjet turned the snow of "
"Netjer-Ta's north red with vampire blood, but a sudden and violent blizzard "
"currently prevented them from further advancing."
msgstr ""
"El Desierto Silencioso se había convertido en posesión skironian, y los "
"enanos luchaban contra hordas de no muertos día y noche en las afueras de "
"las cadenas montañosas. El ejército de Suryen contenía a los skironianos en "
"el Camino Celestial, ayudado por los magos elementales y de luz de la "
"Academia. Mientras tanto, en el frente norte, los huargos y los "
"maat'karianos liderados por Smenkhare y Sadjet teñían de rojo la nieve del "
"norte de Netjer-Ta con sangre de vampiros, pero una repentina y violenta "
"ventisca les impedía avanzar más."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:196
msgid ""
"It was then that Gomatol explained his own mission: to infiltrate vampire "
"land, reach Erynia and assassinate her, taking advantage of the fact that "
"the brunt of her forces was busy fighting the allies. For this, he was going "
"to use an ancient system of caves that was known to the Motsoghnir, but "
"which had been cut off from their main tunnels ages before by an earthquake."
msgstr ""
"Fue entonces cuando Gomatol explicó su propia misión: infiltrarse en tierras "
"vampiras, llegar a Erynia y asesinarla, aprovechando que la mayor parte de "
"sus fuerzas estaba ocupada luchando contra los aliados. Para ello, iba a "
"usar un antiguo sistema de cuevas conocido por los Motsoghnir, pero que "
"había quedado aislado de sus túneles principales hacía mucho tiempo por un "
"terremoto."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:200
msgid ""
"Nyx offered to go alongside them, arguing that they'd need someone who knew "
"the vampires' land well. At first, Gomatol refused to accept a vampiress in "
"his group, until Atenak - hearing the pleas of Akhen and Sigdral - decided "
"to go with them as well. Varag also supported her decision, claiming that, "
"if the vampires attacked him as they did every year, he'd be overburdened "
"with enemies coming from all sides. Thus, the Maat'Karians left their new "
"allies and followed the dwarves to the frozen northern mountains..."
msgstr ""
"Nyx se ofreció a ir con ellos, argumentando que necesitarían a alguien que "
"conociera bien las tierras vampiras. Al principio Gomatol se negó a aceptar "
"a una vampiresa en su grupo, hasta que Atenak —escuchando las súplicas de "
"Akhen y Sigdral— decidió ir con ellos también. Varag también apoyó su "
"decisión, afirmando que si los vampiros lo atacaban como hacían cada año, se "
"vería sobrecargado de enemigos por todos lados. Así, los maat'karianos "
"dejaron a sus nuevos aliados y siguieron a los enanos hacia las montañas "
"heladas del norte..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:211
msgid ""
"The success of Gomatol's and Atenak's mission was very celebrated by the "
"allied troops, who, worn out after days battling large enemy hosts and "
"snowstorms, feared facing a too well-defended Red Pinnacle - whose "
"inhabitants had mostly fled after Erynia's fall, suspecting Skironian "
"treachery."
msgstr ""
"El éxito de la misión de Gomatol y Atenak fue muy celebrado por las tropas "
"aliadas, que, agotadas tras días luchando contra grandes ejércitos enemigos "
"y tormentas de nieve, temían enfrentarse a un Pináculo Rojo demasiado bien "
"defendido, cuyos habitantes habían huido en su mayoría tras la caída de "
"Erynia, sospechando traición skironian."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:215
msgid ""
"Nyx too seemed satisfied and relieved - after all, she had finally managed "
"to avenge her father and siblings - but that wasn't all: she also seemed "
"happier than even Sigdral had ever seen before, and was increasingly warmer "
"to her human friends, especially Akhen. Indeed, the general mood amongst the "
"Maat'Karians as they returned home couldn't be better."
msgstr ""
"Nyx también parecía satisfecha y aliviada —después de todo, finalmente había "
"conseguido vengar a su padre y a sus hermanos—, pero no era solo eso: "
"también parecía más feliz de lo que Sigdral la había visto nunca, y se "
"mostraba cada vez más cercana con sus amigos humanos, especialmente con "
"Akhen. De hecho, el ánimo general entre los maat'karianos mientras "
"regresaban a casa no podía ser mejor."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:219
msgid ""
"But their enthusiasm lasted only until the moment they reached Maat'Kare..."
msgstr ""
"Pero su entusiasmo duró solo hasta el momento en que llegaron a Maat'Kare..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:230
msgid ""
"The emergency council at the Chamber of Sages ended as expected: although "
"Tewarin did his best to dissuade the Sages, he had too little support - most "
"of his fellow Lords were not present - and the enthusiasm caused by Menon's "
"heroic feat was too great; thus, he was indeed given the title of Great Seer "
"of Maat'Kare, which he promised to hold only until the war's conclusion."
msgstr ""
"El consejo de emergencia en la Cámara de los Sabios terminó como se "
"esperaba: aunque Tewarin hizo todo lo posible por disuadir a los Sabios, "
"tenía muy poco apoyo —la mayoría de sus compañeros Señores no estaban "
"presentes— y el entusiasmo provocado por la hazaña heroica de Menon era "
"demasiado grande; así que efectivamente se le concedió el título de Gran "
"Vidente de Maat'Kare, que prometió mantener solo hasta el final de la guerra."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:234
msgid ""
"And he wasted no time in making use of his new powers: firstly, he informed "
"the faraway Maat'Karians of the Sages' ruling, and then he redesigned the "
"armies' strategies, sending Smenkhare and Sadjet to block the advance of the "
"Skironians on the Celestial Path - where the wargs were currently fighting - "
"and relocating Suryen's army to the Gnoll Swamps. Additionally, he "
"commissioned Tewarin to help Atseger as she reinforced Varag in the west, "
"which he begrudgingly obeyed."
msgstr ""
"Y no perdió tiempo en hacer uso de sus nuevos poderes: primero informó a los "
"maat'karianos lejanos sobre la decisión de los Sabios, luego rediseñó las "
"estrategias de los ejércitos, enviando a Smenkhare y Sadjet a bloquear el "
"avance de los skironianos en el Camino Celestial —donde los huargos estaban "
"luchando en ese momento— y reubicando el ejército de Suryen en los Pantanos "
"de los Gnolls. Además, encargó a Tewarin ayudar a Atseger mientras reforzaba "
"a Varag en el oeste, lo cual obedeció de mala gana."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:238
msgid ""
"The rivalry between the Lord and the Master of Four Lights didn't extend to "
"their respective charges - which, in Menon's own words, was a fortunate "
"thing -, and, because Tewarin didn't request his niece to accompany him, "
"Atenak, Akhen, their friends and her soldiers - which became informally "
"known as the Myra Battalion - remained together."
msgstr ""
"La rivalidad entre el Señor y el Maestro de las Cuatro Luces no se extendió "
"a sus respectivos subordinados —lo cual, en palabras del propio Menon, fue "
"una cosa afortunada—, y como Tewarin no solicitó que su sobrina lo "
"acompañara, Atenak, Akhen, sus amigos y sus soldados —que se conocieron "
"informalmente como el Batallón Myra— permanecieron juntos."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:242
msgid ""
"And they didn't remain idle for long. Two weeks after the Siege of "
"Maat'Kare, Menon ordered them to help General Suryen, foreseeing that he "
"might be having problems fighting the Skironians, and thus the Myra "
"Battalion wasted no time going there..."
msgstr ""
"Y no permanecieron ociosos por mucho tiempo. Dos semanas después del Asedio "
"de Maat'Kare, Menon les ordenó ayudar al general Suryen, previendo que "
"podría estar teniendo problemas para combatir a los skironianos, por lo que "
"el Batallón Myra no perdió tiempo en dirigirse allí..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:253
msgid ""
"Heartened by the victory against Maurias, Suryen's army pressed on "
"southwards, and soon they had cleansed the entirety of the Gnoll Swamps of "
"Skironians and established a base at the Peaks of Meditation, a group of "
"mountains in the northern outskirts of the Silent Desert. Smenkhare and "
"Sadjet met Suryen there a few days later, having decisively blocked the "
"enemy advance in the Celestial Path."
msgstr ""
"Animado por la victoria contra Maurias, el ejército de Suryen avanzó hacia "
"el sur, y pronto habían limpiado por completo los Pantanos de los Gnolls de "
"skironianos y establecido una base en los Picos de la Meditación, un grupo "
"de montañas en las afueras norte del Desierto Silencioso. Smenkhare y Sadjet "
"se reunieron con Suryen allí unos días después, habiendo bloqueado "
"decisivamente el avance enemigo en el Camino Celestial."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:257
msgid ""
"Since their massive defeat at Maat'Kare, the Skironians had attempted no "
"further attack by the sea; in fact, they had lost most of their fleet there, "
"and an attack of water elementals summoned by the Academy's best "
"elementalists took care of the remaining ships. Thus, Skiron could no longer "
"transport troops to Netjer-Ta by the sea, which considerably reduced their "
"attack range."
msgstr ""
"Desde su gran derrota en Maat'Kare, los skironianos no habían intentado más "
"ataques por mar; de hecho, habían perdido la mayor parte de su flota allí, y "
"un ataque de elementales de agua convocados por los mejores elementalistas "
"de la Academia se encargó de los barcos restantes. Así, Skiron ya no podía "
"transportar tropas a Netjer-Ta por mar, lo que redujo considerablemente su "
"rango de ataque."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:261
msgid ""
"Notwithstanding, they could still reach Netjer-Ta through portals created in "
"the Silent Desert and through the underground tunnels that connected both "
"continents. Indeed, the Skironians attacked through those tunnels with "
"increasing violence, to the point that Vindalf was forced to request some "
"aid from the wargs, the orcs and the Maat'Karians. Menon answered their call "
"by sending the Myra Battalion, and so Atenak, Akhen and the others plunged "
"into the dark underground caves once more, alongside scores of wargs and "
"orcs..."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, todavía podían llegar a Netjer-Ta a través de portales creados "
"en el Desierto Silencioso y mediante los túneles subterráneos que conectaban "
"ambos continentes. De hecho, los skironianos atacaban a través de esos "
"túneles con violencia creciente, hasta el punto de que Vindalf se vio "
"obligado a pedir ayuda a los huargos, los orcos y los maat'karianos. Menon "
"respondió a su llamada enviando el Batallón Myra, y así Atenak, Akhen y los "
"demás se adentraron una vez más en las oscuras cuevas subterráneas, junto a "
"decenas de huargos y orcos..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:272
msgid ""
"Great was the astonishment of the Motsoghnir when they saw bloodied and "
"exhausted humans and wargs return from the abyss, but not their leader. "
"Nonetheless, Sigdral wasted no time explaining them anything: she rushed "
"back to the surface, and sent an urgent message to Maat'Kare, requesting the "
"mages to use water elementals to rescue Argatyr."
msgstr ""
"Grande fue el asombro de los Motsoghnir cuando vieron regresar del abismo a "
"humanos y huargos ensangrentados y exhaustos, pero no a su líder. Aun así, "
"Sigdral no perdió tiempo explicándoles nada: corrió de vuelta a la "
"superficie y envió un mensaje urgente a Maat'Kare pidiendo a los magos que "
"usaran elementales de agua para rescatar a Argatyr."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:276
msgid ""
"The answer quickly came in the shape of Menon himself. He descended alone to "
"the flooded caves, and returned little later with Argatyr - but there was no "
"celebration, as the dwarf lord was horribly wounded. The Maat'Karian master "
"tended to his wounds, but strongly recommended him to rest. Cloistered in "
"his rooms, allowing none to visit him - Sigdral included -, Argatyr left the "
"command of his warriors to Gomatol."
msgstr ""
"La respuesta llegó rápidamente en forma del propio Menon. Descendió solo a "
"las cuevas inundadas y regresó poco después con Argatyr, pero no hubo "
"celebración, pues el señor enano estaba gravemente herido. El maestro "
"maat'kariano atendió sus heridas, pero le recomendó encarecidamente que "
"descansara. Aislado en sus habitaciones, sin permitir que nadie lo visitara —"
"incluida Sigdral—, Argatyr dejó el mando de sus guerreros a Gomatol."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:280
msgid ""
"Now, the Skironians' only way to Netjer-Ta was the portal at the rebuilt "
"Desret. Thus, the allies prepared the attack that would put an end to their "
"invasion. The orcs were not present; after learning of Argatyr's treachery, "
"they had declared that never again would they march alongside the "
"Motsoghnir. But Romlur's forces met Vindalf's - the Motsoghnir were too worn "
"out after the battle in the underwater caves -, as well as those led by "
"Suryen and Atenak, at the Peaks of Meditation, and then they marched "
"together towards Desret."
msgstr ""
"Ahora, la única forma de los skironianos para llegar a Netjer-Ta era el "
"portal en el reconstruido Desret. Así, los aliados prepararon el ataque que "
"pondría fin a su invasión. Los orcos no estuvieron presentes; tras enterarse "
"de la traición de Argatyr, habían declarado que nunca más marcharían junto a "
"los Motsoghnir. Pero las fuerzas de Romlur se reunieron con las de Vindalf —"
"los Motsoghnir estaban demasiado agotados tras la batalla en las cuevas "
"submarinas— y con las lideradas por Suryen y Atenak en los Picos de la "
"Meditación, y luego marcharían juntos hacia Desret."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:284
msgid ""
"And, at the forefront of the allied armies, stood the Master of Four Lights, "
"Menon the Immortal, resolved to crush Stygia and her hosts with his own "
"hands..."
msgstr ""
"Y, al frente de los ejércitos aliados, se encontraba el Maestro de las "
"Cuatro Luces, Menon el Inmortal, resuelto a aplastar a Stygia y a sus "
"huestes con sus propias manos..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:295
msgid ""
"The Maat'Karian soldiers were exhausted, weakened and wounded, but even so "
"they couldn't help but smile as they crossed the human lands on the way back "
"to the capital: at every town and village they passed by, they were "
"boisterously hailed as heroes, and offered many gifts by the people."
msgstr ""
"Los soldados maat'karianos estaban exhaustos, debilitados y heridos, pero "
"aun así no podían evitar sonreír mientras cruzaban las tierras humanas de "
"camino de vuelta a la capital: en cada pueblo y aldea por la que pasaban, "
"eran aclamados ruidosamente como héroes y recibían muchos regalos por parte "
"de la gente."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:299
msgid ""
"But the greatest celebration awaited them at Maat'Kare itself. The whole "
"city was brimming with joy: children ran through the streets to give a "
"closer look at the soldiers, and the citizens threw laurel branches - a "
"symbol of triumph to the Maat'Karians - to them as they paraded across the "
"city, led by their greatest hero, the Immortal, Menon Hekare."
msgstr ""
"Pero la mayor celebración los esperaba en la propia Maat'Kare. Toda la "
"ciudad rebosaba de alegría: los niños corrían por las calles para ver más de "
"cerca a los soldados, y los ciudadanos les arrojaban ramas de laurel —un "
"símbolo de triunfo para los maat'karianos— mientras desfilaban por la "
"ciudad, liderados por su mayor héroe, el Inmortal, Menon Hekare."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:303
msgid ""
"When they reached the City Heart, Menon climbed on a pulpit and told the "
"citizens of his decision to attack Skiron itself. Not everyone received that "
"news enthusiastically, but most citizens shouted in support of that; after "
"all, Skiron had to pay for what it had done to the peoples of Netjer-Ta."
msgstr ""
"Cuando llegaron al Corazón de la Ciudad, Menon subió a un púlpito y anunció "
"a los ciudadanos su decisión de atacar al propio Skiron. No todos recibieron "
"la noticia con entusiasmo, pero la mayoría de los ciudadanos gritaron en "
"apoyo; después de todo, Skiron tenía que pagar por lo que había hecho a los "
"pueblos de Netjer-Ta."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:307
msgid ""
"However, the counter-attack would only begin after the soldiers recovered. "
"In those days, the City of the Sun celebrated relentlessly; Akhen, Merwe and "
"even the usually somber Mahyus joined the citizens as they partied on the "
"streets and on the public squares. Nyx cloistered herself at Akhen's mansion "
"near Veela's Gardens, to avoid trouble - for the citizens wouldn't take "
"kindly to a vampiress' presence inside their city's walls. Sigdral stayed "
"with her, so that she wouldn't feel lonely, and so did Akhen himself. While "
"Nyx would never admit it, Sigdral knew she was happier in his company than "
"she'd been in a long time."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, el contraataque solo comenzaría después de que los soldados se "
"recuperaran. En esos días, la Ciudad del Sol celebraba sin descanso; Akhen, "
"Merwe e incluso el usualmente sombrío Mahyus se unieron a los ciudadanos "
"mientras festejaban en las calles y plazas públicas. Nyx se encerró en la "
"mansión de Akhen cerca de los Jardines de Veela para evitar problemas, pues "
"los ciudadanos no verían con buenos ojos la presencia de una vampiresa "
"dentro de las murallas de su ciudad. Sigdral se quedó con ella para que no "
"se sintiera sola, y Akhen también. Aunque Nyx nunca lo admitiría, Sigdral "
"sabía que ella estaba más feliz en su compañía de lo que había estado en "
"mucho tiempo."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:311
msgid ""
"Atenak, by her turn, was nowhere to be found in those days. The last of the "
"Myra Battalion to see her was Merwe, who claimed that she looked 'weird', "
"though she had no idea why."
msgstr ""
"Atenak, por su parte, no aparecía por ningún lado en esos días. La última "
"del Batallón Myra en verla fue Merwe, quien dijo que se veía «rara», aunque "
"no tenía idea de por qué."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:315
msgid ""
"And then, a week and a half after the army's return, Tewarin surprised "
"everybody by handing to the Chamber of Sages a petition, signed by eighteen "
"other Lords, to strip Menon of his powers as Great Seer. Such a request, "
"signed by so many Lords, couldn't be ignored; and so a new council was held, "
"and not only the Lords and the Sages, but Sigdral as well, were summoned to "
"it..."
msgstr ""
"Y entonces, una semana y media después del regreso del ejército, Tewarin "
"sorprendió a todos al entregar a la Cámara de los Sabios una petición "
"firmada por otros dieciocho Señores para despojar a Menon de sus poderes "
"como Gran Vidente. Una solicitud firmada por tantos Señores no podía ser "
"ignorada; así que se celebró un nuevo consejo, al que fueron convocados no "
"solo los Señores y los Sabios, sino también Sigdral..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:326
msgid ""
"Akhen felt like in a dream of the worst kind as he sneaked out of the "
"Academy and into the woods surrounding it: when the sun had risen that very "
"same day, he had woken up thinking about a party his old classmates would be "
"throwing at someone else's house; now, he was fleeing his own city, "
"stumbling on the debris of his crumbling world..."
msgstr ""
"Akhen se sentía como en una pesadilla mientras salía a escondidas de la "
"Academia hacia los bosques que la rodeaban: cuando el sol había salido ese "
"mismo día, se había despertado pensando en una fiesta que sus antiguos "
"compañeros darían en la casa de alguien; ahora estaba huyendo de su propia "
"ciudad, tropezando entre los escombros de su mundo derrumbándose..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:329
msgid ""
"And yet his mind was incredibly clear, much to his own surprise. Since the "
"city was crowded with night-guards, he decided to reach the Aracynes' Manor "
"by the sea. As it had with his ancestor, the Trident facilitated the "
"crossing of water bodies, and so he and his friends reached their "
"destination fast and silently. Afterwards they managed to sneak into the "
"manor and take Atenak - who had to believe Akhen's promise of being told "
"everything later - and then they went for the Wadjet's mansion, where they "
"picked the equally puzzled Nyx and Sigdral."
msgstr ""
"Y sin embargo su mente estaba increíblemente clara, para su propia sorpresa. "
"Como la ciudad estaba llena de guardias nocturnos, decidió llegar a la "
"Mansión de los Aracynes junto al mar. Al igual que con su ancestro, el "
"Tridente facilitaba el cruce de cuerpos de agua, por lo que él y sus amigos "
"llegaron a su destino rápida y silenciosamente. Después lograron entrar a "
"escondidas en la mansión y sacar a Atenak —quien tuvo que creer en la "
"promesa de Akhen de que le contarían todo más tarde— y luego fueron a la "
"mansión de los Wadjet, donde recogieron a la igualmente desconcertada Nyx y "
"a Sigdral."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:332
msgid ""
"Next, they entered an underground tunnel which, according to Akhen, had been "
"built by an eccentric ancestor of his as a secret escape out of the Land's "
"End Peninsula. As Mahyus' undead carried them along the way, Akhen finally "
"explained everything. And he did speak in those long, tense hours, as he "
"explained what he had heard from Menon's own mouth. His stunned friends, to "
"make things easier for him, shared his belief that all of the Master's "
"actions were influenced by the Sky Soul."
msgstr ""
"Luego entraron en un túnel subterráneo que, según Akhen, había sido "
"construido por un excéntrico ancestro suyo como una vía de escape secreta "
"fuera de la península de Land's End. Mientras los no muertos de Mahyus los "
"transportaban por el camino, Akhen finalmente lo explicó todo. Y habló "
"durante esas largas y tensas horas, explicando lo que había escuchado de la "
"propia boca de Menon. Sus amigos, atónitos, para facilitarle las cosas, "
"compartieron su creencia de que todas las acciones del Maestro estaban "
"influenciadas por el Alma del Cielo."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:335
msgid ""
"He didn't tell anything about his contact with Myra though, for he himself "
"barely understood what it actually meant. He still had trouble believing "
"that was really his ancestor; and, to make things worse, the Orb itself "
"didn't speak to him even as the group travelled towards the Cyan Mountains, "
"ever watchful of Maat'Karian outposts."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, no contó nada sobre su contacto con Myra, porque él mismo "
"apenas entendía qué significaba realmente. Todavía le costaba creer que "
"fuera realmente su ancestro; y para empeorar las cosas, el Orbe mismo no le "
"hablaba ni siquiera mientras el grupo viajaba hacia las Montañas Cyan, "
"siempre atentos a los puestos avanzados maat'karianos."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:338
msgid ""
"Two weeks after leaving Maat'Kare, they finally sighted the Indigo "
"Pinnacles, which marked the Aigathol's northern frontiers. Exhausted and "
"tense as they were, they felt heartened by the thought of standing on "
"friendly territory, and Sigdral wasted no time unlocking the Mountain Gates "
"for them. However, as they plunged once again in the darkness, they soon "
"noticed something terribly wrong in the Aigathol's caves..."
msgstr ""
"Dos semanas después de dejar Maat'Kare, finalmente avistaron los Pináculos "
"Índigo, que marcaban las fronteras norte de Aigathol. Exhaustos y tensos "
"como estaban, se sintieron animados ante la idea de estar en territorio "
"amigo, y Sigdral no perdió tiempo en abrirles las Puertas de la Montaña. Sin "
"embargo, al adentrarse de nuevo en la oscuridad, pronto notaron que algo "
"andaba terriblemente mal en las cuevas de Aigathol..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:348
msgid ""
"It was with a heavy heart that the friends left the Aigathol's caves - the "
"ones that were still under their control, that is. Atenak promised to help "
"Sigdral as much as she could as one of the rebel leaders, but that didn't "
"help Akhen wave aside the feeling that they were leaving their dwarf friend "
"in the monster's jaws."
msgstr ""
"Fue con el corazón pesado que los amigos dejaron las cuevas de Aigathol —las "
"que todavía estaban bajo su control, claro—. Atenak prometió ayudar a "
"Sigdral todo lo que pudiera como una de las líderes rebeldes, pero eso no "
"ayudó a Akhen a quitarse la sensación de que estaban dejando a su amiga "
"enana en las fauces del monstruo."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:351
msgid ""
"Nevertheless, the only thing he could do at the moment was to reach the "
"Windsong as soon as possible and bring the Order to their side. So, he and "
"the others made haste towards the city of Ineb-Hedj in the Windswept Cliffs "
"– the stronghold of the rebels -; guided across the ever-dangerous vampire "
"mountains by Nyx, they reached their destination in less than a week."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, lo único que podía hacer en ese momento era llegar a las Hijas "
"del Viento lo antes posible y llevar a la Orden a su lado. Así que él y los "
"demás se apresuraron hacia la ciudad de Ineb-Hedj en los Acantilados "
"Barridos por el Viento —el bastión de los rebeldes—. Guiados por Nyx a "
"través de las siempre peligrosas montañas vampiras, llegaron a su destino en "
"menos de una semana."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:354
msgid ""
"Once at Ineb-Hedj, Smenkhare and the other Lords cheerfully received Atenak, "
"whom they had thought lost, and also Akhen, whom - he knew that - they saw "
"as an important symbol to attract the support of more Maat'Karians. "
"Notwithstanding, they understood and accepted the plan of searching for the "
"Windsong, and even prepared provisions and a crew for him and his "
"companions. Atenak, now the sole heiress of the sea-faring Mewates family, "
"easily arranged a ship for them. Thus, two days after their arrival at Ineb-"
"Hedj, Akhen, Merwe, Mahyus and Nyx were ready to depart..."
msgstr ""
"Una vez en Ineb-Hedj, Smenkhare y los otros Señores recibieron alegremente a "
"Atenak, a quien creían perdida, y también a Akhen, a quien —él lo sabía— "
"veían como un símbolo importante para atraer el apoyo de más maat'karianos. "
"Sin embargo, entendieron y aceptaron el plan de buscar a las Hijas del "
"Viento, y hasta prepararon provisiones y una tripulación para él y sus "
"compañeros. Atenak, ahora la única heredera de la familia Mewates, "
"navegantes del mar, les consiguió fácilmente un barco. Así, dos días después "
"de su llegada a Ineb-Hedj, Akhen, Merwe, Mahyus y Nyx estaban listos para "
"partir..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:364
msgid ""
"And thus the four friends, hailed and cheered by the people of Ineb-Hedj, "
"embarked on their small, but sturdy ship and set for the northern horizons, "
"with the hopes of their friends, their people and of all the Aigathol upon "
"their shoulders."
msgstr ""
"Y así los cuatro amigos, aclamados y vitoreados por la gente de Ineb-Hedj, "
"embarcaron en su pequeño pero resistente barco y se dirigieron hacia los "
"horizontes del norte, con las esperanzas de sus amigos, su pueblo y de todo "
"Aigathol sobre sus hombros."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:368
msgid ""
"At first they followed the coastline of north-eastern Netjer-Ta, but, in "
"order to avoid being sighted by vampires - whose bats could tear the sails "
"and whose gargoyles could smash into the hull - the helmsman soon drove the "
"ship to the mysterious deep seas. As they entered waters that no Maat'Karian "
"vessel had sailed since Aldrik's time, they felt the winds get increasingly "
"colder, even though the sun seemed to shine for longer hours. Nearly fours "
"weeks after their departure they saw the first blocks of ice floating adrift "
"on the surrounding waters."
msgstr ""
"Al principio siguieron la costa del noreste de Netjer-Ta, pero para evitar "
"ser avistados por vampiros —cuyos murciélagos podían destrozar las velas y "
"cuyas gárgolas podían estrellarse contra el casco— el timonel pronto dirigió "
"el barco hacia los misteriosos mares profundos. Al entrar en aguas que "
"ningún barco maat'kariano había navegado desde la época de Aldrik, sintieron "
"que los vientos se volvían cada vez más fríos, aunque el sol parecía brillar "
"durante más horas. Casi cuatro semanas después de su partida vieron los "
"primeros bloques de hielo flotando a la deriva en las aguas circundantes."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:372
msgid ""
"And then, few days later, they finally spotted land. As the helmsman "
"skilfully manoeuvred amidst ice blocks, the full landscape of the Blue Realm "
"unravelled before those Maat'Karian eyes that were so used to sunny meadows "
"and deserts: plains, hills, valleys and mountains, all completely covered in "
"ice. When the ship finally docked, Akhen was the first to step out of the "
"ship; he gazed across that frozen world, and his resolve strengthened as he "
"thought that he was now much closer to those who could save his homeland and "
"his master - or so he believed..."
msgstr ""
"Y entonces, pocos días después, finalmente avistaron tierra. Mientras el "
"timonel maniobraba hábilmente entre los bloques de hielo, todo el paisaje "
"del Reino Azul se desplegó ante aquellos ojos maat'karianos tan "
"acostumbrados a praderas soleadas y desiertos: llanuras, colinas, valles y "
"montañas, todo completamente cubierto de hielo. Cuando el barco finalmente "
"atracó, Akhen fue el primero en bajar; contempló aquel mundo congelado y su "
"determinación se fortaleció al pensar que ahora estaba mucho más cerca de "
"aquellos que podrían salvar su patria y a su maestro... o eso creía."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:377
msgid "Part V: Across the Seas"
msgstr "Parte V: A Través de los Mares"

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:387
msgid ""
"Thus, leaving their ship anchored in the frozen southern shores, the "
"Maat'Karians followed Yukia towards Hiera'Kyria. As they went further north, "
"the cold worsened almost exponentially, and, though the weather became "
"clearer, the sun was no aid, for it remained as if frozen just above the "
"horizon. This, alongside the otherworldly and magnificent dancing skylights, "
"made the Blue Realm as alien an environment as the Maat'Karians could have "
"expected to find."
msgstr ""
"Así, dejando su barco anclado en las costas congeladas del sur, los "
"maat'karianos siguieron a Yukia hacia Hiera'Kyria. A medida que avanzaban "
"más al norte, el frío empeoraba casi exponencialmente y, aunque el clima se "
"volvía más claro, el sol no ayudaba, pues permanecía como congelado justo "
"encima del horizonte. Esto, junto con las magníficas y etéreas luces del "
"cielo danzantes, hacía del Reino Azul un entorno tan extraño como los "
"maat'karianos podían haber esperado."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:391
msgid ""
"After the initial hostility, Yukia proved to be quite a nice company. She "
"often made everyone laugh with jokes about Nyx, who retorted in kind. Akhen, "
"however, remained sullen, aloof and reflexive. Merwe was increasingly "
"worried about him; after all, she'd never seen him like that before, and "
"nothing she said seemed to cheer him up. She had already accepted that Akhen "
"would never feel anything for her but a great friendship, but she still felt "
"hurt when she saw him smiling only to what Nyx said."
msgstr ""
"Después de la hostilidad inicial, Yukia resultó ser una compañía bastante "
"agradable. A menudo hacía reír a todos con bromas sobre Nyx, quien respondía "
"de la misma manera. Akhen, sin embargo, permanecía sombrío, distante y "
"reflexivo. Merwe estaba cada vez más preocupada por él; después de todo, "
"nunca lo había visto así, y nada de lo que decía parecía animarlo. Ya había "
"aceptado que Akhen nunca sentiría por ella más que una gran amistad, pero "
"aún le dolía verlo sonreír solo por lo que decía Nyx."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:395
msgid ""
"After a week journeying northwards, they finally sighted the great Windsong "
"Foundation, its white fortifications shining in the eerie sunset light like "
"ice walls; but what truly called the Maat'Karians' attention was a large "
"greenish stain on the other side of Hiera'Kyria..."
msgstr ""
"Después de una semana viajando hacia el norte, finalmente avistaron la gran "
"Fundación de las Hijas del Viento, con sus fortificaciones blancas brillando "
"como muros de hielo bajo la extraña luz del atardecer; pero lo que realmente "
"llamó la atención de los maat'karianos fue una gran mancha verdosa al otro "
"lado de Hiera'Kyria..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:405
msgid ""
"So you've finally decided to show yourself up again... I really didn’t miss "
"you, you know."
msgstr ""
"Así que finalmente decidiste aparecer de nuevo... La verdad es que no te "
"extrañé, sabes."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:409 War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:417
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:425 War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:433
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:441 War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:449
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:457 War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:468
msgid "Myra"
msgstr "Myra"

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:409
msgid ""
"Don't be so caustic, grandson. I had my reasons not to speak to you before; "
"I just wanted to see how you fared on your own, for I didn't want to "
"accustom you to being aided at every turn. And besides, Akhen, I wasn't even "
"supposed to be here, influencing the affairs of the living world; to all "
"effects, I'm a dead person."
msgstr ""
"No seas tan cáustico, nieto. Tenía mis razones para no hablarte antes; solo "
"quería ver cómo te las arreglabas solo, porque no quería acostumbrarte a que "
"te ayudaran en todo momento. Además, Akhen, ni siquiera se suponía que "
"estuviera aquí, influyendo en los asuntos del mundo de los vivos; a todos "
"los efectos, soy una persona muerta."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:413
msgid ""
"Then why did you help me escape the Academy? Why didn't you leave me to rot "
"there? Frankly, I hate how you grown-ups say things and then do exactly the "
"opposite..."
msgstr ""
"Entonces ¿por qué me ayudaste a escapar de la Academia? ¿Por qué no me "
"dejaste podrirme allí? Francamente, odio cómo ustedes los adultos dicen una "
"cosa y luego hacen exactamente lo contrario..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:417
msgid ""
"Well, apologies for my hypocrisy, I just couldn't simply leave my grandson "
"in a situation he couldn't have solved himself. I’m a mother, I simply don't "
"know how not to help those I love."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, disculpas por mi hipocresía, simplemente no podía dejar a mi nieto en "
"una situación que no podía resolver por sí mismo. Soy madre, simplemente no "
"sé cómo no ayudar a quienes amo."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:421
msgid "Tsc... Sorry, I didn't mean to offend..."
msgstr "Tsc... Lo siento, no quise ofender..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:425
msgid ""
"No, you must vent your anger as much as you can - and it's better that you "
"do that on me than on your friends, who are the last ones to blame for "
"anything. You see, Akhen, I felt much like you when my mother Maat died, but "
"I kept my feelings to myself; at certain point, I couldn't stand it anymore, "
"and I ended up doing something extremely irresponsible - something you must "
"know as the Ughure Incident. Now, please just don’t you ever think that I'll "
"ever abandon you, right?"
msgstr ""
"No, debes desahogar tu enojo todo lo que puedas, y es mejor que lo hagas "
"conmigo que con tus amigos, que son los últimos culpables de nada. Verás, "
"Akhen, yo me sentí muy como tú cuando murió mi madre Maat, pero guardé mis "
"sentimientos para mí; en cierto momento ya no pude soportarlo más y terminé "
"haciendo algo extremadamente irresponsable, algo que debes conocer como el "
"Incidente Ughure. Ahora, por favor, nunca pienses que te voy a abandonar, "
"¿de acuerdo?"

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:429
msgid "Well, thanks for that..."
msgstr "Bueno, gracias por eso..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:433
msgid ""
"(cheerful) That's the grandson I know and love, now with a spoonful of "
"grumpiness! Now, I'm sure you have a lot of questions to bombard me with, "
"don't you?"
msgstr ""
"(alegre) ¡Ese es el nieto que conozco y amo, ahora con una cucharada de "
"malhumor! Ahora, estoy segura de que tienes muchas preguntas para "
"bombardearme, ¿verdad?"

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:437
msgid ""
"I do have some. First of all, what exactly are you? I mean, I know you're "
"Myra, but are you a ghost, a projection or what?"
msgstr ""
"Sí tengo algunas. Primero que nada, ¿qué eres exactamente? Quiero decir, sé "
"que eres Myra, pero ¿eres un fantasma, una proyección o qué?"

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:441
msgid ""
"I myself had no answer to that, at first; I exploded in the fight against "
"Svarballi, and felt my soul slowly vanish... But then I felt myself amidst "
"those same spirits whom I was so familiar with: the spirits of Nature. It "
"was only when I failed to sense Nitiballi's presence that I understood "
"everything: he’d taken the brunt of the damage inflicted on me by the "
"explosion, saving my spirit at the expense of his own; and that my spirit "
"had remained on the living plane by its connection to Nature, just like "
"Nitiballi's had after he sacrificed himself to create the Fountain of Life."
msgstr ""
"Yo misma no tenía respuesta para eso al principio; exploté en la lucha "
"contra Svarballi y sentí que mi alma se desvanecía lentamente... Pero luego "
"me sentí entre esos mismos espíritus con los que estaba tan familiarizada: "
"los espíritus de la Naturaleza. Solo cuando no pude sentir la presencia de "
"Nitiballi entendí todo: él había recibido la mayor parte del daño que me "
"infligió la explosión, salvando mi espíritu a costa del suyo; y que mi "
"espíritu había permanecido en el plano de los vivos por su conexión con la "
"Naturaleza, igual que le había pasado a Nitiballi después de sacrificarse "
"para crear la Fuente de la Vida."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:445
msgid ""
"And your spirit remained connected to the Trident just as Nitiballi's did "
"before you, right?"
msgstr ""
"Y tu espíritu permaneció conectado al Tridente igual que el de Nitiballi "
"antes que tú, ¿verdad?"

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:449
msgid ""
"Not exactly; Nitiballi wasn't an existence dependant on the Trident, he "
"simply fed on its energy in order to strengthen his presence on this plane, "
"and I'm the same as him. That's why I never remain away from it for long."
msgstr ""
"No exactamente; Nitiballi no era una existencia dependiente del Tridente, "
"simplemente se alimentaba de su energía para fortalecer su presencia en este "
"plano, y yo soy igual que él. Por eso nunca me alejo de él por mucho tiempo."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:453
msgid ""
"I think I get it... I have just one more question: when you wielded the Sky "
"Soul, you were influenced by its malice, wasn't you? How did you manage to "
"break it?"
msgstr ""
"Creo que entiendo... Solo tengo una pregunta más: cuando empuñaste el Alma "
"del Cielo, fuiste influenciada por su maldad, ¿verdad? ¿Cómo lograste "
"romperla?"

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:457
msgid ""
"You want to know how you may free Menon from the Sky Dragon's influence, "
"don't you? Akhen, I haven't watched Menon closely; I could have, but he kept "
"the Trident safely away from him. Thus, I can't assess his state of mind... "
"but I'm afraid that, after coexisting with the Soul for so long, he may be "
"beyond any salvation."
msgstr ""
"Quieres saber cómo puedes liberar a Menon de la influencia del Dragón del "
"Cielo, ¿no es así? Akhen, no he observado a Menon de cerca; podría haberlo "
"hecho, pero él mantuvo el Tridente bien lejos de sí. Por lo tanto, no puedo "
"evaluar su estado mental... pero me temo que, después de convivir tanto "
"tiempo con el Alma, puede estar más allá de toda salvación."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:461
msgid "(silence)"
msgstr "(silencio)"

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:464
msgid ""
"Well, as you have said yourself, you can't be certain about anything "
"concerning him. Thanks once again for helping me, grandma, and don't worry, "
"for I promise you that I will stop the Sky Dragon's schemes just as you've "
"once done."
msgstr ""
"Bueno, como tú misma dijiste, no puedes estar segura de nada respecto a él. "
"Gracias una vez más por ayudarme, abuela, y no te preocupes, porque te "
"prometo que detendré los planes del Dragón del Cielo tal como tú lo hiciste "
"una vez."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:468
msgid ""
"I wish you good luck then, Akhen - and never forget that you may always "
"count on me..."
msgstr ""
"Entonces te deseo buena suerte, Akhen, y nunca olvides que siempre puedes "
"contar conmigo..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:472
msgid ""
"Such was the dialogue Akhen had on the prow of the ship as it sailed away "
"from the Blue Realm. Myra's words reverberated in his mind, from her "
"explanation regarding the spirits of Irdya to her thoughts on Menon... "
"Unwilling to keep musing on that subject, he decided to practice the "
"summoning of true elementals again."
msgstr ""
"Ese fue el diálogo que Akhen tuvo en la proa del barco mientras se alejaba "
"del Reino Azul. Las palabras de Myra resonaban en su mente, desde su "
"explicación sobre los espíritus de Irdya hasta sus pensamientos sobre "
"Menon... Poco dispuesto a seguir reflexionando sobre ese tema, decidió "
"practicar nuevamente la invocación de elementales verdaderos."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:475
msgid ""
"But the ship's journey was not to be peaceful. As the vessel sailed farthest "
"away from dry land than it had till then; it was caught by a sea storm "
"stirred by mighty westerly winds which pushed the ship increasingly "
"eastwards - to Morogor."
msgstr ""
"Pero el viaje del barco no iba a ser tranquilo. Cuando la nave se había "
"alejado más de tierra firme que nunca, fue atrapada por una tormenta marina "
"provocada por fuertes vientos del oeste que empujaban el barco cada vez más "
"hacia el este, hacia Morogor."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:478
msgid ""
"Everyone strived hard against the raging seas and the freezing wind, to no "
"avail. Akhen – who could not master the Trident to the point of controlling "
"the weather – tried to use Tidals to push the ship away from the east, but "
"he still didn’t have full control over them: the water elementals ran "
"berserk, lunging against the ship's hull more violently than even the ocean "
"waves, cracking it open..."
msgstr ""
"Todos lucharon con fuerza contra los mares enfurecidos y el viento helado, "
"sin éxito. Akhen —quien no dominaba el Tridente lo suficiente como para "
"controlar el clima— intentó usar mareas para empujar el barco lejos del "
"este, pero todavía no tenía control total sobre ellas: los elementales de "
"agua enloquecieron, lanzándose contra el casco del barco con más violencia "
"que las propias olas del océano, abriéndolo..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:481
msgid ""
"In the ensuing mayhem, Akhen could only see the seamen hurriedly picking the "
"tiny reserve boats before another colossal wave hit the ship, knocking many "
"of its crew off it. Akhen was amongst those poor souls; as he sank slowly "
"into the ocean, dragged downwards by the weight of the Trident, he thought "
"on how ironic it was, to be killed by the very sea he was supposed to tame..."
msgstr ""
"En el caos que siguió, Akhen solo pudo ver a los marineros tomando "
"apresuradamente los pequeños botes de reserva antes de que otra ola colosal "
"golpeara el barco, lanzando a muchos de su tripulación por la borda. Akhen "
"estaba entre esas pobres almas; mientras se hundía lentamente en el océano, "
"arrastrado hacia abajo por el peso del Tridente, pensó en lo irónico que era "
"morir por el mismo mar que se suponía que debía dominar..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:484
msgid ""
"But then he felt a powerful hand dragging him upwards, and the wind blew his "
"face again. Too weakened to fight against the elements any more, he let "
"himself be dragged by that strong saviour..."
msgstr ""
"Pero entonces sintió una mano poderosa que lo arrastraba hacia arriba, y el "
"viento volvió a golpear su rostro. Demasiado debilitado para seguir luchando "
"contra los elementos, se dejó arrastrar por aquel fuerte salvador..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:487
msgid ""
"When he next came to his senses, he felt solid ground beneath him, and a "
"soft pile of what smelled like grass beneath his head. As he opened his "
"eyes, he was met by a beautiful pair of almond green eyes and a mischievous "
"smile..."
msgstr ""
"Cuando recuperó el sentido, sintió tierra firme bajo él y una suave pila de "
"algo que olía a hierba bajo su cabeza. Al abrir los ojos, se encontró con un "
"hermoso par de ojos verde almendra y una sonrisa traviesa..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:498
msgid ""
"The people of Rockvale did receive the foreigners quite enthusiastically. As "
"Branwyn told them in her strangely rhythmic intonation, the Aeserians were "
"usually very warm towards any foreigner that arrived on their towns. Still, "
"Akhen couldn't avoid feeling embarrassed as everyone stared at him with a "
"mix of amazement and curiosity."
msgstr ""
"La gente de Rockvale recibió a los extranjeros con bastante entusiasmo. Como "
"les contó Branwyn con su extraña entonación rítmica, los aeserianos solían "
"ser muy amables con cualquier extranjero que llegaba a sus pueblos. Aun así, "
"Akhen no podía evitar sentirse avergonzado mientras todos lo miraban con una "
"mezcla de asombro y curiosidad."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:502
msgid ""
"Afallon received the foreigners at his hut – the amplest in town, but still "
"a humble abode next to a Maat'Karian home. He told them more about his "
"people and home: the Aeserians had inhabited that island for ten generations "
"already, having come, according to their tradition, from a land far to the "
"west, uprooted by beasts known as 'orcs'. Both Akhen and Nyx were very "
"surprised by the revelation, and told the elder about their own homeland; "
"certainly, they pondered, the Aeserians were one of the barbarian tribes "
"said to neighbour Skiron in Argea - tribes who traced their lineage back to "
"the Maat'Karians' own ancestors."
msgstr ""
"Afallon recibió a los extranjeros en su cabaña —la más amplia del pueblo, "
"pero aun así una humilde morada al lado de una casa maat'kariana—. Les contó "
"más sobre su pueblo y su hogar: los aeserianos habían habitado esa isla "
"durante diez generaciones, habiendo venido, según su tradición, de una "
"tierra muy al oeste, desplazados por bestias conocidas como «orcos». Tanto "
"Akhen como Nyx se sorprendieron mucho con la revelación y le contaron al "
"anciano sobre su propia patria; ciertamente, pensaron, los aeserianos eran "
"una de las tribus bárbaras que se decía que limitaban con Skiron en Argea, "
"tribus que remontaban su linaje a los propios ancestros de los maat'karianos."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:506
msgid ""
"Afterwards, Akhen explained about the shipwreck, and that he needed to find "
"his companions. Afallon promised to stir the neighbouring Aeserian towns to "
"help him in the search, and even to place some men and women under his "
"command. Akhen himself sent razorbirds scouting the region."
msgstr ""
"Después, Akhen explicó lo del naufragio y que necesitaba encontrar a sus "
"compañeros. Afallon prometió movilizar a los pueblos aeserianos vecinos para "
"ayudarlo en la búsqueda, e incluso poner a algunos hombres y mujeres bajo su "
"mando. El propio Akhen envió aves navaja a explorar la región."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:510
msgid ""
"Four days later, one of the razorbirds returned; through mind link – a "
"technique which allowed summoner and elemental to communicate – Akhen saw a "
"dreadful scene: wildfire and smoke clouds, and towering horned creatures "
"flying above the remains of a Maat'Karian ship..."
msgstr ""
"Cuatro días después, una de las aves navaja regresó; a través del enlace "
"mental —una técnica que permitía al invocador comunicarse con el elemental— "
"Akhen vio una escena terrible: incendios forestales y nubes de humo, y "
"enormes criaturas con cuernos volando sobre los restos de un barco "
"maat'kariano..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:514
msgid ""
"Akhen wasted no time: he told Afallon to warn as many Aeserian towns as he "
"could that a terrible threat was looming, and then he immediately left "
"Rockvale, led eastwards by Branwyn; for the Green Isle was about to "
"experience the same terror that had uprooted the Maat'Karians' forefathers "
"from the Old Home..."
msgstr ""
"Akhen no perdió tiempo: le dijo a Afallon que alertara a todas las ciudades "
"aeserianas que pudiera de que una terrible amenaza se acercaba, y luego "
"partió inmediatamente de Rockvale, guiado hacia el este por Branwyn; porque "
"la Isla Verde estaba a punto de sufrir el mismo terror que había expulsado a "
"los antepasados de los maat'karianos de su Antiguo Hogar..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:525
msgid ""
"And the Aeserians wasted no time in preparing for the drake attack: "
"messengers sent by Afallon swiftly reached even the remotest Aeserian towns "
"and also the Chomi colonies in the southern Green Isle; and, three days "
"after the battle near Forstsea, nearly all chiefs in the island were "
"gathered at the Chomi-Aeserian town of Southbay."
msgstr ""
"Y los aeserianos no perdieron tiempo en prepararse para el ataque de los "
"dracos: los mensajeros enviados por Afallon llegaron rápidamente incluso a "
"las ciudades aeserianas más remotas y también a las colonias chomi en el sur "
"de la Isla Verde; y, tres días después de la batalla cerca de Forstsea, casi "
"todos los jefes de la isla se reunieron en la ciudad chomi-aeseriana de "
"Southbay."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:529
msgid ""
"At the meeting, Afallon introduced Akhen as a 'seer from the distant west', "
"and then let him explain about the threat of the drakes. To his relief, "
"everyone trusted his words – as he later knew, the support of the widely-"
"respected Afallon was crucial – and started discussing strategies to counter "
"that invasion."
msgstr ""
"En la reunión, Afallon presentó a Akhen como un «vidente del lejano oeste», "
"y luego le permitió explicar la amenaza de los dracos. Para su alivio, todos "
"confiaron en sus palabras —como supo después, el apoyo del muy respetado "
"Afallon fue crucial— y comenzaron a discutir estrategias para contrarrestar "
"esa invasión."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:533
msgid ""
"Counselled by the Maat'Karians, who knew the drakes' weaknesses better, the "
"allies decided to concentrate their defences on swampy and forested areas. "
"In the following day, as battalions from all corners of the island travelled "
"to its eastern regions, another drake troop attacked, razing an entire town. "
"The few survivors who made it to friendly haven described a gargantuan "
"winged creature who could crush ten men with a single blow, and who spit "
"hell from its mouth. Akhen, Merwe and Mahyus all agreed that that had to be "
"the dragon Vritras."
msgstr ""
"Aconsejados por los maat'karianos, que conocían mejor las debilidades de los "
"dracos, los aliados decidieron concentrar sus defensas en zonas pantanosas y "
"boscosas. Al día siguiente, mientras batallones de todos los rincones de la "
"isla se dirigían a sus regiones orientales, otra tropa de dracos atacó, "
"arrasando una ciudad entera. Los pocos sobrevivientes que llegaron a un "
"refugio amigo describieron una criatura alada gigantesca que podía aplastar "
"a diez hombres de un solo golpe y que escupía infierno por su boca. Akhen, "
"Merwe y Mahyus coincidieron en que esa debía ser el dragón Vritras."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:537
msgid ""
"Another drake attack managed to lay waste to many tiny villages, but was "
"stopped at a swamp by Chomi and Aeserian fighters, who also managed to win "
"against other smaller drake battalions. However, when the attackers "
"organized a massive attack on one of their opponents’ key defences, the "
"natives had to call for the aid of the ‘seer’ and his friends, and so the "
"Maat’Karians hurried to the Stone of Destiny, a huge mountain full of "
"natural underground tunnels..."
msgstr ""
"Otro ataque de dracos logró destruir muchos pueblos pequeños, pero fue "
"detenido en un pantano por combatientes chomi y aeserianos, quienes también "
"vencieron a otros batallones más pequeños de dracos. Sin embargo, cuando los "
"atacantes organizaron un ataque masivo contra una de las defensas clave de "
"sus oponentes, los nativos tuvieron que pedir ayuda al «vidente» y a sus "
"amigos, por lo que los maat'karianos se apresuraron hacia la Piedra del "
"Destino, una enorme montaña llena de túneles subterráneos naturales..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:548
msgid ""
"The successful defence of the Stone of Destiny proved to be a huge morale "
"boost to the defenders, and a blow to the enemy confidence as well – as "
"noted by the decrease in the ferocity of their assaults."
msgstr ""
"La exitosa defensa de la Piedra del Destino resultó ser un gran impulso para "
"la moral de los defensores y también un golpe a la confianza del enemigo, "
"como se notó por la disminución en la ferocidad de sus ataques."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:552
msgid ""
"Nevertheless, the drakes now had a trump card. In the meeting at Rockvale, "
"as the leaders were discussing a way to reach the main enemy camp, a drake "
"messenger appeared, bringing a message from Vitras himself. As Merwe had "
"foreseen, the enemy commander demanded that Mahyus refrained from fighting "
"in exchange for Branwyn's survival. To everyone's surprise, Mahyus promised "
"that nobody would see him on the battlefield anymore; his friends, however, "
"knew that there was more to his words than it might have seemed."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, los dracos ahora tenían una carta bajo la manga. En la reunión "
"en Rockvale, mientras los líderes discutían cómo llegar al campamento "
"principal enemigo, apareció un mensajero draco con un mensaje del propio "
"Vitras. Como Merwe había previsto, el comandante enemigo exigía que Mahyus "
"se abstuviera de luchar a cambio de la supervivencia de Branwyn. Para "
"sorpresa de todos, Mahyus prometió que nadie lo vería más en el campo de "
"batalla; sus amigos, sin embargo, sabían que había más detrás de sus "
"palabras de lo que parecía."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:556
msgid ""
"In the following days, the Aeserians, the Chomi and the Maat'Karians "
"succeeded in retaking many regions, albeit at the cost of many losses. The "
"allies attacked from three main fronts: the north-western one led by Afallon "
"himself, the south-western one composed of Chomi and Aeserian troops; and "
"the western one, which counted with Akhen and scores of Aeserian and Chomi "
"warriors put under his command."
msgstr ""
"En los días siguientes, los aeserianos, los chomi y los maat'karianos "
"lograron reconquistar muchas regiones, aunque a costa de muchas pérdidas. "
"Los aliados atacaron desde tres frentes principales: el noroccidental "
"liderado por el propio Afallon, el suroccidental compuesto por tropas chomi "
"y aeserianas, y el occidental, que contaba con Akhen y decenas de guerreros "
"aeserianos y chomi bajo su mando."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:560
msgid ""
"And, even though Mahyus was no longer fighting, 'the Seer's' offensive was "
"the one that reached the main drake base first. Hidden in a thick forest "
"amidst a ring of hills, the Maat'Karians delayed their attack on the base "
"for some time, in order to give their allies time to get nearer, but they "
"couldn't remain unseen by drake scouts' keen sight for long..."
msgstr ""
"Y aunque Mahyus ya no luchaba, la ofensiva del «Vidente» fue la que llegó "
"primero al campamento principal de los dracos. Ocultos en un bosque denso "
"entre un anillo de colinas, los maat'karianos retrasaron su ataque al "
"campamento por un tiempo para darles a sus aliados oportunidad de acercarse, "
"pero no pudieron permanecer ocultos de la aguda vista de los exploradores "
"dracos por mucho tiempo..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:571
msgid ""
"Thus, after triumphing in that unexpected war, Akhen and his group left the "
"Green Isle. As he waved the last farewell to Afallon and Adapa from the "
"slender Chomi vessel's prow, he reflected on the aftermath of that campaign: "
"he hadn't managed to find strong allies there – though the Aeserians who'd "
"fought under him had decided to keep following him – but he'd managed to "
"greatly develop his elemental-summoning powers. Still, the greatest winner "
"was really Mahyus, who now spent most of his time happily at the beck and "
"call of the Aeserian bard, much to her own amusement."
msgstr ""
"Así, después de triunfar en esa guerra inesperada, Akhen y su grupo dejaron "
"la Isla Verde. Mientras decía su último adiós a Afallon y Adapa desde la "
"proa del esbelto barco chomi, reflexionó sobre las consecuencias de esa "
"campaña: no había logrado encontrar aliados fuertes allí —aunque los "
"aeserianos que habían luchado bajo su mando decidieron seguirlo—, pero había "
"logrado desarrollar mucho sus poderes de invocación de elementales. Aun así, "
"el mayor ganador fue realmente Mahyus, quien ahora pasaba la mayor parte de "
"su tiempo felizmente a disposición de la barda aeseriana, para gran "
"diversión de ella."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:575
msgid ""
"The seas to the south of the Green Isle were even more violent than those to "
"the north, but the skilled Chomi were used to sailing those waters, and so "
"their ship made the cross without a single loss of life. On the other hand, "
"the strong currents blew the vessel off course, taking it to an unexpected "
"region..."
msgstr ""
"Los mares al sur de la Isla Verde eran aún más violentos que los del norte, "
"pero los hábiles chomi estaban acostumbrados a navegar esas aguas, por lo "
"que su barco cruzó sin perder una sola vida. Por otro lado, las fuertes "
"corrientes desviaron el barco de su rumbo, llevándolo a una región "
"inesperada..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:586
msgid ""
"The crossing of the Nannan Swamps around River Oshune, albeit uncomfortable, "
"was safe, and Akhen and his friends reached Ifeh after three days. He was "
"impressed by the size and architecture of the great Chomi city, which he "
"secretly expected to be rustic like the Aeserian towns. Olufemi led him and "
"the others through the curious Chomi crowds towards the stately Sky Shrine, "
"and there the Maat'Karians met Orun, the city's Babalawo – or High Priest – "
"and paramount authority figure."
msgstr ""
"El cruce de los Pantanos de Nannan alrededor del río Oshune, aunque "
"incómodo, fue seguro, y Akhen y sus amigos llegaron a Ifeh después de tres "
"días. Quedó impresionado por el tamaño y la arquitectura de la gran ciudad "
"chomi, que en secreto esperaba que fuera rústica como los pueblos "
"aeserianos. Olufemi los guió a él y a los demás a través de las curiosas "
"multitudes chomi hacia el majestuoso Santuario del Cielo, y allí los "
"maat'karianos conocieron a Orun, el Babalawo de la ciudad —o Sumo Sacerdote— "
"y máxima autoridad."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:590
msgid ""
"He showed gratitude for the aid offered the Green Isle Chomi and their "
"Aeserian friends even though he owed them nothing, but when the Maat'Karian "
"told him about his own mission, the High Priest claimed that he couldn't "
"spare him an appreciable reinforcement, for he had to prepare for an "
"impending raid by the Washraha."
msgstr ""
"Mostró gratitud por la ayuda ofrecida a los chomi de la Isla Verde y a sus "
"amigos aeserianos aunque no les debía nada, pero cuando el maat'kariano le "
"habló de su propia misión, el Sumo Sacerdote dijo que no podía destinarle un "
"refuerzo considerable, porque tenía que prepararse para una incursión "
"inminente de los Washraha."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:594
msgid ""
"Akhen consulted briefly with his friends: he did not wish to get involved in "
"a foreign war again, but he wasn't sure whether other Chomi cities would be "
"as welcoming and friendly as Ifeh; and, after all the hardships he'd faced "
"in the sea up till then, he wasn't willing to search for allies on other "
"continents. Thus, Akhen pledged himself to cripple the Washraha campaign by "
"striking a heavy blow at them, in order to unburden the Chomi."
msgstr ""
"Akhen consultó brevemente con sus amigos: no deseaba involucrarse de nuevo "
"en una guerra ajena, pero no estaba seguro de si otras ciudades chomi serían "
"tan acogedoras y amigables como Ifeh; y después de todas las dificultades "
"que había enfrentado en el mar hasta entonces, no estaba dispuesto a buscar "
"aliados en otros continentes. Así, Akhen se comprometió a debilitar la "
"campaña de los Washraha asestándoles un golpe fuerte, para aliviar la carga "
"de los chomi."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:598
msgid ""
"Orun was impressed and, though he didn't show that, incredulous at their "
"possibilities of success, but he accepted the deal. He ordered Olufemi to "
"guide the Maat'Karians through a secret path that led to the Washrahan "
"capital, and gave them enough resources for the dangerous journey. After a "
"day's rest, Akhen's retinue left Ifeh and travelled southwards, through "
"swamps again, then meadows criss-crossed by rivers, until they reach a vast "
"and unusual lake..."
msgstr ""
"Orun quedó impresionado y, aunque no lo demostró, incrédulo ante sus "
"posibilidades de éxito, pero aceptó el trato. Ordenó a Olufemi que guiara a "
"los maat'karianos por un camino secreto que llevaba a la capital washrahana "
"y les dio suficientes recursos para el peligroso viaje. Después de un día de "
"descanso, el séquito de Akhen dejó Ifeh y viajó hacia el sur, nuevamente a "
"través de pantanos, luego por praderas atravesadas por ríos, hasta llegar a "
"un vasto y extraño lago..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:609
msgid ""
"The mages didn't need to go deep into the caves to understand what had made "
"Kayode so fearful: the energy emanating from the depths wasn't huge, or "
"evil, it was simply so strange and unfathomable that even Akhen, Merwe and "
"Mahyus felt uneasy. They also realised, by Mahyus' and Nyx's sudden "
"weakening, that it was not welcoming of undead beings."
msgstr ""
"Los magos no necesitaron adentrarse mucho en las cuevas para entender qué "
"había asustado tanto a Kayode: la energía que emanaba de las profundidades "
"no era enorme ni malvada, simplemente era tan extraña e insondable que "
"incluso Akhen, Merwe y Mahyus se sintieron incómodos. También se dieron "
"cuenta, por el repentino debilitamiento de Mahyus y Nyx, de que no era "
"bienvenida para los seres no muertos."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:612
msgid ""
"Akhen decided to split their forces: Olufemi, Nyx, Mahyus, Branwyn and the "
"Chomi would go through the mountain jungle, whilst he, Merwe and the "
"Maat'Karians would go underground. Olufemi approvingly pointed out that in "
"smaller numbers they'd be harder to spot in the jungle. Only Nyx disliked "
"the plan, because she did not like the idea of Akhen going alone with Merwe, "
"as much as she didn't want to admit that."
msgstr ""
"Akhen decidió dividir sus fuerzas: Olufemi, Nyx, Mahyus, Branwyn y los chomi "
"irían a través de la selva de montaña, mientras que él, Merwe y los "
"maat'karianos irían por el subsuelo. Olufemi señaló con aprobación que en "
"grupos más pequeños serían más difíciles de detectar en la selva. Solo Nyx "
"desaprobó el plan, porque no le gustaba la idea de que Akhen fuera solo con "
"Merwe, aunque no quisiera admitirlo."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:615
msgid ""
"Akhen and Merwe went very carefully at first, expecting to find the weirdest "
"and most dangerous creatures; but the first miles underground were actually "
"a pleasant journey. Merwe illuminated their path until they reached an area "
"where flashes of light coming seemingly out of nowhere lit up the caves. As "
"the mysterious energy grew stronger with the light, the two mages readied "
"themselves for the unknown..."
msgstr ""
"Akhen y Merwe avanzaron con mucho cuidado al principio, esperando encontrar "
"las criaturas más extrañas y peligrosas; pero los primeros kilómetros bajo "
"tierra fueron en realidad un viaje agradable. Merwe iluminó su camino hasta "
"que llegaron a una zona donde destellos de luz que parecían surgir de la "
"nada iluminaban las cuevas. A medida que la misteriosa energía se volvía más "
"fuerte junto con la luz, los dos magos se prepararon para lo desconocido..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:625
msgid ""
"The Washraha didn't dare pursue the Chomi in the jungle, and so Akhen's "
"retinue returned to Ifeh without further trouble. The leaders of the city "
"didn't seem to be fazed at the news that their enemies might still attack "
"them; they visibly didn't expect much from Sa-Tarva. Orun told Akhen that he "
"would soon receive the promised platoon and, as bonus, a ship; but the "
"Maat'Karian, feeling uneasy, postponed the day of departure, even though Nyx "
"and Mahyus urged him to leave as soon as possible."
msgstr ""
"Los Washraha no se atrevieron a perseguir a los chomi en la selva, por lo "
"que el séquito de Akhen regresó a Ifeh sin más problemas. Los líderes de la "
"ciudad no parecían inquietos ante la noticia de que sus enemigos aún podrían "
"atacarlos; era evidente que no esperaban mucho de Sa-Tarva. Orun le dijo a "
"Akhen que pronto recibiría el pelotón prometido y, como bono, un barco; pero "
"el maat'kariano, sintiéndose inquieto, pospuso el día de partida, aunque Nyx "
"y Mahyus le insistían en que se fueran lo antes posible."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:629
msgid ""
"Akhen's uneasiness was justified seventeen days after his return to Ifeh, in "
"the middle of a particularly hot and dry week: Chomi outpost guards came to "
"the city panting and wounded, claiming that a massive Washrahan host was on "
"the way. The city quickly prepared its defences, and the Maat'Karians "
"readied themselves for another battle as Empress Sa-Tarva and her armies "
"loomed over the flickering horizon..."
msgstr ""
"La inquietud de Akhen se justificó diecisiete días después de su regreso a "
"Ifeh, en medio de una semana particularmente calurosa y seca: guardias de "
"puestos avanzados chomi llegaron a la ciudad jadeando y heridos, afirmando "
"que un enorme ejército washrahano se acercaba. La ciudad preparó rápidamente "
"sus defensas, y los maat'karianos se prepararon para otra batalla mientras "
"la Emperatriz Sa-Tarva y sus ejércitos se cernían sobre el horizonte "
"titilante..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:640
msgid ""
"And so the Maat'Karians and their new allies left Arajunna. After all those "
"months away from their homeland, the soldiers were all anxious to set foot "
"on Netjer-Ta, cross the lofty Maat'Karian walls and drink Maat'Karian beer "
"with their families. Akhen, however, couldn't avoid feeling a bit nervous as "
"well; for the closer he was to Netjer-Ta, the closer he was to the "
"inevitable clash with Menon. He even caught himself wishing that their "
"return was delayed just a bit longer, that they ended up on another unknown "
"shore where they could get more allies and postpone that fated battle..."
msgstr ""
"Y así los maat'karianos y sus nuevos aliados dejaron Arajunna. Después de "
"todos esos meses lejos de su patria, los soldados estaban ansiosos por pisar "
"Netjer-Ta, cruzar las altas murallas maat'karianas y beber cerveza "
"maat'kariana con sus familias. Akhen, sin embargo, tampoco podía evitar "
"sentirse un poco nervioso; porque cuanto más cerca estaba de Netjer-Ta, más "
"cerca estaba del inevitable enfrentamiento con Menon. Hasta se sorprendió "
"deseando que su regreso se retrasara un poco más, que terminaran en otra "
"costa desconocida donde pudieran conseguir más aliados y posponer esa "
"batalla destinada..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:644
msgid ""
"And – for better or for worse – his wish was fulfilled, as the sailors found "
"an unknown shore after a few days of travel..."
msgstr ""
"Y —para bien o para mal— su deseo se cumplió, cuando los marineros "
"encontraron una costa desconocida después de unos días de viaje..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:655
msgid ""
"Akhen could barely believe how lucky and unlucky he was at the same time: "
"unlucky for docking on Argea - which was expected to be much farther away - "
"and lucky for being found by friendly people on the cradle of Skiron. Most "
"people of his retinue still distrusted the strange being, but Akhen knew he "
"was friendly, in spite of his somewhat ambiguous demeanour."
msgstr ""
"Akhen apenas podía creer lo afortunado y desafortunado que era al mismo "
"tiempo: desafortunado por atracar en Argea —que se esperaba que estuviera "
"mucho más lejos— y afortunado por ser encontrado por gente amistosa en la "
"cuna de Skiron. La mayoría de las personas de su séquito todavía "
"desconfiaban del extraño ser, pero Akhen sabía que era amistoso, a pesar de "
"su comportamiento algo ambiguo."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:659
msgid ""
"Volturnus led the humans into the wild, uninhabited heartlands of Argea. The "
"Maat'Karians couldn't help but stand in awe at the lushness of the life that "
"grew there; they used to think of Argea as a barren wasteland that sheltered "
"Skironians and orcs, but the vast and green forests, noisy rivers and blue "
"lakes before them were as beautiful and idyllic as those of the 'pure' Green "
"Isle."
msgstr ""
"Volturnus guió a los humanos hacia las tierras salvajes y deshabitadas del "
"corazón de Argea. Los maat'karianos no pudieron evitar quedar asombrados por "
"la exuberancia de la vida que crecía allí; solían pensar en Argea como un "
"desierto estéril que albergaba a skironianos y orcos, pero los vastos y "
"verdes bosques, los ríos ruidosos y los lagos azules ante ellos eran tan "
"hermosos e idílicos como los de la «pura» Isla Verde."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:663
msgid ""
"Nevertheless, they were still on a land inhabited by some unfriendly "
"factions, and so their journey was only calm so far..."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, todavía estaban en una tierra habitada por algunas facciones "
"hostiles, por lo que su viaje había sido tranquilo solo hasta ese momento..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:674
msgid ""
"Of all the places Akhen had been in that journey across the seas, Heartwood "
"Valley was certainly the most beautiful and the most enticing - at least for "
"him, who had the strongest connection to nature's energy amongst his "
"friends. Nestled amidst colossal mountains, covered in lush forests and "
"filled with the sound of the fauns' romping, the cicadas' cry and the birds' "
"singing; the valley was like a cauldron bursting with life."
msgstr ""
"De todos los lugares que Akhen había visitado en ese viaje a través de los "
"mares, el Valle del Bosque Profundo era sin duda el más hermoso y atractivo, "
"al menos para él, que tenía la conexión más fuerte con la energía de la "
"naturaleza entre sus amigos. Anidado entre montañas colosales, cubierto de "
"exuberantes bosques y lleno del sonido de los faunos jugando, el canto de "
"las cigarras y el canto de los pájaros; el valle era como un caldero "
"rebosante de vida."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:678
msgid ""
"The travellers were left to wait in a small villa; Aferius led Akhen to a "
"small island in the middle of a lake; once there, they met the three Wardens "
"at a clearing covered by huge and strangely overarching trees."
msgstr ""
"A los viajeros los dejaron esperar en una pequeña villa; Aferius llevó a "
"Akhen a una pequeña isla en medio de un lago; una vez allí, se reunieron con "
"los tres Guardianes en un claro cubierto por árboles enormes y extrañamente "
"arqueados."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:682
msgid ""
"After Aferius' introductions, Akhen told of his journey, concluding with the "
"promise to help the fauns fight Skiron once Maat'Kare's Civil War was over. "
"The Wardens were very interested in such alliance, but still didn't "
"completely trust the human; and the meeting would have lasted for many "
"hours, were it not the loud and frantic blowing of a horn, which echoed "
"ominously in the valley..."
msgstr ""
"Después de las presentaciones de Aferius, Akhen contó su viaje, concluyendo "
"con la promesa de ayudar a los faunos a luchar contra Skiron una vez que "
"terminara la Guerra Civil de Maat'Kare. Los Guardianes estaban muy "
"interesados en esa alianza, pero aún no confiaban completamente en el "
"humano; y la reunión habría durado muchas horas de no ser por el fuerte y "
"frenético sonido de un cuerno, que resonó de forma ominosa en el valle..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:693
msgid ""
"Thus, led by a faun scout, Akhen and his group left Heartwood Valley and "
"went northwards, to the Argean shores washed by the Strait of the "
"Continents. On the way, he explained to everyone about Myra. He feared that "
"his friends would find it weird, but, to his surprise, the knowledge that "
"the spirit of their legendary heroine was literally with them boosted their "
"morale as much as Aegaion's defeat."
msgstr ""
"Así, guiados por un explorador fauno, Akhen y su grupo dejaron el Valle del "
"Bosque Profundo y se dirigieron al norte, hacia las costas de Argea bañadas "
"por el Estrecho de los Continentes. En el camino, les explicó a todos sobre "
"Myra. Temía que a sus amigos les pareciera extraño, pero para su sorpresa, "
"el saber que el espíritu de su legendaria heroína estaba literalmente con "
"ellos elevó su moral tanto como la derrota de Aegaion."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:697
msgid ""
"Their cheerfulness was undermined when they reached the shores, however, as "
"they saw the northern horizon punctuated with Skironian war ships. After "
"some deliberation, they decided to attempt crossing the underwater "
"Motsoghnir tunnels, the same ones that Argatyr had blocked months before; "
"Akhen's plan was to reopen them with earthen and water elementals, just like "
"Menon had done to rescue the dwarf lord."
msgstr ""
"Su alegría se vio empañada cuando llegaron a las costas, sin embargo, al ver "
"el horizonte norte salpicado de barcos de guerra skironianos. Después de "
"deliberar, decidieron intentar cruzar los túneles submarinos de los "
"Motsoghnir, los mismos que Argatyr había bloqueado meses antes; el plan de "
"Akhen era reabrirlos con elementales de tierra y agua, tal como Menon había "
"hecho para rescatar al señor enano."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:701
msgid ""
"The crossing was, in the end, successful – though not devoid of a great deal "
"of tension; the tunnel opened amidst the rubble by the elementals was "
"precarious, and they could have all been crushed by the ocean's weight at "
"any time. And, when they finally trod on Netjer-Ta's soil for the first time "
"in more than an year, they found themselves in a pitch-black system of "
"caves. Worse still, they had no way to tell whether they were in friendly or "
"hostile territory..."
msgstr ""
"El cruce fue, al final, exitoso —aunque no exento de mucha tensión; el túnel "
"abierto entre los escombros por los elementales era precario, y podrían "
"haber sido aplastados por el peso del océano en cualquier momento. Y cuando "
"finalmente pisaron suelo de Netjer-Ta por primera vez en más de un año, se "
"encontraron en un sistema de cuevas completamente oscuro. Peor aún, no "
"tenían forma de saber si estaban en territorio amigo u hostil..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:706
msgid "Part VI: Forces of Nature"
msgstr "Parte VI: Fuerzas de la Naturaleza"

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:716
msgid ""
"It barely looked like they were fleeing a dwarf lord bent on murdering them: "
"glad that they were together again after so many months, the friends talked "
"almost cheerfully about Akhen's group's journey across the seas, from the "
"ill-fated expedition to the Blue Realm, to the unexpected war against drakes "
"on the Green Isle, to the adventures in Arajunna and then the desperate "
"showdown with Aegaion himself - by far the story which impressed Atenak and "
"Sigdral the most."
msgstr ""
"Apenas parecía que estuvieran huyendo de un señor enano empeñado en "
"asesinarlos: contentos de estar juntos de nuevo después de tantos meses, los "
"amigos hablaron casi alegremente sobre el viaje del grupo de Akhen a través "
"de los mares, desde la desastrosa expedición al Reino Azul, hasta la "
"inesperada guerra contra los dracos en la Isla Verde, las aventuras en "
"Arajunna y luego el desesperado enfrentamiento con el propio Aegaion —sin "
"duda la historia que más impresionó a Atenak y Sigdral."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:720
msgid ""
"But then the talk became more serious, as Atenak explained what had happened "
"in Netjer-Ta in those months. Sadjet had taken Ineb-Hedj; Smenkhare had "
"surrendered himself to give Atenak and the surviving rebels the chance to "
"flee, and they had hurried to the Aigathol caves, gathering a few more "
"adepts on the way."
msgstr ""
"Pero luego la conversación se volvió más seria, cuando Atenak explicó lo que "
"había pasado en Netjer-Ta en esos meses. Sadjet había tomado Ineb-Hedj; "
"Smenkhare se había entregado para darles a Atenak y a los rebeldes "
"sobrevivientes la oportunidad de huir, y ellos se habían apresurado hacia "
"las cuevas de Aigathol, reuniendo a algunos adeptos más en el camino."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:724
msgid ""
"Once in the caves, the rebels were no longer pursued by Menon, who had "
"turned his attention to Skiron, but then they became a target for Argatyr. "
"Together with the Aigathol, they resisted the Motsoghnir for many months, "
"but when their leader started joining the fray himself, Sigdral's forces "
"were steadily decimated, to the point that only a few hundred of her people "
"still lived. The battle joined by Akhen was to be Sigdral's and Atenak's "
"last stand."
msgstr ""
"Una vez en las cuevas, los rebeldes ya no eran perseguidos por Menon, quien "
"había dirigido su atención hacia Skiron, pero entonces se convirtieron en "
"objetivo de Argatyr. Junto con los Aigathol, resistieron a los Motsoghnir "
"durante muchos meses, pero cuando su líder comenzó a unirse personalmente a "
"la lucha, las fuerzas de Sigdral fueron diezmadas constantemente, hasta el "
"punto de que solo unos pocos cientos de su pueblo seguían vivos. La batalla "
"en la que participó Akhen iba a ser la última resistencia de Sigdral y "
"Atenak."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:728
msgid ""
"On the surface, they decided on their next course of action. Atenak agreed "
"that, with Aegaion weakened, Menon should focus on Skiron more than ever, "
"and so Maat'Kare would be vulnerable to them. But they couldn’t attack Menon "
"with Argatyr on their heels, and they couldn't hope to defeat the dwarf "
"master with their current forces. There was, however, one faction on Netjer-"
"Ta which could still be friendly to them, and so Akhen, riding a tame "
"gryphon, hurried to that faction's land..."
msgstr ""
"En la superficie, decidieron su próximo curso de acción. Atenak estuvo de "
"acuerdo en que, con Aegaion debilitado, Menon debería enfocarse en Skiron "
"más que nunca, y así Maat'Kare quedaría vulnerable para ellos. Pero no "
"podían atacar a Menon con Argatyr pisándoles los talones, y no podían "
"esperar derrotar al maestro enano con sus fuerzas actuales. Sin embargo, "
"había una facción en Netjer-Ta que todavía podía serles amistosa, por lo que "
"Akhen, montando un grifo domesticado, se apresuró hacia las tierras de esa "
"facción..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:739
msgid ""
"Akhen returned swiftly to the Valley of Alenya - the last safe haven for the "
"Aigathol in the mountains - with the good news; now they stood a chance of "
"defeating Argatyr, though possibilities of defeat were not to be "
"underestimated either."
msgstr ""
"Akhen regresó rápidamente al Valle de Alenya —el último refugio seguro para "
"los Aigathol en las montañas— con buenas noticias; ahora tenían una "
"oportunidad de derrotar a Argatyr, aunque las posibilidades de derrota "
"tampoco debían subestimarse."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:743
msgid ""
"After dwarvish scouts found out that Argatyr was sending troops all over the "
"underground tunnels after them, the allies decided to set their plan in "
"course: moving quickly through the caves and mercilessly crushing any "
"opposition, they got closer and closer to their goal - and, as expected, "
"nearly unopposed, as the Motsoghnir withdrew their battalions to their "
"capital; Varag had launched his offensive."
msgstr ""
"Después de que los exploradores enanos descubrieran que Argatyr enviaba "
"tropas por todos los túneles subterráneos tras ellos, los aliados decidieron "
"poner en marcha su plan: avanzando rápidamente por las cuevas y aplastando "
"sin piedad cualquier oposición, se acercaron cada vez más a su objetivo, y, "
"como era de esperar, casi sin oposición, ya que los Motsoghnir retiraron sus "
"batallones hacia su capital; Varag había lanzado su ofensiva."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:747
msgid ""
"And then, as Sigdral blew open the last gate, they were met with wind gusts "
"and the booming of thunder, and the Aigathol held their axes and hammers "
"even more tightly; for they were about to fight a showdown against an "
"ancient dwarven power from their remotest legends..."
msgstr ""
"Y entonces, cuando Sigdral voló la última puerta, los recibió una ráfaga de "
"viento y el estruendo de truenos, y los Aigathol apretaron aún más fuerte "
"sus hachas y martillos; porque estaban a punto de librar un enfrentamiento "
"decisivo contra un antiguo poder enano de sus leyendas más remotas..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:758
msgid ""
"The defeat of Argatyr and his Motsoghnir was quietly celebrated by most, "
"though; after so many months of constant and brutal fighting, the caves of "
"Netjer-Ta were silent once again, and both the Aigathol and the Maat'Karian "
"rebels could sleep in peace once more."
msgstr ""
"La derrota de Argatyr y sus Motsoghnir fue celebrada en silencio por la "
"mayoría; después de tantos meses de combates constantes y brutales, las "
"cuevas de Netjer-Ta volvieron a quedar en silencio, y tanto los Aigathol "
"como los rebeldes maat'karianos pudieron dormir en paz una vez más."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:762
msgid ""
"Only two people remained gloomy. To Sigdral, who had just killed the one she "
"had once loved, who had lost both her brother and her mentor and who now was "
"the ruler of a wrecked nation, that triumph brought little joy. Gomatol had "
"promised to remain her close friend, and even allowed her to keep Ymer’s "
"Hammer, claiming that she now was the only dwarf in Netjer-Ta worthy of it. "
"As for the Motsoghnir who had remained loyal to Argatyr, their resentment "
"would not acquiesce to any compensation, and so Sigdral expelled them from "
"those caves; they were last sighted heading for the northern mountains."
msgstr ""
"Solo dos personas permanecieron sombrías. Para Sigdral, que acababa de matar "
"al que una vez había amado, que había perdido tanto a su hermano como a su "
"mentor y que ahora era la gobernante de una nación destrozada, ese triunfo "
"traía poca alegría. Gomatol había prometido seguir siendo su amigo cercano y "
"hasta le permitió conservar el Martillo de Ymer, afirmando que ella era "
"ahora la única enana en Netjer-Ta digna de él. En cuanto a los Motsoghnir "
"que habían permanecido leales a Argatyr, su resentimiento no aceptaría "
"ninguna compensación, por lo que Sigdral los expulsó de esas cuevas; se les "
"vio por última vez dirigiéndose hacia las montañas del norte."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:766
msgid ""
"As for Akhen, he just couldn't relax with the confrontation against his "
"master looming closer and closer. With Argatyr's threat over, he'd "
"inevitably have to march against his own people. He'd always known he'd have "
"to do that, but he wouldn't have been capable of giving his followers the "
"order to march eastwards if Nyx hadn't been there for him. Sigdral, busy "
"with the rebuilding of her nation, could not follow them, but promised to "
"join them in the final battle."
msgstr ""
"En cuanto a Akhen, simplemente no podía relajarse con el enfrentamiento "
"contra su maestro acercándose cada vez más. Con la amenaza de Argatyr "
"terminada, inevitablemente tendría que marchar contra su propio pueblo. "
"Siempre había sabido que tendría que hacerlo, pero no habría sido capaz de "
"darles a sus seguidores la orden de marchar hacia el este si Nyx no hubiera "
"estado allí para él. Sigdral, ocupada con la reconstrucción de su nación, no "
"pudo seguirlos, pero prometió unirse a ellos en la batalla final."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:770
msgid ""
"Akhen and Atenak had planned on sending scouts to the frontier cities and "
"migdols, to muster whatever support they could from among the population. "
"Their hope was to be able to take the western cities with the people's "
"support, thus keeping bloodshed to a minimum. However, they were still to "
"enter Tarkyn's Meadows when they were faced by their countrymen..."
msgstr ""
"Akhen y Atenak habían planeado enviar exploradores a las ciudades "
"fronterizas y migdoles para reunir todo el apoyo posible entre la población. "
"Su esperanza era poder tomar las ciudades del oeste con el apoyo del pueblo, "
"manteniendo así el derramamiento de sangre al mínimo. Sin embargo, aún no "
"habían entrado a los Prados de Tarkyn cuando se enfrentaron a sus "
"compatriotas..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:781
msgid ""
"Akhen's group had, till then, battled vampire lords, Lich-Lords, drakes, "
"giants and Aegaion himself; but Khamet and his soldiers were, by far, the "
"hardest foes to fight. The rebels knew that they couldn’t waste time there, "
"lest they’d be caught by more Maat’Karian battalions, but they couldn’t "
"leave their countrymen's bodies rotting in the open, and so they only "
"resumed their march after giving them all a worthy cremation."
msgstr ""
"El grupo de Akhen había luchado hasta entonces contra señores vampiros, Dama "
"Liches, dracos, gigantes y el propio Aegaion; pero Khamet y sus soldados "
"fueron, con diferencia, los enemigos más difíciles de enfrentar. Los "
"rebeldes sabían que no podían perder tiempo allí, no fuera que los "
"alcanzaran más batallones maat'karianos, pero tampoco podían dejar los "
"cuerpos de sus compatriotas pudriéndose a la intemperie, por lo que solo "
"reanudaron la marcha después de darles a todos una cremación digna."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:785
msgid ""
"After learning the Chomi's fighting tactics, Atenak led them all through a "
"region of Tarkyn’s Meadows that was heavily forested and criss-crossed by "
"streams. There they managed to easily defeat the many elemental battalions "
"sent after them; Atenak hoped to reach Ineb-Hedj, which should still be full "
"of rebels, and from there they could try and convert more cities to their "
"cause."
msgstr ""
"Después de aprender las tácticas de combate de los chomi, Atenak los guió a "
"todos a través de una región de los Prados de Tarkyn muy boscosa y "
"atravesada por arroyos. Allí lograron derrotar fácilmente a los numerosos "
"batallones de elementales enviados tras ellos; Atenak esperaba llegar a Ineb-"
"Hedj, que todavía debía estar llena de rebeldes, y desde allí intentar "
"convencer a más ciudades de unirse a su causa."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:789
msgid ""
"However, certain morning they were awoken by deafening blasts and the acrid "
"smell of burning wood: there was a massive wave of fire elementals burning "
"down large patches of the forest, scorching the earth and even drying up "
"streams running nearby. When a wind blew most of the smoke away, they were "
"able to see, standing amidst that inferno, the dread Fire Empress herself..."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, cierta mañana fueron despertados por detonaciones "
"ensordecedoras y el olor acre de madera quemada: había una enorme oleada de "
"elementales de fuego quemando grandes extensiones del bosque, calcinando la "
"tierra e incluso secando los arroyos cercanos. Cuando el viento se llevó la "
"mayor parte del humo, pudieron ver, de pie en medio de ese infierno, a la "
"temible Emperatriz del Fuego en persona..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:800
msgid ""
"Feeling more confident now that the mighty Fire Empress had joined them, the "
"small rebel army went on through forests and hills towards Ineb-Hedj. In "
"order to save them time, Nyx offered to go rescue Smenkhare, since she knew "
"well the mountains where he should be hidden. Akhen didn't want to let her "
"go alone, but Mahyus and Branwyn went along with her."
msgstr ""
"Sintiéndose más confiados ahora que la poderosa Emperatriz del Fuego se "
"había unido a ellos, el pequeño ejército rebelde continuó a través de "
"bosques y colinas hacia Ineb-Hedj. Para ahorrarles tiempo, Nyx se ofreció a "
"ir a rescatar a Smenkhare, pues conocía bien las montañas donde debía estar "
"escondido. Akhen no quería dejarla ir sola, pero Mahyus y Branwyn la "
"acompañaron."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:804
msgid ""
"And they couldn't have been more successful: after a mere four days, they "
"reunited with the rest of the army, bringing a weakened, but exhilarating "
"Smenkhare along with them. He approved their plan of retaking Ineb-Hedj, "
"adding that they could exhort its people to join them in the fight to free "
"the city."
msgstr ""
"Y no pudieron tener más éxito: después de apenas cuatro días, se reunieron "
"con el resto del ejército, trayendo consigo a un debilitado pero animado "
"Smenkhare. Él aprobó su plan de reconquistar Ineb-Hedj, agregando que "
"podrían exhortar a su pueblo a unirse a ellos en la lucha por liberar la "
"ciudad."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:808
msgid ""
"They took just a couple of days to sight the former rebel stronghold. As the "
"sun rose from the horizon, the rebel army, led by Atenak and Akhen, stormed "
"out of the forested hills that framed the city's lands, screaming loudly so "
"that the people of Ineb-Hedj could hear them..."
msgstr ""
"Solo les tomó un par de días avistar el antiguo bastión rebelde. Mientras el "
"sol salía por el horizonte, el ejército rebelde, liderado por Atenak y "
"Akhen, salió en tromba de las colinas boscosas que enmarcaban las tierras de "
"la ciudad, gritando fuerte para que la gente de Ineb-Hedj pudiera oírlos..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:819
msgid ""
"The news of Ineb-Hedj's fall to the rebels, of Akhen's return and of his vow "
"to stop Menon's tyranny spread swiftly throughout Maat'Karian lands, carried "
"by merchants and travellers. As Sadjet had foreseen, many lords expressed "
"their dissatisfaction with the central government when the Fire Empress and "
"Ineb-Hedj defied it first, and news were that the people of various other "
"cities and towns supported the rebels."
msgstr ""
"La noticia de la caída de Ineb-Hedj en manos de los rebeldes, del regreso de "
"Akhen y de su juramento de detener la tiranía de Menon se extendió "
"rápidamente por las tierras maat'karianas, llevada por mercaderes y "
"viajeros. Como Sadjet había previsto, muchos señores expresaron su "
"descontento con el gobierno central cuando la Emperatriz del Fuego e Ineb-"
"Hedj lo desafiaron primero, y se decía que la gente de varias otras ciudades "
"y pueblos apoyaba a los rebeldes."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:823
msgid ""
"However, there were still many who actually supported Menon's politics - "
"such as most of the Sages - and they wouldn't sit idly as their favoured "
"government was challenged. When Menon himself decreed that the loyalists "
"must suppress the 'rebel weed' from growing, the result was that the civil "
"war took unprecedented proportions."
msgstr ""
"Sin embargo, todavía había muchos que realmente apoyaban la política de "
"Menon —como la mayoría de los Sabios— y no se quedarían de brazos cruzados "
"mientras su gobierno favorito era desafiado. Cuando el propio Menon decretó "
"que los leales debían suprimir la «mala hierba rebelde» antes de que "
"creciera, el resultado fue que la guerra civil alcanzó proporciones sin "
"precedentes."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:827
msgid ""
"In cities with a rebel-sympathizer majority under loyalist rule, violent "
"protests erupted; rebel lords sent troops to help the civilians, and this "
"prompted their loyalist counterparts to send out actual armies to storm "
"their cities. The rebels, led by Sadjet and Smenkhare, managed to deal with "
"their foes without difficulty, but that was not what Akhen, Merwe, Atenak "
"and Mahyus cared about. They only felt shock before that violent fratricide "
"that was destroying their civilisation before their very eyes."
msgstr ""
"En ciudades con mayoría simpatizante de los rebeldes bajo gobierno leal, "
"estallaron protestas violentas; señores rebeldes enviaron tropas para ayudar "
"a los civiles, y esto provocó que sus contrapartes leales enviaran ejércitos "
"reales a tomar sus ciudades. Los rebeldes, liderados por Sadjet y Smenkhare, "
"lograron enfrentar a sus enemigos sin dificultad, pero eso no era lo que le "
"importaba a Akhen, Merwe, Atenak y Mahyus. Solo sentían conmoción ante ese "
"fratricidio violento que estaba destruyendo su civilización ante sus propios "
"ojos."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:831
msgid ""
"Thus, in order to end the civil war, they had to bring Menon down as quickly "
"as possible; and so Akhen, Atenak and Smenkhare prepared an attack on the "
"Land's End Peninsula itself. However, they knew that, by land, it was "
"completely sealed by a mighty defence led by none less than Suryen himself. "
"They could still break it, but not alone, and so they sent an aid call to "
"Sigdral."
msgstr ""
"Por lo tanto, para terminar con la guerra civil, tenían que derribar a Menon "
"lo más rápido posible; así que Akhen, Atenak y Smenkhare prepararon un "
"ataque contra la propia península de Land's End. Sin embargo, sabían que por "
"tierra estaba completamente sellada por una poderosa defensa liderada nada "
"menos que por el propio Suryen. Aún podían romperla, pero no solos, por lo "
"que enviaron una llamada de ayuda a Sigdral."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:835
msgid ""
"And the answer came quickly. Seven days later, Sigdral arrived at Ineb-Hedj "
"with her small army of battle-hardened dwarves, alongside Romlur and his "
"wargs; he had really observed the Maat'Karian affairs from afar, and had "
"decided that Akhen was the side worth taking."
msgstr ""
"Y la respuesta llegó rápido. Siete días después, Sigdral llegó a Ineb-Hedj "
"con su pequeño ejército de enanos endurecidos en batalla, junto a Romlur y "
"sus huargos; él realmente había observado los asuntos maat'karianos desde "
"lejos y había decidido que el bando de Akhen valía la pena apoyar."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:839
msgid ""
"And so Akhen, Atenak, Sigdral, Romlur and their respective armies marched "
"towards the Land's End Peninsula. Going mostly through rebel-held territory "
"and facing little resistance, they didn't take long to find the massive Fort "
"Abhai..."
msgstr ""
"Y así Akhen, Atenak, Sigdral, Romlur y sus respectivos ejércitos marcharon "
"hacia la península de Land's End. Avanzando principalmente por territorio "
"controlado por los rebeldes y enfrentando poca resistencia, no tardaron en "
"encontrar la enorme Fortaleza Abhai..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:850
msgid ""
"Nyx had noticed that, since Ineb-Hedj’s retaking, Akhen had been even tenser "
"than usual, and she knew why: for every rebel victory, he was a step closer "
"to the inevitable showdown with the one who had always been a father to him. "
"She too felt tenser as they neared the end of that war, but for a different "
"reason: she feared the outcome of that final battle. Not that she didn't "
"trust Akhen; she simply hadn't forgotten how Menon had, almost single-"
"handedly, devastated Jevyan's armada and Stygia's legion, and she just "
"couldn't bear the thought of her Akhen facing that monster alone..."
msgstr ""
"Nyx había notado que, desde la reconquista de Ineb-Hedj, Akhen estaba aún "
"más tenso de lo habitual, y sabía por qué: por cada victoria rebelde, él "
"estaba un paso más cerca del inevitable enfrentamiento con quien siempre "
"había sido un padre para él. Ella también se sentía más tensa a medida que "
"se acercaban al final de esa guerra, pero por una razón diferente: temía el "
"resultado de esa batalla final. No es que no confiara en Akhen; simplemente "
"no había olvidado cómo Menon había devastado casi por sí solo la armada de "
"Jevyan y la legión de Stygia, y simplemente no soportaba la idea de que su "
"Akhen enfrentara solo a ese monstruo..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:854
msgid ""
"Funny how love can make one so irrational, she thought as she caught herself "
"pleading with him not to duel Menon, even though she knew nothing would move "
"him from that, for he was the only one who could save him from the Sky "
"Soul's spell..."
msgstr ""
"Qué curioso cómo el amor puede volver a uno tan irracional, pensó mientras "
"se descubría suplicándole que no duelara con Menon, aunque sabía que nada lo "
"haría cambiar de idea, porque él era el único que podía salvarlo del hechizo "
"del Alma del Cielo..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:858
msgid ""
"But Akhen was understanding; he too was fearful of a stand-off against he "
"who had been the mightiest amongst the mightiest for seven centuries, and, "
"as hard as it was to admit, he knew he had slim chances of surviving that "
"encounter..."
msgstr ""
"Pero Akhen comprendía; él también temía un enfrentamiento contra quien había "
"sido el más poderoso entre los poderosos durante siete siglos y, por más "
"difícil que fuera admitirlo, sabía que tenía pocas posibilidades de "
"sobrevivir a ese encuentro..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:862
msgid ""
"Also for that reason, he felt like they should no longer suppress their "
"feelings for each other. And then, at the highest tower of Maat'Kare's "
"greatest fortress, Akhen and Nyx confessed to each other for the first time "
"with a long kiss. It mattered not to either that their ancestors had been "
"mortal enemies, or that they'd never be able to have children of their own "
"blood, or even that they might both die soon; all that mattered was that, "
"against all odds, they loved each other."
msgstr ""
"Por esa misma razón, sintió que ya no debían reprimir sus sentimientos el "
"uno por el otro. Y entonces, en la torre más alta de la mayor fortaleza de "
"Maat'Kare, Akhen y Nyx se confesaron por primera vez con un largo beso. No "
"les importaba a ninguno que sus ancestros hubieran sido enemigos mortales, "
"ni que nunca pudieran tener hijos de su propia sangre, ni siquiera que ambos "
"pudieran morir pronto; lo único que importaba era que, contra todo "
"pronóstico, se amaban."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:866
msgid ""
"In the following morning, as everyone prepared to resume marching, their "
"friends noticed something different about the human and the vampiress, as if "
"they were more bonded to each other than ever, and they smiled; after being "
"amidst so much strife and violence for so long, it was good to be reminded "
"that there were still beautiful things in that world."
msgstr ""
"A la mañana siguiente, mientras todos se preparaban para reanudar la marcha, "
"sus amigos notaron algo diferente en el humano y la vampiresa, como si "
"estuvieran más unidos que nunca, y sonrieron; después de estar rodeados de "
"tanta lucha y violencia durante tanto tiempo, era bueno recordar que todavía "
"había cosas hermosas en este mundo."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:870
msgid ""
"Two days later, they could finally sight, rising above the horizons, the "
"glistening towers of the City of the Sun, their beloved city, now turned "
"into their ultimate enemy..."
msgstr ""
"Dos días después, finalmente pudieron avistar, elevándose sobre el "
"horizonte, las relucientes torres de la Ciudad del Sol, su querida ciudad, "
"ahora convertida en su enemigo definitivo..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:881
msgid ""
"The soldiers who still fought outside the Foundation Square all stopped when "
"they saw Akhen carrying Menon's lifeless, skeletal body. Whilst the "
"loyalists fell on their knees, unable to believe that the Immortal had "
"fallen, the rebels roared in triumph - and were scolded by Akhen, who "
"claimed that the fall of the Master of Four Lights was no reason for "
"celebration."
msgstr ""
"Los soldados que aún luchaban fuera de la Plaza de la Fundación se "
"detuvieron todos cuando vieron a Akhen cargando el cuerpo sin vida y "
"esquelético de Menon. Mientras los leales caían de rodillas, incapaces de "
"creer que el Inmortal había caído, los rebeldes rugieron en triunfo, pero "
"fueron reprendidos por Akhen, quien afirmó que la caída del Maestro de las "
"Cuatro Luces no era motivo de celebración."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:885
msgid ""
"Still, he could do nothing to contain the wave of joy and relief that ran "
"the country with the news of Menon's destruction. The loyalist sages and "
"lords who surrendered were ultimately forgiven, and those who didn't were "
"captured and sent to the great prison of Duat. Akhen was hailed as a hero: "
"the nickname he received in the Green Isle became known amongst "
"Maat'Karians, thanks to the Chomi, and in addition to that he received a new "
"one: the Liberator."
msgstr ""
"Aun así, no pudo hacer nada para contener la ola de alegría y alivio que "
"recorrió el país con la noticia de la destrucción de Menon. Los sabios y "
"señores leales que se rindieron fueron finalmente perdonados, y aquellos que "
"no lo hicieron fueron capturados y enviados a la gran prisión de Duat. Akhen "
"fue aclamado como un héroe: el apodo que recibió en la Isla Verde se hizo "
"conocido entre los maat'karianos gracias a los chomi, y además de eso "
"recibió uno nuevo: el Liberador."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:889
msgid ""
"But he didn't bother about all the praise and gratitude he received; he was "
"more interested in making Menon's story known, so that people might "
"understand that he was being controlled. Not everyone forgave the former "
"Great Seer, but his funeral was attended by many, Smenkhare and Sadjet "
"included; his remains were burnt in a funeral pyre at the Academy's highest "
"tower, so that the winds could spread his ashes over the city he'd protected "
"for so long."
msgstr ""
"Pero él no se preocupaba por todos los elogios y gratitud que recibía; "
"estaba más interesado en dar a conocer la historia de Menon, para que la "
"gente entendiera que había sido controlado. No todos perdonaron al antiguo "
"Gran Vidente, pero su funeral fue atendido por muchos, incluyendo a "
"Smenkhare y Sadjet; sus restos fueron quemados en una pira funeraria en la "
"torre más alta de la Academia, para que los vientos pudieran esparcir sus "
"cenizas sobre la ciudad que había protegido durante tanto tiempo."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:893
msgid ""
"Afterwards, the rebellion's leaders gathered to decide what they were going "
"to do next. After all, the country was devastated, the population had "
"decreased by the thousands, and Aegaion was still alive and coveting the Sky "
"Soul. The cursed jewel's new guardian, however, had a plan in mind..."
msgstr ""
"Después, los líderes de la rebelión se reunieron para decidir qué harían a "
"continuación. Después de todo, el país estaba devastado, la población había "
"disminuido por miles, y Aegaion seguía vivo y codiciando el Alma del Cielo. "
"Sin embargo, el nuevo guardián de la joya maldita tenía un plan en mente..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:903
msgid ""
"The decision of moving their whole civilization to the Silent Desert was "
"extremely controversial, but in the end everyone agreed that it was for the "
"best. The building of New Maat'Kare took, coincidentally, sixteen months, "
"and in the end it was easily the largest city in all of Netjer-Ta."
msgstr ""
"La decisión de trasladar toda su civilización al Desierto Silencioso fue "
"extremadamente controvertida, pero al final todos estuvieron de acuerdo en "
"que era lo mejor. La construcción de la Nueva Maat'Kare tomó, casualmente, "
"dieciséis meses, y al final fue fácilmente la ciudad más grande de todo "
"Netjer-Ta."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:907
msgid ""
"Even though he had been the author of the idea, Akhen couldn't avoid feeling "
"sad at the sight of Maat'Kare being emptied. He was the last to leave it; "
"after wandering those streets one last time, he turned his back to the City "
"of the Sun forever."
msgstr ""
"Aunque él había sido el autor de la idea, Akhen no pudo evitar sentir "
"tristeza al ver cómo Maat'Kare se vaciaba. Fue el último en abandonarla; "
"después de recorrer esas calles por última vez, le dio la espalda a la "
"Ciudad del Sol para siempre."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:911
msgid ""
"The Maat'Karians adapted quickly to their new city, as did the Chomi and the "
"Aeserians - who, in the end, chose to stay there, and were warmly received "
"by the Seer's people. Branwyn became famous for her songs, and even built a "
"school of music, with the patronage of Atenak - who, together with "
"Smenkhare, founded and presided over the Defence Committee of New Maat'Kare. "
"Merwe helped Sadjet organize the new Academy; she also developed a whole new "
"school of magic based on star energy. Decades later, those who managed to "
"master this difficult lore were renowned as Star Masters."
msgstr ""
"Los maat'karianos se adaptaron rápidamente a su nueva ciudad, al igual que "
"los chomi y los aeserianos, quienes al final decidieron quedarse allí y "
"fueron recibidos con calidez por el pueblo del Vidente. Branwyn se volvió "
"famosa por sus canciones e incluso construyó una escuela de música, con el "
"patrocinio de Atenak, quien junto con Smenkhare fundó y presidió el Comité "
"de Defensa de la Nueva Maat'Kare. Merwe ayudó a Sadjet a organizar la nueva "
"Academia; también desarrolló toda una nueva escuela de magia basada en la "
"energía de las estrellas. Décadas después, aquellos que lograron dominar "
"este difícil conocimiento fueron reconocidos como Maestros Estelares."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:915
msgid ""
"Atseger returned from her self-imposed exile years later, and became a "
"professor in the New Academy. By that time, Mahyus was the most renowned "
"Umbra Master there, and Merwe had managed to obtain her third light, the "
"Aquamarine one. Some say she might have even obtained the last one, had she "
"tried, but Merwe simply refused to learn the Umbra Arts."
msgstr ""
"Atseger regresó de su exilio autoimpuesto años después y se convirtió en "
"profesora de la Nueva Academia. Para entonces, Mahyus era el Maestro Umbra "
"más reconocido allí, y Merwe había logrado obtener su tercera luz, la "
"Aguamarina. Algunos dicen que incluso podría haber obtenido la última si lo "
"hubiera intentado, pero Merwe simplemente se negó a aprender las Artes Umbra."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:919
msgid ""
"Sigdral and Gomatol married - a marriage that was less about love and more "
"about politics, for that would finally bring both the Aigathol and the "
"Motsoghnir together; notwithstanding, in her visits to her friends in New "
"Maat'Kare, she never seemed discontent with her life. She was also "
"responsible for restoring the Order of Runecrafters."
msgstr ""
"Sigdral y Gomatol se casaron; un matrimonio que tenía menos que ver con el "
"amor y más con la política, porque eso finalmente uniría a los Aigathol y a "
"los Motsoghnir; sin embargo, en sus visitas a sus amigos en la Nueva "
"Maat'Kare, nunca parecía descontenta con su vida. También fue responsable de "
"restaurar la Orden de los Forjadores de Runas."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:923
msgid ""
"Akhen and Nyx lived as happily as they could ever have wished. Adaptating to "
"that new life was hardest for her, but that was solved when Merwe developed "
"a potion that could replace human blood in the vampiress' diet. Not every "
"Maat'Karian was warm towards her, but no one could deny that she was a "
"worthy citizen; the many war orphans that she and her husband raised like "
"their own children all became notable citizens, some of them becoming "
"powerful swordsmen just like their foster-mother, others even managing to "
"bring some vampire clans to their side."
msgstr ""
"Akhen y Nyx vivieron tan felices como podrían haber deseado. Adaptarse a esa "
"nueva vida fue lo más difícil para ella, pero eso se solucionó cuando Merwe "
"desarrolló una poción que podía reemplazar la sangre humana en la dieta de "
"la vampiresa. No todos los maat'karianos eran cálidos con ella, pero nadie "
"podía negar que era una ciudadana valiosa; los muchos huérfanos de guerra "
"que ella y su esposo criaron como si fueran sus propios hijos se "
"convirtieron todos en ciudadanos notables, algunos de ellos convirtiéndose "
"en poderosos espadachines igual que su madre adoptiva, otros incluso "
"logrando atraer a algunos clanes vampiros a su lado."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:927
msgid ""
"Akhen himself didn't take any position of authority. Alongside Branwyn, he "
"built an institute aimed at fostering the arts; he himself became a writer "
"of prose and poetry, claiming that 'people also needed beauty and fantasy in "
"order to live well'. His most famous work was not of fiction; published "
"posthumously, the 'Seer's Scrolls' told of things which Akhen had discovered "
"during his overseas journeys, and prophesied the coming of a person who "
"would be able to vanquish the Sky Dragon..."
msgstr ""
"El propio Akhen no ocupó ningún cargo de autoridad. Junto a Branwyn, "
"construyó un instituto destinado a fomentar las artes; él mismo se convirtió "
"en escritor de prosa y poesía, afirmando que «la gente también necesitaba "
"belleza y fantasía para vivir bien». Su obra más famosa no fue de ficción; "
"publicada póstumamente, los «Rollos del Vidente» contaban cosas que Akhen "
"había descubierto durante sus viajes por el extranjero y profetizaban la "
"llegada de una persona que sería capaz de vencer al Dragón del Cielo..."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:931
msgid ""
"The sea of sand surrounding New Maat'Kare isolated it from the rest of the "
"world as it did to the abyss above which it was built - for New Maat'Kare's "
"chosen location was none other than the Yawning Abyss, where the Sky Soul "
"had remained for centuries, and where it would remain for some more. For a "
"long time, the only contact they had with the outside world was through the "
"dwarves, the wargs and their powerful orcish allies, the Burning Fang clan."
msgstr ""
"El mar de arena que rodeaba a la Nueva Maat'Kare la aislaba del resto del "
"mundo, al igual que el abismo sobre el cual fue construida; porque la "
"ubicación elegida de la Nueva Maat'Kare no era otra que el Abismo "
"Bostezante, donde el Alma del Cielo había permanecido durante siglos y donde "
"permanecería por algunos más. Durante mucho tiempo, el único contacto que "
"tuvieron con el mundo exterior fue a través de los enanos, los huargos y sus "
"poderosos aliados orcos, el clan Colmillo Ardiente."

#. [part]
#: War_of_the_Jewel/utils/intros.cfg:935
msgid ""
"As the ages succeeded each other, the old cities of the Maat'Karians were "
"slowly swallowed by the earth and by nature; even the original City of the "
"Sun, once thriving and splendorous, became a solemn ruin of a glorious, "
"ancient and near-forgotten era..."
msgstr ""
"A medida que las épocas se sucedían, las antiguas ciudades de los "
"maat'karianos fueron lentamente tragadas por la tierra y la naturaleza; "
"incluso la Ciudad del Sol original, alguna vez próspera y esplendorosa, se "
"convirtió en una solemne ruina de una era gloriosa, antigua y casi "
"olvidada..."

